title: oatmeal caramelitas
directions: In a large bowl combine 1 cup flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, soda, salt and melted butter.
Blend well to form crumbs.
Press 1/2 of crumbs into bottom of 11 x 7-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecans.
Blend caramel topping and 3 tablespoons flour.
Pour over chocolate and pecans to cover.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Cut into bars.

title: medley salad
directions: Cut up vegetables.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: mama's beef stew
directions: Cook meat until done; add other ingredients and cook until vegetables are done, adding catsup last.
Serve with crackers or bread.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add shortening and work into pastry blender.
Add milk all at once.
Stir until flour is moistened.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook stew meat on low in crock-pot with onion, Italian seasoning and salt.
Two hours before serving, add soup and sour cream.
Cook noodles; mix with sauce.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: To beaten eggs, add buttermilk and beat again.
Add oil and water.
Beat thoroughly.
Add each dry ingredient and gently mix after each addition.
Do not overbeat.

title: grandma's casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery, green pepper and zucchini.
Add ground turkey or ground chuck or combination of each to make one pound, salt, oregano, garlic, stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce, water and mushrooms.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam. Spread 8 ounce uncooked noodles in bottom of pan.
Cover with sauce, then cover with 8 ounces low-fat skim Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting. Cut into 8 servings.
Contains 3 proteins and 1 bread plus 1 vegetable.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans; season with Accent.
Combine with celery soup and 1/2 of onion rings.
Put in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with rest of onion rings.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes until bubbly hot.

title: jackie's low-cal chicken cacciatore
directions: Cut meat into serving size pieces.
Sprinkle with salt.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Add meat and cook; drain fat.
Add tomatoes, onions, garlic and water or wine.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until meat is just tender.
Add green peppers and cook 15 minutes longer.
Skim fat; simmer sauce to thicken.
Makes 6 to 8 servings at about 202 calories or less.
To reduce calories, add more tomatoes and peppers.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and brown sugar.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and egg in bowl; mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples. Drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: kool-aid playdough
directions: Mix together flour, salt, alum and Kool-Aid.
Add boiling water and oil.
Knead together.
If it is too sticky, add more flour.
Store in airtight container and this will last a long time.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cook pineapple juice, sugar and Perma-Flo until thick.
When cool, add cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Beat until smooth.

title: lump crab meat dish
directions: Saute and brown onion, garlic and bell pepper in 2 tablespoons of margarine. Make crumbs of the crackers. Add 1/2 of crumbs to the sauteed mixture. Add crab meat and mix well. Place in a covered casserole. Thirty minutes before serving, pour the milk over crab mixture. Top with remaining crumbs. Drizzle melted margarine over all. Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa together.
Cream the Crisco and margarine until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well. Add flour and milk alternately and beat well. Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Work together margarine and crumbs into deep square dish and pack down.
In small mixing bowl, cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Put on top of wafer layer; spread can of blueberry pie filling on.
Top with Cool Whip; chill.

title: crab cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray cookie sheet with nonstick vegetable spray.
Combine crab meat, mustard, margarine, egg, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings.
Add 2 to 4 teaspoons bread crumbs to bind.
Shape into 4 cakes (use about 1/2 cup mixture each).
Roll in remaining crumbs; place on prepared cookie sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned, turning cakes over halfway through cooking time.
Serve with lemon wedges, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Make cake in large flat pan (17 x 11 1/2-inch).
Bake about 20 minutes.
Make pudding with 1 cup milk.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Add cool pudding to cream cheese/Cool Whip mixture.
Drain pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip mixture on cooled cake.
Sprinkle nuts and pineapple on top.
Keep refrigerated. Bake at 350°.

title: shake and bake
directions: Mix, then use on chicken or pork chops like Shake 'n Bake mix from the store.

title: steak supper in foil
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Place 24 x 18-inch piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil in baking pan.
Place meat on foil.
Stir together mushroom soup and onion soup mix (dry); spread on meat.
Top meat with vegetables.
Sprinkle water on vegetables.
Fold foil over and seal securely.
Cook 1 1/2 hours until tender.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add boiling water and pineapple.
Chill until firm and add 1 quart whipped topping. Fold in the angel food cake, which has been broken into bite size pieces.
Press mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let set in refrigerator until firm. Top with whipped topping and coconut.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix everything together, except nuts and raisins, in large bowl.
Add nuts and raisins; mix until blended.
Take a teaspoon and drop rounded spoonfuls onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Leave about 3 inches between spoonfuls.
Bake for about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: quick and easy chili with a zip
directions: Brown meat, then drain fat.
Add onion, garlic and bell pepper.
Let wilt.
Add tomatoes, pinto and red beans, chili peppers, seasoning mix, salt, pepper and sugar.
Let simmer on low heat for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and butter or fat. Line pie pan with plain pastry or use a premade pie pastry.
Put in pecans in a layer.
Add egg mixture.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 50 to 60 minutes.
The nuts will rise to the top of the pie to form a crusted layer.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Combine eggs, pumpkin, sugar, salt, ground ginger, ground cloves and evaporated milk.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add cake mix sprinkled over filling.
Cube margarine over cake mix.
Add pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: very easy yeast rolls
directions: Cream sugar, salt, and butter.

title: creamy tuna mold
directions: In a small pan, soften gelatin in cold water; stir over low heat until gelatin is dissolved. In a small bowl, combine tuna, mayonnaise, lemon juice and finely chopped onion; beat until smooth. Blend in dissolved gelatin, sour cream and capers. Spoon into 3 1/2-cup mold; chill until firm. Unmold on a platter lined with lettuce; add garnish of cucumber slices and cherry tomatoes.

title: tropical chicken
directions: Combine orange juice, vinegar, nutmeg and basil; set aside. Lightly coat chicken with flour. In hot shortening, saute chicken until golden on all sides.
Sprinkle with salt.
Add orange juice mixture.
Place potatoes between and around chicken pieces.
Cook, covered, over medium heat, approximately 25 minutes or until chicken and potatoes are tender.
Then add pineapple with juice. Heat, covered, for 5 minutes.
Serve at once.
Garnish with parsley.
Use pan drippings as a sauce if desired.

title: tarragon wine mustard
directions: Blend dry mustard and water in a small bowl.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Combine wine, vinegar, flour, tarragon, salt and allspice in saucepan. Stir in mustard mixture.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Cook for 2 minutes or until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour into bowl.
Chill, covered, overnight. Beat with wire whisk until smooth. Spoon into 8 ounce jars.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields 2 (8 ounce) jars.
Makes great holiday present!

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well; chill or freeze. Thaw before serving.

title: vinegar pie pastry
directions: The indestructible pie crust.
Roll, re-roll and save scraps. Refrigerate or freeze.

title: tortilla soup
directions: To make soup, heat the oil in a large pot.
Add the pieced tortillas, reduce heat and cook until they are golden brown and slightly crisp.
Add the onion and cook 3 minutes longer; add garlic and jalapeno and cook another 2 minutes.
Add the chilies, tomatoes and tomato paste; cook for 10 minutes.
Stir in the cumin and cayenne.
Slowly whisk in the chicken broth and picante sauce. Simmer the soup for about 20 minutes, or until slightly reduced. Add the shredded chicken and avocado and heat until warmed through.
To make garnish, Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Cut tortillas into strips.
Place the strips on a baking sheet and bake for 10 to 15 minutes, or until crisp.
To serve, ladle soup into 6 bowls and garnish with the grated cheese, cilantro and baked tortilla strips.
Serves 6.

title: golden age breakfast
directions: Mix well.
Pour into greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Let stand, covered, for at least 30 minutes or store in refrigerator overnight.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and blend well.
Bake in an unbaked pie shell for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
May be topped with Cool Whip, ice cream or whipped cream.

title: pineapple dressing salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple into pan.
Combine sugar, flour and eggs.
Add to juice and cook, stirring constantly, until thick. Remove from heat and blend in butter.
Cool.
Add pineapple chunks, bananas and marshmallows.

title: chocolate pistachio cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, orange juice, water, eggs and oil in a large bowl.
Blend to moisten, then beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour about 3/4 of batter into a well-greased and floured Bundt pan or a 10-inch tube pan.
Add 3/4 cup chocolate syrup to remaining batter.
Mix well. Pour over batter in pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until done. Cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool on wire rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix together and bake for 40 minutes covered and 25 minutes uncovered in 350° oven.
Put cheese on top towards the end.

title: chocolate chip pan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 10 x 15-inch baking pan.
In a small bowl, mix flour and baking soda.
In a large bowl, mix butter, sugars and vanilla extract.
Add eggs and mix well. Gradually stir in flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate morsels and nuts.
Spread mixture in pan, then spread M&M's on top.
Bake 25 minutes.
Cool in the pan and cut into squares.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Mix noodles, cottage cheese, sour cream and onion together.
Spoon into greased baking dish; top with meat sauce, then top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and brown.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt. add water, vinegar and beaten egg. Blend well. Makes one double crust for pie.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 11-inch baking dish; add peaches.
Mix flour, sugar and milk; pour over top of peaches.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: chicken spread
directions: Mix above ingredients well and serve with crackers.

title: cherry and nut sheet cake
directions: Mix flour, oleo, sugar and baking powder together like pie crust, then add eggs, vanilla and milk mixture.
Roll between wax paper and put on cookie sheet.
If sticky, add more flour.
Put layer of dough, then nuts mixture, another layer of dough, then add 1 can cherries (Thank You).
Put lattice work on top.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine and cook in double boiler until thick enough.
Pour into baked pie shell and chill.

title: steak and sweet pepper saute
directions: Heat 1 1/2 teaspoons olive oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add half the steaks.
Cook until brown on both sides, about 4 minutes for medium-rare or until desired doneness. Remove steak to platter; keep warm.
Repeat with remaining steaks.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in order given in casserole.

title: tropical bar cookies
directions: For crust:
Mix flour, 1/4 cup sugar, butter and 1/4 cup chopped almonds until crumbly.
Press into 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: golden or banana punch
directions: In a large saucepan, mix the sugar and water; bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add the frozen orange juice.
Cool.
Mash or process the bananas with the juice of the lemons.
Add to the first mixture.
Add the pineapple juice.
Stir well.
Divide into two equal portions and freeze.
When ready to serve, place one frozen portion into a punch bowl and pour over 2 bottles or 1 (2 liter) bottle of ginger ale.
Stir.

title: california dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese and Fluff with wooden spoon.
Serve over fresh fruit (strawberries, pineapple, etc.).

title: al's pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients; mix well. Bake in crust which has been baked until set.
Bake for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: frozen ground beef soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in heavy container with top.
Cook until ground beef is done, about 30 minutes.
Then chop meat into large pieces.
Put top back on and cook about 20 minutes longer.

title: lemonade
directions: Squeeze lemons in pitcher.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Fill with water about 2 inches from top.
Stir and chill.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: aunt margaret's asparagus supreme
directions: Layer in casserole and bake in a 325° oven until cheese is melted and casserole is heated through.

title: picante sauce
directions: Put vegetables in blender; chop.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook 30 to 40 minutes after it starts to boil.
Fill jars and seal.
Makes 11 to 12 pints.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken on bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Place cheese on top of chicken. Cover with soup thinned with milk. Mix melted margarine with stuffing and place over cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covered with foil.

title: dirt cake
directions: Blend together Cool Whip, margarine, cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
In a second bowl, blend together vanilla pudding, milk and vanilla.
Combine and mix both mixtures together. Crush Oreo cookies in a food processor until finely chopped.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch dish:
Bottom:
Oreo cookies.
Middle:
Pudding mixture.
Top:
Oreo cookies.

title: spinach dip(for vegetables)
directions: In a covered blender, blend all at high speed until finely chopped. Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
You can make this 1-2 days before serving.

title: pecan delight
directions: Whip egg white until foamy.
Add cream of tartar; whip until stiff, but not dry.
Whip in sugar in small quantities at a time. Fold in crackers, nuts, vanilla and salt.
Bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch dish at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until golden brown. Cool and add whip topping.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: dutch meat loaf
directions: In mixing bowl, combine ground beef, sausage, bread crumbs, onion and 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Beat egg and salt.
Add to meat mixture.
Shape into loaf in baking pan. Bake 30 minutes at 325°. Drain off fat.

title: anita's seacoast salad
directions: Prepare the macaroni as directed.
Add the other ingredients. Chill.
The peas may be cooked slightly or just thawed.

title: butter crumb cod
directions: Combine all ingredients except fish. Mix well. Place fish in baking dish and spread mixture over top. Bake 350 degrees for 30-40 minutes. Done when fish flakes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all together good.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) cake pans at 350° for 30 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: homemade reese's cups
directions: Melt margarine and pour
over cracker crumbs.
Mix well and add peanut butter.	Fold
in
powdered
sugar,
then press into 9 x 13-inch sheet
cake pan.	Melt Hershey bar and spread evenly over mixture.
Let	cool
until
chocolate	begins	to harden and cut into desired sizes.

title: can't leave alone bars
directions: In a bowl, combine the dry cake mix, eggs and oil. With floured hands, press 2/3 of the mixture into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Set remaining cake mixture aside.

title: fruit dip
directions: Save pineapple juice to dip into mixture.
Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: crumb coffee cake
directions: Crumb flour, sugar and Crisco together.
Save out 1 cup of crumb mixture for topping.
Put soda into buttermilk, mix into crumb mixture.
Add egg, salt and vanilla.
Beat vigorously.
Pour into large oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup crumb mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: special k cookies
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a rolling boil.
Set off burner.
Add peanut butter and stir until well mixed.
Add vanilla and cereal. Mix and drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Have peanut butter out of jar and ready to mix in.

title: potato dish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray oblong pan with cooking spray. Add all ingredients, except butter and cornflakes, to potatoes. Mix; spread in pan.
Mix cornflakes and melted butter; spread over potato mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: candy cookies
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Stir in sugar, salt, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Boil exactly 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter, then oats.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
(Cool, then chill.
Store airtight.)

title: spicy picadillo
directions: Brown onions in drippings or butter in a large pan.
Add beef and brown; drain excess fat.
Add garlic, cloves, cinnamon, tomatoes and sugar; simmer for approximately 1 hour, covered.
Add raisins and cumin; simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Add almonds. Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Salt to taste.
Serve hot in a chafing dish with chips.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend soup with barbecue sauce and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Mixture should be very moist to ensure moistness of meatballs.
Shape meatballs and quick fry until browned on all sides.
Place in baking dish and bake for thirty-five minutes.
Drain excess fat and then pour soup and barbecue sauce mixture over meatballs.
Bake for an additional fifteen minutes or until bubbly.

title: stuffed potatoes with ham
directions: Clean and dry potatoes.
Rub skins lightly with oil and Worcestershire sauce.
Bake until tender (about 1 hour at 400°). Remove potatoes, let cool slightly, then slit open and scoop out potato.
Mash potatoes, then mix in sour cream, ham, onions, salt and pepper.
Stuff potato skins with potato mix.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, covered.
Remove cover and sprinkle with cheese; return to oven until cheese melts.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, well beaten egg, salt and chocolate. Beat well.
Sift flour with baking powder and add alternately with milk.
Beat again.
Chill several hours.

title: pretzel dessert or salad
directions: In mixing bowl, cream together margarine and 3 tablespoons of sugar.
Add pretzels.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 10 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.
Cool.

title: beef enchilada casserole
directions: Cook veggies until clear. Add meat and cook until pink is gone. Add water, chili powder and oleo and simmer about 30 minutes or until thickened.

title: crock pot apple butter
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Pour into a 6 qt. slow cooker, uncovered on low, 8 to 12 hours.
Stir occasionally.
After 8 hours check thickness.
If it is too thin continue cooking until it reaches desired thickness. Fill clean pint jars and put on rims and rings.
Secure tightly. Process in boiling water bath for 20 minutes. Remove jars from water.
Lids should pull down as jars cool. Makes 7 to 9 pints.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Spread Oreos in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Soften ice cream and spread on top of cookies.
Warm chocolate, and pour on top of ice cream.
Freeze.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Refreeze.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Add berries last.
Mix all together, stirring for 2 to 3 minutes.
Bake in 2 (8 or 9-inch) layer pans at 350° until done, for 30 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese and tortillas.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Place rounded tablespoonfuls of meat mixture and cheese in each tortilla; roll up tightly.
Place seam side down in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Top with remaining meat mixture.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 minutes.
After removing from oven, sprinkle with remaining cheese and serve.

title: fudge cookies
directions: Mix eggs and sugar; add flour gradually.
Then add soda, salt and nuts.
Place on a greased pan and cook in a low 250° to 275° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sauteed-de-deer backstrap
directions: Cut backstrap into 1/4-inch thick fillets.
Season with Cajun seasoning and fresh black pepper. Put flour in 1 gallon bag.
Add seasoned meat and shake.
Heat peanut oil in nonstick frying pan. Saute meat on both sides (2 minutes per slice).
Put meat aside in ovensafe stoneware 2-quart pot. Pour off excess oil and make gravy using drippings, water, flour mixture and onions.
Pour this over meat in stoneware pot. Add mushrooms (sliced), mushroom soup and wine. Cover roast
and bake at 350° for 90 minutes. Serve with steamed rice or mashed potatoes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Beef round steak may be substituted.

title: almond tea
directions: Bring 2 cups water to a boil; add tea bags.
Boil other 4 cups of water.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add tea to the sugar and water mixture.
Add the remaining ingredients.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Break broccoli into small flowerets and blanch for 3 minutes. Mix and toss all ingredients.
Serves 4.

title: holiday potatoes
directions: In a large bowl mash hot potatoes.
Add cream cheese and butter; beat well until cream and butter are melted and mixed. Add sour cream.
Blend eggs, onion and milk; add to mixture.
Add salt and pepper to mixture.
Mix well until light and fluffy. Place in greased 9-inch round casserole.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: cream corn
directions: Mix together and bake in a casserole for 1 hour at 350°.

title: the best fruitcake
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Line with waxed paper and grease the paper.
Mix fruits and nuts in a large mixing bowl.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, and sugar over mixture; toss to coat all nuts and fruits with flour.
Set aside. Beat eggs until foamy, then add vanilla.
Pour over fruit mixture and stir just until blended.
Pour into prepared loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: old fashioned dried apple cake
directions: Cook apples until soft, adding enough water to have juice in apples.
Melt butter; add syrup and sugar.
Stir until all is melted.
Remove from heat.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Add flour. Mix well.
Use more flour, as needed, to make dough stiff.
Pinch off enough dough to roll out thin (about 8 to 9-inch round).
Make six or eight layers.
Stack layers; spread apples between each layer.
Top layer will be cake.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: slime cake
directions: Make cake according to directions on box.
Make and bake two 8 or 9-inch layers.
Separately, follow box instructions to make the vanilla pudding, adding the 8 to 12 drops of green food coloring as you blend ingredients.
Cover this mixture and place in refrigerator at least an hour, or until you are ready to use it. (This is the slime.)

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg, margarine and 2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice until crumbly.
Press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually blend in sweetened condensed milk, 2 eggs, pumpkin and 2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice.
Mix well.
Pour over crust and sprinkle with nuts and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: bacon stuffed burgers
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and discard all but 2 tablespoons drippings.
Saute onions in drippings until tender. Crumble bacon; add with mushrooms to skillet and set aside. Meanwhile, combine beef, pork, cheese, pepper, garlic powder and steak sauce in a large bowl.
Shape into 16 patties.
Divide bacon mixture and place over 8 of the patties.
Place remaining patties on top and press edge lightly to seal.
Grill over medium coals until well done.
(Pork sausage in burgers requires thoroughly cooking).
Serve on buns with lettuce if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Put flour in a deep narrow bowl (small mixing bowl).
Make a well in the flour.
Put the 3 eggs and salt in the well.
Begin whipping with a fork.
Gradually the eggs will pick up more and more of the flour.
Keep whipping until you have a soft ball of dough.
Dump onto well floured board.
Knead more flour in until you have a stiff dough that is no longer sticky.
Divide into 3 balls.
Roll out about 1/8 inch thick, making sure your dough is well floured on top and bottom.
Pick up and turn over (should be larger than a pie shell), then cut in 3 to 4 inch wide strips. Stack; flouring well between each strip.
After they are all rolled and stacked, cut across stack to desired width of noodles (1/4 inch).
Cook in large kettle of meat stock or just plain water that you add a teaspoon of salt and 2 tablespoons of oil to. Takes 20 to 30 minutes to cook.

title: portuguese fish chowder
directions: In a deep kettle, fry out pork cubes slowly, turning occasionally, until crisp bits remain. Remove these to use later. In the hot fat, fry onions slowly until soft and golden. Add 6 cups cold water, potatoes, seasonings and vinegar. Boil until potatoes are half done. Add fish chunks. Continue cooking gently until fish is tender. Add the browned bits of pork.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add pineapple to sugar and boil.
Add juices and cool.

title: cherokee casserole
directions: Brown meat in olive oil.
Add onions; cook until tender.
Stir in ingredients in order given, except cheese.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon into a baking dish and top with cheese.
Broil until cheese is melted.

title: rich wild rice
directions: Precook wild rice.
Saute onion, celery and pepper in a little butter.
Break up pork sausage and brown slightly.
Mix with rest of ingredients and bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: applesauce raisin cookies
directions: While stirring ingredients in bowl, simmer the raisins in tiny pan with enough water to cover them and a little to spare.
Be sure to drain water from raisins before adding to dough. Cream the shortening.
Add brown sugar and egg; mix well. Add applesauce. Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture. Add raisins and nuts, if desired.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: creamy turkey and broccoli
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, prepare stuffing mix according to package directions.
Stir in 1/2 can onions. Spread stuffing over bottom of greased 9-inch round baking dish. Arrange broccoli spears over stuffing mix with florets around edge of dish.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Pour into large greased casserole dish. Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes. Insert butter knife in middle.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix together yogurt, Cool Whip and Sweet 'N Low and pour into pie crust.
Chill for at least 1 hour.
My favorite yogurt flavors include:
caramel, banana cream, black cherry and lemon.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar, beaten eggs and melted margarine. Add vanilla. Mix well and pour into two unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Soak gelatin in clam juice.
Blend cream cheese and mayonnaise. Add celery, onion and rest of seasonings.
Add gelatin mixture; blend well.
Fold in shrimp and clams.
Pour into a 6-cup oiled mold.
I use a fish mold.
Chill overnight.
Unmold on large serving dish.
May be decorated to resemble a fish or sprinkled with paprika.
Serve with crackers.
Will serve a large party.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well. Roll into 3/4-inch balls and coat with chocolate.
Makes about 40.

title: seasoned potato wedges
directions: Place potatoes on cookie sheet.
Combine melted margarine, water and seasoning; brush over potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage, potatoes and tomatoes
directions: Fry sausage in pan while loosening it with 2 forks to make clumps (or use your hands).
Fry until browned.
Add diced potatoes and stewed tomatoes.
Stir periodically on low flame until potatoes are cooked.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: In mixing bowl mix together the margarine, oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla; mix these ingredients well.
Add flour, cocoa, salt, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, buttermilk, zucchini, chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix for 2 minutes.

title: glazed kolbassi
directions: Put into crock-pot and stir.
Cut about 1-inch pieces of kolbassi into the sauce and cook about 3 hours.
Enjoy.

title: dill mustard
directions: In top of a double boiler, combine mustard, vinegar, sugar, water, salt and dill.
Cover and let set at room temperature for 4 hours.
Bring water in bottom of a double boiler to a boil; add eggs to mustard mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened, about 10 minutes.
Cool.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: chicken breast in sour cream
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in shallow baking dish; cover with mushrooms.
In a small bowl, combine mushroom soup, orange juice and sour cream; mix well.
Pour over chicken until completely covered.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: red french dressing
directions: Shake all ingredients in tightly covered jar. Refrigerate at least 3 hours. Or mix in a blender.
Will not separate this way. Makes 2 2/3 cups.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix apples with sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Pour in unbaked pie crust.
Beat eggs.
Melt butter or margarine and mix together. Pour over apples.
Bake at 325°.
Easy and good.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Set aside.
Cook spaghetti in water with 1/4 cup cooking oil.
Set aside.
Cook pepperoni in microwave just enough to get grease out of it.
Layer ingredients in bowl as follows:
spaghetti, Mozzarella cheese, sausage, pepperoni, green peppers, onion and top with Parmesan cheese.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Mix salad ingredients in the morning with the bottle of salad dressing.

title: mom's raisin cookies
directions: Combine raisins and water in a small saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cook for 3 minutes; remove from the heat and let cool (do not drain).

title: heather's scottish shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter.
Sift together flour, sugar and salt.
Combine dry ingredients and butter; mix well. Pat dough into an ungreased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Press down evenly. Pierce with a fork through dough every half-inch.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares while still warm.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers and onions in salt water for 5 minutes.
Let remaining ingredients come to boil, then drain and add pickles. Boil for 5 minutes, can hot.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain and add salt, pepper, mushrooms and tomato sauce.
Pour in 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Combine sour cream and herbs.
Unroll crescent triangle and arrange on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes until rolls are brown.

title: cinnamon apples
directions: Core apples with corer.
Be sure to leave apple whole and unsliced.
Gently peel.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Mix together and shape into a ball or serve in a bowl with crackers, etc.

title: quick apple butter cake
directions: Place a layer of graham crackers and a layer of apple butter until you have the desired number of layers, usually 4 to 6 layers. Cover and refrigerate until you are ready to serve it.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: 1 + 1 + 2 = 1 (9-inch) pie crust.

title: chicken curry
directions: Lightly brown onions and celery in hot oil; add flour and blend.
Add broth and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add tomato juice, seasoning and chicken.
Heat thoroughly and serve over rice.

title: party chicken breasts
directions: Wrap each piece of chicken diagonally with a strip of bacon. Cover bottom of casserole pan with a generous layer of chipped beef.
Place chicken in single layer on this.
Cover with combined mushroom soup and sour cream.
No salt or pepper is necessary as chipped beef seasons.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: spanish rice
directions: In medium saucepan, put oil, rice and chicken cubes.
Fry until rice is browned a little, breaking up the chicken cubes while frying.
Add water, tomato sauce, garlic and onion.
Turn on low and cook until all water is absorbed.
Stir and serve.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Cut up tomatoes.
Bring to a boil long enough to soften the flesh,
then
run
tomatoes through a food mill to remove skin and
seed.	Return tomatoes to pot, boiling again.	Stir often
to prevent
scorching.
When the puree is thick enough that
the bubbles splatter, can in sterilized jars and add 1/2 teaspoon canning salt to quart jar of tomatoes.

title: debbie's polish mistakes
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Spread on party rye (can be frozen now to use later or baked now).
Bake on a cookie sheet for 15 minutes in a 325° oven.
Will make an open-faced sandwich. Great for a party.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook sausage over low heat 5 to 8 minutes.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic; saute until tender.
Add beans, tomatoes and seasonings; simmer, uncovered, for about 20 minutes.
Serve over the rice.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cut cooked chicken into bite-size pieces.
Stir mayonnaise, milk, vinegar, pepper and salt together, then add the chicken, grapes, celery and green pepper.
Toss gently to mix.
Spoon chicken salad onto lettuce leaves.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Begin 2 hours ahead.
In 5-quart Dutch oven over medium-high heat, in very hot salad oil, gradually cook flour until dark brown but not burned, about 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in onion, green pepper, garlic, salt and thyme leaves; cook until onion and green pepper are tender, stirring occasionally.

Open oysters and drain liquid into flour mixture; refrigerate oysters. Add tomatoes with their liquid, okra and water; heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer about 30 minutes, or just until mixture thickens slightly.
Add oysters, shrimp, crab and hot pepper sauce; cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until shrimp turn pink and opaque.
Serve in soup bowl with a scoop of rice. Yields 8 servings, or 14 cups.

title: saturday chicken(4 to 6 servings; closely related to sunday chicken.)
directions: Take your chicken and salt and garlic salt it a bit, then paprika it thoroughly. Next, spread it out in one layer in a shallow baking pan. Dilute the soup with the cream. Pour it over the chicken and sprinkle the chopped parsley prettily on top. Bake it, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
When blended, add blueberries.
Bake in greased muffin tins at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Will keep in refrigerator 2 to 3 weeks.
(I also use chopped canned peaches.)

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix
beef, bread crumbs, egg, milk, onion, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Shape into balls and let stand 30 minutes.
Brown in hot oil.
Add
water
and simmer 20 minutes.
Add soup and cook 10 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: red hot dessert
directions: Dissolve red hots in 2 cups boiling water.
Add jello and applesauce.
Refrigerate until set.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: pecan pralines(classic creole new orleans recipe)
directions: Combine heavy cream and sugar in medium size saucepan.
Heat over medium heat, stirring occasionally until mixture becomes golden brown and reaches the soft ball stage*.
Immediately add pecans and lemon juice.
Continue to cook until mixture again reaches soft ball stage.
Drop praline mixture from large kitchen spoon onto oiled cookie sheet into mounds, spreading each into a cake 1/4-inch thick and 4 inches in diameter.
Let harden.
Gently lift each praline with a spatula.
Store in airtight container with wax paper in between.
Pralines are extremely fragile, handle with care.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix together until smooth.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Make frosting about 5 minutes before taking cake out.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch for 3 minutes or until clear; add jello.
Stir then cool.
Slice strawberries into baked pie crust; pour cooked mixture over strawberries.
Top with whipped cream when set.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and vanilla pudding.
Add sour cream and 1/2 carton Cool Whip.
Spread 1/2 of this mixture in bottom of pan.
Put a layer of vanilla wafers on top and then a layer of bananas on top of the vanilla wafers.
Pour remaining mixture on top of this. Spread with other 1/2 cup Cool Whip as topping.

title: strawberry jam cupcakes
directions: Cream
sugar with shortening until fluffy, add eggs and blend well.
Sift
together
flour,
salt,
cinnamon, soda and nutmeg. Add alternately
with
milk to creamed mixture.
Fold in jam and bake in greased muffin pans in moderate oven (375°) for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove
from
pan
and
frost with any favorite frosting.
Makes 20 cupcakes.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chow mein noodles, in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Top with chow mein noodles and bake 15 minutes more.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix butter, shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs.
Blend in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonful into balls.
Mix remaining sugar and cinnamon and roll balls in mixture before placing on an ungreased cookie sheet. Place 2-inches apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: one bowl chocolate fudge
directions: You can add marshmallows to make it sweeter.

title: chicken or shrimp saganati
directions: In 2 teaspoons of the oil, cook onions until golden; add garlic and cook 2 minutes.
Add oregano, cook 2 minutes more.
Add ouso, then tomatoes; partially cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: all bran rolls
directions: Mix, stir, and cool shortening, water, sugar, All Bran and salt.
Add eggs (beaten) yeast and flour; beat thoroughly.
Cover and put in refrigerator overnight.
Take out portions for rolls as needed.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: batter-fried mushrooms
directions: Wipe mushrooms with damp cloth.
In a medium bowl, combine beer, flour and egg.
Dip mushrooms in batter.
Fry in very hot oil, turning with tongs until evenly browned.
Drain on paper towels.

title: triple layer pie
directions: Prepare chocolate pudding with 1 3/4 cups milk.
Pour into pie shell.
Prepare vanilla pudding with 1 3/4 cups milk.
Pour carefully over the chocolate layer.
Fold chocolate syrup into whipped topping and spread over vanilla layer.
Chill for 3 hours.

title: tomato soup
directions: Put all in a crock-pot for 3 to 4 hours to really mix the flavors (or mix everything and leave it overnight in a closed container in the refrigerator and then heat as needed).

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: *Or boil potatoes with peel on them and cut in cubes, if desired.
Do not thaw potatoes if frozen are used.

title: hopping john
directions: Rinse black-eyed peas thoroughly.
Place smoked ham hocks in pot covered with 3 inches of water.
When water boils, add the black-eyed peas.
Season with a bay leaf, cayenne pepper, black pepper, garlic powder and Cajun spice.
Cover, stir periodically, add water if needed.
Cook until peas are tender and ham hocks are done.
Put rice in pot and cover with water up to first knuckle of pointer finger.
Bring to boil.
Once boiling, stir, cover and turn flame off.
Allow rice to steam until cooked.
Serve with chopped onion, hot sauce and corn bread.
Traditional Southern New Year's Day dish.

title: hot smokies
directions: Cook slow in crock-pot 4 hours, or fast 2 hours.

title: beef and peppers stir-fry
directions: Slice steak crosswise into 1/8-inch strips. Combine water, sherry and soy sauce.
Pour over beef and marinate while cutting peppers into thin strips.
Quickly cook peppers in hot oil in large frying pan or wok 3 to 4 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from pan.
Pour off and reserve marinade.

title: drunken dogs(crock-pot cooking)
directions: Cut hot dogs into bite size pieces.
Bring everything to a boil.
Simmer 2 hours.
Eat with toothpicks.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix ingredients together until consistent (batter will be stiff). Butter Dutch oven (bread pans or skillet) and pour stiff batter into Dutch oven. With knife, mark an "X" in top of batter. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until test toothpick comes out clean. Remove from oven and let cool for about 10 minutes. Remove from baking pan and serve warm or cooled. (If made as one large loaf, it may take more than an hour to bake. If divided into smaller loaves, decrease baking time and test for doneness.)

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix well and place in large pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Mix the sugar and cinnamon with the apple slices.
Put into unbaked pie shell.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal; let stand 20 minutes.
Mix sugars and butter.
Then add eggs.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine meat, salt and pepper.
Mix soup with milk or sour cream and chiles in saucepan.
Heat a small skillet with oil to hot.
Heat each tortilla just to soften.
Dip each tortilla in sauce and place a small spoonful in tortilla.
Add some chicken, onion and cheese; roll up.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Blend well cake mix, water, 2 tablespoons creme de menthe, oil and egg whites.
Beat at medium-high for 2 minutes.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until top springs up when depressed.
Cool thoroughly.
Chill.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Lay 1 (12 x 15-inch) piece of aluminum foil on table.
Place hamburger and onion slice; salt and pepper.
Next, add carrots and potatoes; salt and pepper again.
Close up foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Mix well.
Add milk and vanilla; mix well.
Chill about 2 hours.
Drain cherries.
Pat dry with paper towel.
Shape small amount of sugar mixture around cherries.
(Make sure to keep sugar mixture on ice while shaping the mixture around the cherries.)
Allow cherries to chill about 2 to 3 hours.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and boil potatoes.
Drain water and add butter, cream cheese and sour cream.
Mash or mix with mixer.
Put in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: quick skillet meal
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion; drain.
Add beans, rice, water and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil and simmer until rice is done.
Top with any kind of cheese and serve over crunched chips of any kind.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Cook spaghetti, drain.
Combine with remaining ingredients. Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart loaf or casserole pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May be turned out of pan for serving.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: For each serving spread dressing or mayonnaise and salsa on tortilla.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with lettuce and meat.
Roll up, wrap each tortilla in a plastic wrap and refrigerate.

title: chocolate-oatmeal crispies(makes 30 cookies)
directions: Partially melt chocolate in double boiler over medium heat. Remove from heat and stir until all is melted.
Cool.
Sift flour, soda and salt. Set aside.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Boil water; add candies.
Dissolve and add Jell-O and dissolve.
Remove from stove.
Add applesauce.

title: creamy lemon meringue pie(makes one 8 or 9-inch pie)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks; stir in Eagle Brand and ReaLemon.
Pour into crust.
In small bowl, beat egg whites with cream of tartar until soft peaks form; gradually add sugar, beating until stiff but not dry.
Spread meringue on top of pie, sealing carefully to edge of shell.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until meringue is golden brown.
Cool.
Chill before serving. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: pork chop surprise
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use large roasting pan; slice onions on bottom.
Place chops on sliced onions, be sure not to overlap. Slice potatoes in quarters; place on chops.
Combine soup with 1 can of water.
Pour over ingredients; top with salt, pepper and chopped garlic.
Bake 2 hours in covered roaster.
Serves 6.

title: nanna's red hot salad
directions: Cook applesauce until thick.
Dissolve red hots in hot water. Add gelatin and stir to dissolve.
Add applesauce.
Pour half into mold or 2-quart casserole.
Chill until firm.
Blend cream cheese and mayonnaise; stir in celery and nuts.
Spread over gelatin and chill.
Pour remaining applesauce mixture over cream cheese mixture.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaf with mayonnaise, if desired.

title: salad cheese balls
directions: Beat egg white.
Mix with it the cheese and seasoning.
Mold in small balls and roll in cracker crumbs.
Place in the refrigerator for 1 hour or until the egg dries on the outside. Drop in deep fat or oil and fry to a golden brown.

title: easy chocolate freeze
directions: Line 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with waxed paper.
Extend over sides. Mix crumbs with 6 tablespoons margarine; set aside.
Melt 7 squares chocolate and margarine over very low heat, stirring constantly. Cool.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Beat in sugar at high speed of mixer until thick about 10 minutes.
Fold in chocolate mixture and vanilla, then 4 cups of Cool Whip.
Spoon about 1 1/2 cups into pan.
Sprinkle 2/3 cup cookie crumbs; press lightly.
Repeat layers.
Freeze overnight.
Garnish with remaining Cool Whip and drizzle with chocolate.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry onion in bacon drippings. Drain. Brown sausage meat and drain. Combine all ingredients and mix well. Put in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter.
Add powdered sugar and evaporated milk.
Cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Store in quart jar.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and eggs; cool and peel and cut into pieces. Add other ingredients, pickle cubes, onion, pimientos and mustard. Add salt; mix in mayonnaise.
Put in bowl and sprinkle top with paprika.

title: lumberjack stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot and bring to a boil, then let simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Tastes great over rice.

title: vitella con peperoni(veal with peppers)
directions: Cut veal in 1-inch cubes.
Cut peppers in 1/2-inch slices. Fry onions and peppers with olive oil for 15 minutes or until tender.
Cook veal in separate pan with olive oil for 10 minutes. Add tomatoes and cook for 20 minutes.
Add peppers and onions to veal and simmer for 15 minutes over low heat.
Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Mix the remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Combine first bowl of ingredients into last bowl.
Chill.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dice or
chop
cucumbers, tomatoes and onions into very small pieces.
Add
all
ingredients together in a salad bowl. Toss with a spoon.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: turkey roll-ups
directions: Cook the turkey in a pan until done. Combine the cooked turkey with the chilies, spinach, soup and cheese; mix well. Spread the mixture evenly over the tortillas and roll each one up. Use toothpick to secure. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: pecan cheese ring
directions: Place cheeses, onion, mayonnaise and cayenne pepper in a large bowl. Stir until well combined. Place a 3-inch custard cup upside down in the middle of a 10-inch spring-form pan. Sprinkle half of the pecans in the bottom of the pan. Spread cheese mixture on top of pecans. Cover with plastic wrap and chill the mixture until firm, at least 1 hour.

title: cheese egg
directions: Scramble eggs in bowl.
Cut up cheese and put in bowl.
Pour in skillet and cook (scramble) until done.
Amanda loves this for breakfast.

title: oreo ice cream dessert
directions: Pour margarine over cookies.
Spread ice cream on top of cookies.
Mix chips, milk and sugar and drizzle over top of ice cream.

title: jewel box jello
directions: Take the red, orange and lime Jell-Os and dissolve each in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour into 8-inch square pans and chill until firm.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Keep popcorn hot and crisp in 300° oven.
Butter sides of saucepan.
Mix together remaining ingredients, except vanilla. Cook to hard ball stage (250°).
Add vanilla.
Pour slowly over hot, popped popcorn, stirring just to mix thoroughly.
Butter hands lightly; shape into balls.
Makes 15 to 20 balls.

title: lord baltimore cake
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition. Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool completely.
Frost.

title: aunt blondie's chili
directions: Mix all ingredients (except macaroni) together and cook for about an hour (simmer).
Add cooked macaroni for about the last 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar.
Slowly add milk, beating until well blended. Fold into topping mixture.
Ladle into pie shell.
Freeze until firm.
Serve frozen.
Store any leftovers in freezer.
Recipe makes 1 large pie.
Double recipe makes 3 (9-inch) pies.
(March 1986.)

title: chicken wings
directions: Place wings on cookie sheet; drizzle butter over top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn; bake 15 minutes more.
Pour sugar and soy sauce over top.
Bake 15 minutes; turn.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: herbed cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl; stir well.
Use the cheese as a filling for snow peas, celery sticks, cherry tomatoes or cucumber slices.
Can use as a spread for party bread.
Yields about 2 cups.

title: punch
directions: Combine Jell-O, sugar and water in a pan and dissolve. Add pineapple juice and cranberry juice. Pour into containers and freeze.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add eggs, oil, vanilla and buttermilk. Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jerry's biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Measure flour and put in a medium bowl. Cut in shortening until flour becomes coarse crumbs.
Blend in just enough milk, with a fork, until dough leaves sides of bowl. (Too much milk makes dough too sticky to handle; not enough milk makes biscuits dry.)
Knead gently on lightly floured surface 10 to 12 times.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix oleo, 1 1/2 cups sugar, eggs, vanilla, flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt together.
Form small balls and roll in mixture of 3 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 6 to 8 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, salt and pepper.
Place into casserole dish. Pour corn on top. Place in oven at 350° until it begins to bubble around edges. Remove and cover with Tater Tots. Return to oven until Tater Tots are golden brown.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Press each biscuit flat.
Place into ungreased muffin pan, bringing dough up to edge of pan.
Spoon meat mixture into cups. Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Melt oleo in casserole dish and arrange chops on top. Sprinkle over soup mix and rice.
Cover with water.
Bake covered for 1 hour at 350° adding more water if necessary.
You can also add a package of frozen peas if desired about 15 minutes before removing from oven.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Heat oven at 325°.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Stir in sugar and oil; beat.
Add zucchini, pineapple and vanilla.
Beat.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add to zucchini mix.
Beat until well mixed.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan; remove to wire rack.
Cool and serve.
Will freeze until ready to serve.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix milk, flour, sugar and egg in a bowl.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan, then pour can of cherry filling on top of ingredients.
Stir around.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: date nut loaf
directions: Mix together into loaf.
Wrap in wax paper and chill.

title: cranberry congealed salad
directions: Combine the gelatin and the boiling water.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in cold water.
Set aside. Combine the cranberries, orange, pineapple, pecans and sugar.
Mix well.
Stir into gelatin mixture.
Mix well.
Chill until firm.
Serve with creamy fruit sauce.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Mix margarine, Crisco and sugar together.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk alternately with flour.
Add flavorings and then the walnuts; mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube cake pan and bake starting in a cold oven at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Pour into a greased cake pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: fern's no trouble pickles
directions: Slice medium size cucumbers lengthwise; pack cold in quart jars.
Add 1 tsp. salt and pinch of alum in each jar.
Dissolve sugar in vinegar and water; boil rapidly.
Pour over cucumbers in jars and seal.
Process in boiling water bath for about 10 minutes, or until they begin to change color.

title: my grandmother's gingersnaps
directions: Measure flour, soda, ginger, salt and cinnamon.
Cream Crisco until soft.
Gradually add sugar, creaming after each addition, until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg and molasses.
Add flour mixture.
Form teaspoons of soft dough into small balls by rolling them lightly between palms, then roll dough balls in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: deviled celery sticks
directions: In a small bowl, mix together meat spread, pickles, capers, onion, pepper, Worcestershire, sour cream and walnuts.
Fill celery sticks with this mixture.
Arrange on serving plate.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes about 1 cup filling.

title: party tortillas
directions: Mix cream cheese and Hidden Valley Ranch powder together. Blend in chopped green onion and Cheddar cheese.
Spread mixture over tortilla.
Sprinkle equal amounts of pimentos, black olives and green chiles over tortilla.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken breasts; debone and cut into chunks.
Cook broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder over low heat.
Place broccoli in a greased casserole dish.
Put chicken on top of broccoli and pour sauce over chicken.
Top with grated cheese, then buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: patrice's mayonnaise muffins
directions: Mix mayonnaise with flour and sugar; add milk and mix.
Spoon into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Place all ingredients except coconut in electric blender. Cover and blend at low speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into a lightly greased and floured 9 or 10-inch glass pie plate.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
This pie makes its own crust.

title: egg sausage casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: marinated shrimp salad
directions: In a blender or food processor, process vinegar, oil, onions, parsley, garlic salt, basil and pepper until well blended.
In a medium bowl, combine shrimp and red onion.
Pour vinegar mixture over shrimp mixture; stir until well coated and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight to allow flavors to blend.
Serve chilled. Yield:
4 cups.

title: party sandwich for a crowd
directions: Cut bread in half length-wise.
Hollow out top and bottom of loaves, leaving 1/2 inch shell.
Discard removed bread or save for another use.
Combine cheeses, onion, mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce; spread over cut sides of bread.
Layer ham and roast beef on bottom and top halves; place pickles on top of bottom half. Gently press halves together and wrap in plastic wrap; refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Cut into 1 1/2 inch slices.
12-14 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Brown ground meat; drain.
Drain squash.
Place all ingredients in casserole, reserving 1/4 cup cheese for top.
Mix well.
Top with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown onion in hot fat.
Add meat and seasonings; brown.
Add drained beans and soup.
Pour into greased casserole.
Mash potatoes; add milk, egg and seasonings.
Spoon in mounds over meat.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Mix water and sugar; bring to a boil.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill before serving.
Makes two gallons or 40 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Chop onions, garlic and celery.
Beat egg.
Mix beef, sausage and crumbs.
Add onion, garlic, celery and egg.
Mix well.
Add milk, ketchup and seasonings.
Mix well.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in a loaf pan.
Pour tomato sauce over top.
Bake for another 15 minutes.
Take out of pan and pour rich sauce over the top.

title: kookoo sabzi(fried herb patties)
directions: Break eggs in a large bowl.
Add 2 tablespoons of oil, salt and pepper.
Beat well.
Add chopped herbs and greens.
Mix well.

title: banana loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat at low speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into a 9 x 5-inch pan, greased on the bottom.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes, or until springs back when lightly touched.

title: chex party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Heat butter or margarine in shallow baking pan in oven until melted.
Remove.
Stir in salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add Chex, nuts and pretzels; mix until well coated.
Heat for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Spread on paper towels to cool.

title: goulash
directions: Mix together and put into a baking dish. Cover with cheese and bake until hot through and the cheese is melted.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Combine egg whites, corn syrup, water, sugar and cream of tartar in top of double boiler.
Beat for 1 minute at high speed to blend.
Place over boiling water and beat until mixture forms peaks when beater is raised, about 7 minutes.
Remove from boiling water.
Add vanilla and continue beating until thick enough to spread.
Frost top of cake and sides.
Top with fresh coconut if desired.

title: stromboli
directions: If you like peppers or anything else, you can add it along in your filling.

title: kielbasa with sauerkraut and potatoes
directions: Put sauerkraut into a saucepan and mix with kielbasa, cut into 1/2-inch chunks.
Heat to boiling, then simmer an hour or more. Peel and cut potatoes into bite-size pieces, then cook separately until nearly done.
Add potatoes to sauerkraut kielbasa mixture at end of hour, discarding potato water.
Cook until done and flavors have mixed.
Sauerkraut will make potatoes feel firm even when done.
Serve with cornbread.

title: helen's seasoning mix
directions: Mix in large bowl to get evenly mixed.
Store in empty spice containers or canning jars.
If the spice containers are not 3 ounce size, cut back on salt.
Use to personal taste.

title: old fashioned sugar tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening
and sugar together; beat until light. Add eggs, cream
and
vanilla;	mix
well.
With flour, baking powder and salt
(sifted
together), add to shortening, sugar, eggs, cream and vanilla mixture.	Blend well.
Shape into 3 to 4 balls. Chill 1
hour.
Roll
out and cut in doughnut shapes. Bake 8 minutes at 375° or until delicately brown.

title: delicate lemon meringue pie
directions: Pour the lemon pie filling into the baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Add cream of tartar and sugar, gradually, beating until stiff.
Pour meringue on pie.
Place pie in oven. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: norwegian apple cake
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar; blend well.
Add eggs; blend well. Sift dry ingredients.
Add butter and sugar mixture (batter will be stiff).
Add apples.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Drizzle with 10x sugar to make it special.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into baking dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix all but last ingredient and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown, about 25 minutes.

title: valley apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. In a small bowl, combine 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, nutmeg and cinnamon. Sprinkle over apples, tossing to coat well. Spoon apples into pie crust. Drizzle with lemon juice. In a bowl, combine 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup flour; cut in butter until crumbly. Sprinkle over apples. Slide pie into a brown paper bag and fold end over twice. Fasten with paper clips and place on a cookie sheet. Bake 1 hour. Serves 6-8.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple and pie filling in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over.
Cut butter and dab over top.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Boil mushrooms in mixture for 2 minutes.
Cover and let cool. Refrigerate overnight.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Melt butter; mix with cornbread dressing.
Line an 8 x 12-inch pan with half the cornbread dressing mixture.
Set aside.
Cook squash until barely done; drain and mash.
Saute onion; add to squash along with the rest of ingredients.
Put in pan; cover with rest of cornbread mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until bubbly and slightly browned.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: banana freeze pop
directions: Cut
banana in half, insert sticks in cut end.	Roll in peanut butter,
then
in	crushed
peanuts.
Wrap loosely and freeze.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Fix beef roast until done and cut up in small pieces.
Cook all ingredients together for a good 1/2 hour.

title: potato and broccoli casserole
directions: Combine soup, cottage cheese, sour cream and milk, mixing until well blended.
Add all remaining ingredients except cheese; mix lightly.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese; continue baking until melted.

title: zucchini cookies(a favorite with the cookie monster.)
directions: Mix together egg, oil, sugar and molasses until well blended. Combine flour, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and baking soda.
Add oats and zucchini and mix.
Drop by 1/4 cup portions onto greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a spoon.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 12 minutes.
Makes 12 large cookies.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Combine sugar, milk and vinegar.
Mix well until thick.
Toss lightly with cabbage.
Makes about 8 to 10 servings.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim
fat
from
beef.	Cut beef with grain into 2-inch strips.
Cut
strips
across grain into 1/8-inch slices.
Toss beef,
1 tablespoon vegetable
oil, 1 teaspoon cornstarch, the salt, 1
teaspoon
soy
sauce
and white pepper in glass bowl. Refrigerate
minutes.
Cut each tomato into 8 wedges.
Cut green
peppers
into
1-inch
pieces.
Cut onion into 3/4-inch pieces.
Mix
1/4 cup chicken broth, 2 tablespoons cornstarch, 2 tablespoons soy sauce and the sugar.
Heat wok until 2 drops of water bubble and skitter.
Add 3 tablespoons vegetable oil. Rotate to coat.
Add onion, ginger root and garlic.
Stir-fry until garlic
is light brown.
Add beef.	Stir-fry until beef is	brown, about
minutes.
Remove
beef
from wok.
Add 2 tablespoons vegetable oil; rotate to coat side.
Add tomatoes. Stir-fry
30 seconds.
Stir in 1/2 cup chicken broth.
Heat to boiling.	Stir in	cornstarch
mixture.
Cook
and stir until thickened.
Add green peppers and beef.
Stir-fry 30 seconds. Makes 6 servings.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in ungreased muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Dough will keep in refrigerator for about a week. Makes 12 rolls.

title: potato wedges
directions: Melt butter in shallow pan.
Wash potatoes, leaving the peel on.
Cut into wedges.
Mix dry mixture in mixing bag.
Add 4 to 5 potato wedges; shake until potatoes are coated.
Lay potatoes in pan with melted butter.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.
Turn potatoes every 15 minutes.

title: crazy cookies
directions: Melt chips in double boiler.
Remove from heat and add noodles and nuts.
Mix well.
Spoon on cookie trays and refrigerate.
Keep stored in refrigerator.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Make into small balls. Bake on cookie sheet for about 15 minutes or until light brown at 350°.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Blend the soup and water, set aside.
Mix the ground beef, onion, baking powder, milk and rice together.
Make into walnut size balls and place into a 2 1/2-quart casserole and gently pour soup mixture over top. Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes. Uncover for 15 minutes.
Very good with mashed potatoes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter (3 tablespoons) in a 9-inch layer pan in oven.
Sprinkle brown sugar over butter.
Arrange fruit in sugar mixture in pan.
Mix 1/3 cup butter with sugar until creamy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt thoroughly.
Mix pineapple juice into creamy batter. Spread batter over fruit in the pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool a few minutes in pan (so topping doesn't run). Loosen cake from sides of pan.
Place service plate over pan and turn over.

title: boston fish chowder
directions: Cover fish with cold water and bring to boiling.
Use water for fish stock.
Fry bacon until crisp; remove from pan.
Brown onion in hot bacon fat.
Cut potatoes into cubes and add to fried onions.
Strain fish stock into onions and potatoes and cook until potatoes are soft (10 minutes).
Flake cooked fish and add to potatoes.
Add milk, butter and seasonings and reheat.
Sprinkle parsley and dill and bacon bits on top before serving.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Cook for 2 minutes after mixture reaches a full boil.
Stir frequently.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, salt, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Remove when cool. Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: pork chops
directions: Punch chops with meat tenderizer and lemon pepper.
Fry in oil and a little garlic salt.
Just brown this in a casserole dish.

title: fish almondine
directions: Separate whites and yolks of eggs.
Beat yolks and whites separately.
Dip fish into yolks, then into cracker crumbs, then into egg whites and roll in crushed almonds.
Fry in butter. Excellent for salmon or steelhead steaks.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off grease.
Mix ground beef with soup, spaghetti and rice.
Put in casserole dish and top with sliced cheese, grated cheese.
Bake at 300° until cheese melts and casserole is bubbly.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: sweet-sour cucumbers
directions: About 1 hour before serving or up to 2 days before, in large bowl combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 45 minutes to blend flavors, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 cups.

title: fettush
directions: Break bread into bite size pieces; cut all vegetables into small pieces.
Mix bread and vegetables in salad bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well and garnish with black olives. Serves 6.

title: party dessert
directions: Mix Dream Whip according to package.
Add softened cream to Dream Whip.
Fold in pineapple and marshmallows.
Better if refrigerated overnight.

title: pumpkin seeds
directions: Spread clean pumpkin seeds on a cookie sheet.
Let them dry overnight.
Preheat oven to 250°.
Combine butter and salt; toss with seeds.
Bake for 50 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes, or until seeds are lightly browned.

title: oreo crust ice cream dessert
directions: Boil for 15 minutes the chocolate, evaporated milk, sugar and butter.
Cool mixture and spread over ice cream and top with Cool Whip and nuts.
Return to freezer until ready to eat.

title: luann's microwave spice chicken
directions: Mix V-8, vinegar, hot sauce, oregano and garlic powder. Marinate chicken breasts in this mixture for 1/2 hour; reserve marinade.
Place chicken breasts on microwave-safe plate and cover with plastic wrap; microwave on Medium-high for 10 minutes.
Place cooked chicken back into marinade and add celery, green pepper and onion.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Mix cornstarch into marinade and chicken until blended and place in microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Serve over rice with remaining marinade.

title: chili-cheese dip
directions: Brown and crumble sausage. Drain. Set aside.
Melt Velveeta in top of double boiler or in microwave.
Add chili, chili powder and sausage. Serve hot.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and cheese together.
Stir in broccoli; pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Crush crackers and cover top; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice together.
Add pecans and drained fruits.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in 2 (9-inch) prepared pie shells and refrigerate.

title: knox blox
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill.
Once set, cut into bite-sized cubes.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Empty sherbet into a punch bowl.
Pour in ginger ale.
Baste the sherbet with the ginger ale until it begins to melt.
Slice lime and float in the punch.
Garnish with mint leaves.

title: beef and broccoli stir-fry
directions: Slice beef into small pieces.
Mix sugar, soy sauce, baking soda, cornstarch, water and oil.
Add beef and marinate 1/2 hour. Lightly coat wok with oil.
Cook garlic and ginger root on medium heat for 1 to 2 minutes, then add beef marinade; stir often.
Cut broccoli into small pieces.
Place in boiling water for 2 to 3 minutes; drain and rinse with cold water.
Add cooked broccoli to beef.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over beef and broccoli. Cook and stir until beef and broccoli are well coated.
Serve over white rice.

title: easy cinnamon rolls
directions: Cut shortening into flour and sugar.
Dissolve yeast in water and mix into flour.
Stir.
Place in greased bowl for 1 hour. Knead well on lightly floured surface.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Roll up and cut crosswise into 1/2-inch rolls.
Cover; let set overnight at room temperature.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Frost.

title: hominy pie casserole
directions: Brown meat in hot
oil,
add
flour, tomato and seasonings. Brown hominy and onion
in	oil,
add
to meat mixture. Place in casserole, sprinkle
with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli-chicken cups
directions: Be careful in your selection.
Do not choose too young or too old.
When selected, give your entire thoughts to prepare for domestic use.
Some wives insist upon keeping them in a pickle, others are constantly getting them into hot water and some just don't care.
This may make them sour, hard and sometimes bitter. Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience, understanding and some real consideration.
Sweeten them with love and season with kisses. Wrap them in a mantle of charity.
Keep warm with a steady fire of domestic devotion and serve with peaches and cream.
Thus prepared, they will keep forever.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
In another bowl, mix the last 3 and then combine all 6.
Crush a package of Oreo cookies.
Mix some in and pour the rest over the top.

title: my best fudge frosting
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in boiler.
Add margarine, milk, syrup and salt.
Heat to boiling, stirring frequently.
Boil vigorously 3 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Cool.
Beat in 4x sugar and vanilla.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Grease shallow baking dish.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Blend mayonnaise, lemon juice and soup.
Arrange broccoli in dish; top with chicken.
Pour sauce over.
Top with crumbs, butter and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken macaroni
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to package directions. Add chicken and soup.
Heat thoroughly.

title: corn vegetable medley
directions: In saucepan, heat soup and milk to boiling, stirring often. Stir in vegetables.
Return to boiling.
Cover; cook over low heat 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring often.
Stir in cheese.
Heat through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Make a white sauce of flour, butter and milk; add the beaten egg yolks, seasoning and grated cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Let stand a few minutes to cool.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a casserole in moderate oven about 25 minutes. Serve immediately.

title: truffles(from a 1930 chocolate lovers hershey cookbook)
directions: Cream butter.
Combine 2 cups of the sugar and cocoa.
Stir into butter.
Add flavoring to milk and beat into the creamed mixture.
Add enough sugar to make a manageable dough.
If dough is too soft, may be placed in refrigerator to chill.

title: the world's best cookies
directions: Combine sugars and butter.
Cream until fluffy.
Add egg; mix well.
Add oil and vanilla; mix.
Add oats, cornflakes, coconut and nuts; stir well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; add to mixture and combine well.
Form into balls the size of walnuts. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork dipped in water.
Bake at 325° for about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: easy tomato aspic
directions: Heat tomatoes to boiling; lower heat and simmer 2 minutes. Add rest of ingredients and stir until Jell-O is dissolved.
Chill until set.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
(If using 9 x 13-inch pan, bake for 25 to 35 minutes.)

title: chicken under glass
directions: Place chicken breasts in long baking dish in a single layer. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In large saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a rapid boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat, add butter and oats.
Mix well.
Drop on wax paper by spoon, about 2-inches apart.
Let cool.

title: green bean and mushroom casserole
directions: Drain 1/2 juice from beans. Mix soup and beans. Season to taste. Cook for 15 minutes on medium heat. Sprinkle chow mein noodles on top; bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cream cheese apple cake
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sugar and 1 egg; blend and set aside.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add oil and 3 eggs; mix all together.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Reserve 2 cups of batter. Pour remaining batter into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan. Carefully spoon cream cheese mixture over batter.
Spoon over the 2 cups of batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine milk, cream and vanilla pudding mix in a mixing bowl. Whip until thick and then whip in the peanut butter.
Place filling in a baked pie crust.
Top with whipped cream and chill overnight.	Garnish with sliced almonds before serving.

title: grandma evan's hot dutch cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage (do not overcook).
Combine everything but milk. Cook in double boiler.
Stir constantly until thickened.
Remove from fire and add milk.
Beat with wire whip.
Pour over cabbage.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown meat.
Add water.
Cover and cook slowly for 1 hour. Combine brown sugar, cornstarch, vinegar, pineapple juice and soy sauce, stirring constantly until thickened.
Pour over pork; let stand 10 minutes.
Add green pepper, pineapple and onion.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Vegetables should remain crisp.
Serve over rice.

title: easy chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken and cool.
Debone and chop.
Boil spaghetti in chicken broth until tender.
Drain and reserve broth.
Saute celery and onion in butter until tender.
Mix all ingredients in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish and add enough broth to moisten well. Garnish with additional cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: smoothie
directions: Melt white chocolate and butterscotch in top of double boiler. Stir in peanut butter.
Put in little papers and cool.

title: easy turkey asparagus(4 servings)
directions: Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Place asparagus in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Top with turkey.
Pour soup mixture over turkey.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Top with cheese and onion rings.
Bake for 5 minutes, or until cheese is melted.

title: granny's peach preserves
directions: Boil ingredients until the mixture sheets from a spoon, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove it from the heat and add a few chopped maraschino cherries.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: justin wilson's garlic bread
