directions: Slice bread lengthwise.
Mix margarine or butter (softened), garlic and pepper.
Spread mixture over bread.
Sprinkle cheese over.
Wrap in foil and bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Cook over low heat until mix forms a ball.
Stir constantly. Drop on wax paper and knead to remove lumps.
Store in plastic bag.

title: quick mac and meat
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Cook and drain macaroni. Mix tomato soup, macaroni and meat.
Eat and enjoy.

title: special k treats
directions: Heat on low until sugar dissolves.
In separate bowl, pour mixture over 6 cups Special K cereals.
Roll into balls and place on wax paper.

title: k.f.c. chicken(original)
directions: Mix and shake in plastic bag.
Put 1/4 pound of butter in pan and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Heat juice from cherries and pineapple.
Pour over jello to dissolve.
Add softened cream cheese.
Stir until almost smooth. Cool.
Add cherries, pineapple, Coke and nuts.
Chill in desired container to congeal.

title: teriyaki marinade for flank steak
directions: Place all ingredients for marinade in blender, then marinate meat in a covered dish or Ziploc bag up to 24 hours.
Barbecue and enjoy!

title: three cheese chicken bake
directions: In a skillet, saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in the soup, mushrooms, pimentos and basil; set aside.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Cut up chicken and bake for 1/2 hour.
Put pieces of cooked chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cream of chicken soup and milk over the chicken.
Mix stuffing, butter and broth together. Sprinkle this mixture on top of chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken or turkey casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan put 1/2 the stuffing mix.
Cut meat into bite-size pieces and spread over dressing.
Mix soup, milk and water.
Pour over casserole.
Top with cheese if desired.
Bake uncovered 1 hour at 350°.

title: middle east tabouleh salad
directions: Wash burghul with cold water and drain at once, squeezing all the water out.
Add lemon juice, oil, salt and pepper.
Stir well. Let stand a few minutes or until burghul has absorbed the lemon and oil.
Sliced and chopped vegetables must be pretty dry so that when you add the burghul which has been mixed with oil and lemon juice, it will not be soggy, but hold together better.
Add mint last, if you want.

title: lunchbox cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, combine margarine and shortening.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy. Stir in flour and baking soda; stir in cereal and nuts.
Mix well and drop by level tablespoonful on ungreased cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes until golden.
Cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.

title: surprise meringues
directions: Beat egg whites, salt, vanilla and cream of tartar until peaks are stiff.
Add sugar gradually; beat until stiff.
Fold in chocolate bits.
Cover cookie sheet with paper bag and drop on by rounded teaspoonful.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Cool before removing.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix rice and broccoli.
Saute in butter; onions and celery. Add cream of mushroom soup, Cheez Whiz and salt and pepper.
Mix this with rice and broccoli.
Pour in casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Squeeze liquid out when draining spinach.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly; chill 2 hours or more. Roll into balls one inch in diameter.
Freeze or refrigerate until ready to use.
Bake about 30 minutes until golden.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen balls.

title: potato-cheddar soup
directions: Cook bacon in heavy soup pot until crisp.
Drain all but 1 tablespoon bacon grease.
Add onion, chicken broth, carrot, potatoes and seasonings.
Add water to cover.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add flour to hot water in covered jar and shake to make a smooth, thin paste.
Slowly add to simmering soup, stirring constantly.
Cook 5 minutes to thicken.
Add sherry and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Correct seasonings.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix the oleo, eggs and 1 1/2 cups sugar together real good, then add dry ingredients.
Roll into balls size of walnuts.
Mix the 2 teaspoons sugar and the cinnamon.
Roll the cookies into the sugar-cinnamon mixture; bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: garlic beans
directions: Put beans in bowl.
Place garlic buttons around in beans.
Mix vinegar, cooking oil, sugar and pepper.
Pour over beans.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
Leave overnight.
Drain off all liquid and serve.

title: frosted coffee cookies
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add egg and hot coffee. Sift next 4 dry ingredients and add to the first mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Frost while still hot with confectioners sugar.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Coat large saute pan with oil.
Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Brown chicken over medium heat, allow 7 minutes each side or until no longer pink.
Sprinkle chicken with cumin, garlic powder and Mexican spices before turning.
Remove chicken to a platter, allow to cool.
Saute onion and garlic in chicken drippings until tender.
Add corn and chiles. Stir well to combine.
Add canned tomatoes, saute 1 minute.
Pull chicken breasts apart by hand into shredded strips.
Add shredded chicken to saute pan, combine with vegetables.
Dust the mixture with flour to help set.
Microwave tortillas on high for 30 seconds. This softens them and makes them more pliable.
Coat the bottom of 2 (9 x 13) pans with a ladle of enchilada sauce.
Using a large shallow bowl, dip each tortilla in enchilada sauce to lightly coat.
Spoon 1/4 cup chicken mixture in each tortilla.
Fold over filling, place 8 enchiladas in each pan with seam side down.
Top with remaining enchilada sauce and cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes in preheated 350 degree oven until cheese melts.
Garnish with chopped cilantro, chopped scallions, sour cream and chopped tomatoes before serving.
Serve with Spanish rice and beans.

title: drop cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Mix in milk, powder, salt, and flavoring.
Add flour in small portions.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until very light brown.
If cooked too long, they will get hard. Otherwise, cookies are light and fluffy.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake by directions on box.
When you take it out of the oven, make holes in cake with wooden spoon handle.
Pour condensed milk and caramel into holes, after the two have been mixed together.
Cool cake in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.
Top cake with Cool Whip and crumbled Heath bars.

title: frozen chocolate mousse(10 to 12 servings)
directions: *Optional:
Substitute 2 cups graham crackers, or butter cookies, or animal cookies, or Nilla wafers, or...and 1/4 cup melted butter for crust.

title: black's brown rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together, pour in covered casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pop-up pizza casserole
directions: Mix
all ingredients, except cheese, with hamburger and simmer 10	minutes.
Pour	hot
meat
mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan
and cover with cheese.
Pour Pop-Over Batter over cheese, covering completely.

title: chocolate pudding delight
directions: You will need an 8 1/2 by 11-inch ungreased pan.

title: daddy's hamburger supreme
directions: Mix together ground beef, potato, carrot, onion, spices and egg. Shape into patties; brown on both sides in Crisco in a heavy skillet.
Remove patties onto a plate with paper towel to absorb grease. Add soup, water and pimentos to skillet, mix well and bring soup mixture to a slow boil.
Return patties to skillet, top with green pepper slices and spoon soup mix over top. Cook 45 minutes over a simmering heat on top of stove.
If desired, serve with mashed potatoes using gravy over the potatoes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer about 10 minutes.
Then it's ready to use.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except potato chips and cheese; blend well.
Spoon into a lightly greased casserole; sprinkle with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.
This recipe makes six servings.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, margarine and cream cheese well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour, beating until batter is smooth.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a greased and lightly floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: salmon confetti
directions: Drain salmon.
Reserve liquid.
Cook macaroni.
Saute onion, green pepper and celery in butter for 10 minutes.
Stir in flour. Cook, stirring, for 2 minutes.
Add milk; stir until thickened. Stir in reserved salmon liquid, salt and pepper and 2 cups cheese. Cook, stirring, until cheese is melted.
Stir in pimento, salt and pepper.
Combine macaroni and salmon mixture in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until very hot.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite sized pieces (this should take about 2 months).
Add brown gravy to cover.
Salt and pepper.
Cook over a kerosene fire about 4 weeks at 465°.
Makes about 3,800 servings. If more guests are expected, add 2 rabbits.
Do so only if necessary, however, as most people do not like hare in their stew.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cut chicken into cubes.
Mix all ingredients and chill. Serves 12.

title: apple bundt cake(very healthy)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix juice, oil, egg whites, sugar and vanilla together; add apples and stir well.
Add rest of ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Spray Bundt pan with nonstick spray; add batter and bake for 1 hour.
Let cool before removing from pan.
Serves 24.

title: salisbury steak patties
directions: Combine these first ingredients, cover and refrigerate for a short time.
Then make into 6 large patties and brown in 3 tablespoons bacon drippings.
When browned, add 2 cans of beef gravy, 2 tablespoons sherry and 1/4 pound fresh mushrooms.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Drain off grease.
Stir in pizza sauce.
Simmer for 5 minutes on medium-low heat.
While this is cooking, split English muffins in half and toast in oven.
Put ground beef and pizza sauce mix on muffin halves and top with half slice of cheese.
Broil in oven until melted.
Quick supper.
Kids love these.

title: a.1. chili(serves 6)
directions: In a large heavy pot, over high heat, cook beef, green pepper, onion and garlic, stirring frequently until beef is browned, about 15 minutes.
Stir in chili powder.
Cook, stirring for 1 minute. Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid.
Chop tomatoes and add tomatoes and liquid, steak sauce and water to beef mixture. Heat to a boil. Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: pecan chewy cookies
directions: Melt shortening.
Add sugar.
Cream together.
Add well beaten eggs.
Add vanilla and the sifted dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts. Bake in a shallow pan (8 x 12-inch), greased and floured at 350°.

title: one step pound cake
directions: Combine cake ingredients in a bowl and beat at low speed for 3 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured 12 cup tube pan at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool.

title: coconut balls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and cook about 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, add nuts and Rice Krispies, blend well and shape into balls while it is hot and roll balls in coconut.

title: cottage cheese-tomato appetizers(low calorie)
directions: Cut small slice off bottom of tomatoes and set flat.
Cut thin slice from tops and spoon out centers with melon baller or spoon and discard.
Invert and chill.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish one layer deep.
Mix sauce and bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken and bake in a 400° oven for 1 to 1 1/4 hours until tender.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix with milk and sugar and slowly beat in Cool Whip and vanilla until mixed.
Cube cake or tear into small pieces and put in deep glass bowl in layers: 1) cream cheese mixture, 2) pieces of cake, and 3) cherries (spoon in juice along edges so that it runs down sides).
Continue layers, ending with cream cheese and cherries on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Saute first 6 ingredients together for 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms and white wine.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
A great side dish for chicken.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon, reserving about 3 tablespoons drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside. Cook onion in reserved drippings until tender.
Stir in pork and beans, brown sugar, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and mustard. Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered at 350° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours or in microwave on High for 15 minutes. Stir; top with bacon.
Let stand a few minutes before serving. Makes 6 servings.

title: oreo supreme
directions: Mix 3/4 Oreos with margarine, reserving 1/4 of the Oreos.
Pat in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix pudding and milk; pour over Oreo mixture.
Spread 12 or 16 ounces of Cool Whip over pudding mixture.
Sprinkle with reserved Oreos.
Refrigerate.

title: stuffed eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash. Combine yolks, crab meat, celery, bell peppers and salad dressing. Mix in sour cream.
Blend well.
Refill egg halves.
Chill.

title: cheese cake chilled
directions: Combine ingredients into large bowl with electric mixer and mix on medium speed 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill about 2 hours and add whipped cream on top.

title: famous meat loaf(serving 100)
directions: Mix thoroughly and make into firm loaves.
Bake at 350° in convection oven until done, about 1 hour.
To test, stick a fork in the middle.
If no red juice comes out on fork, it is done.

title: okra with corn and tomatoes
directions: Prepare okra as directed.
Fry bacon until crispy.
Remove bacon and reserve grease.
In a medium size pot, stir okra, corn, onion, salt and red pepper sauce into reserved bacon grease. Cover and cook over medium heat until corn is tender.
Stir in tomatoes; simmer for a while longer.
Stir in bacon.
Simmer an additional 4 minutes.
Sprinkle fresh pepper over vegetables.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken in seasoned water.
Remove chicken when done to cool.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth left after cooking chicken. Drain all but 3/4 cup of broth off spaghetti.
While spaghetti is cooking, saute onion and pepper in butter until soft.
Add sauteed vegetables and remaining ingredients to cooked spaghetti.
Add boned chicken meat.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add Tabasco to your families taste.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple (reserve juice, add enough water to equal 1 cup).
Heat this cup liquid, dissolve black cherry jello in the hot liquid.
Add pie filling and pineapple to jello, let set up in refrigerator.
Beat cream cheese, add sour cream, sugar, vanilla and add pecans.
Spread over set jello.

title: peanut butter icing
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Ice peanut butter cookies when mixed thoroughly.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: Rinse bean sprouts under running cold water; drain.
Heat 1 tablespoon vegetable oil in 10-inch skillet until hot.
Rotate skillet until oil covers bottom.
Cook and stir mushrooms in oil over medium heat until coated, about 1 minute.
Add bean sprouts, rice, chicken and onions; cook and stir over medium heat, breaking up rice, until hot, about 5 minutes.
Push rice mixture to side of skillet.
Add 1 tablespoon vegetable oil to skillet.
Add eggs; cook and stir over medium heat until eggs are thickened throughout but still moist.
Stir eggs into rice mixture.
Stir in soy sauce and white pepper.
Makes 4 servings.

title: white barbecue sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender.
Pour into container and refrigerate.
When marinating meat, especially poultry, use glass or plastic dish.
Marinates best overnight.
Also acts like a tenderizer.

title: lemon blueberry coffee cake
directions: In a bowl, combine the egg, sugar, lemon peel and milk; mix well.
Stir in the biscuit mix just until moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour into greased 9 inch round baking pan.

title: bread and butter pickles(servings:  4)
directions: Cover cucumbers, onions and salt with water and let set overnight.
In morning, drain.
Cook, adding rest of ingredients, until transparent.
Pack hot in pint jars.
Makes 10 to 12 pints.

title: sweet dills
directions: Drain liquid from dill slices.
Layer pickles.
Then cover with sugar, layer of pickles, then sugar alternately until all pickles are used.
Alternately turn jar over each day until all sugar is dissolved.

title: holderkuchlein(elderberry "fritters")
directions: *50-50 oil and butter works best.

title: relish tray dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl.
Chill.
Serve with raw vegetables or chips.
Makes 1 quart dip.

title: grandfather lee christmas fruit cookies
directions: Combine shortening, salt and extract and blend.
Add sugar gradually and cream well.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift flour and soda and add to creamed mixture, alternating with milk, mixing thoroughly.
Add fruit and nuts and blend.
Drop small rounds on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: huckleberry salad
directions: First Layer:
Mix 2 packages jello, 2 cups hot water and 1 cup cold water.
Let jell.

title: pauline's no-bake cookies
directions: Boil together the sugar, butter, milk, peanut butter and cocoa for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add oats, coconut and vanilla. Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.
Allow to cool.

title: pineapple cherry squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix well the first 4 ingredients.
Add 7-Up.
Do not overbeat. Grease and flour lightly 2 (10-inch) cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and seasoning mix.
Layer on tray.
Put taco sauce over cheese.
Put tomatoes, lettuce, cheeses and olives next.
Serve with taco chips to scoop.

title: pasta salad
directions: Slice all vegetables together.
Cook noodles and drain.
Add noodles to vegetables; add Italian dressing and chill.
Serve with bacon bits.

title: better than ever chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Poke holes with wooden spoon when cake comes out of oven.
Pour Eagle Brand milk carefully in holes. Cover with caramel topping.
Let cool and refrigerate.
Cover with Cool Whip, then sprinkle with Heath bars.

title: betty crocker wedding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease bottoms of pans with shortening; dust with flour.
Beat all ingredients in large bowl on low speed, scraping bowl until moistened.
(Batter will be thick.)
Beat on medium speed 2 minutes.
(Batter will be lumpy.) Pour into pans evenly.
After baking, cakes measure about 2 inches in center.
Run knife through remaining batter.
Refrigerate remaining batter.
Bake as directed or until toothpick comes out clean.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes depending on size of pans.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken breasts in shallow baking pan.
Place 1/2 slice of Swiss or Mozzarella cheese on top of each breast.
Mix soup with wine and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle top with dressing mix. Drizzle butter over mix.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: baked seafood bisque(servings:  4)
directions: Make white sauce from butter, flour, milk and seasonings. When thickened, add cheese and sherry.
Combine with thawed seafood.
At this point, it may be refrigerated or frozen.
Put in individual ovenproof dishes.
Top with remaining cheese and crumbs.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 20 minutes until brown and bubbly. Serves 4 to 6.

title: oreo fudge pie
directions: Spread ice cream in crust; top with fudge sauce.
Freeze until firm, about 6 hours.
To serve, garnish pie with whipped topping and cookies.
Makes 8 servings.

title: low-fat chili
directions: In a large pot, brown ground round; stir in chopped onions and pepper and brown until onions are transparent.
Add chili powder; stir and add tomatoes and beans.
Cook on low heat approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Top with shredded cheese if desired.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and butter.
Line a 9 x 13-inch dish with 1/2 mixture.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip. Spread 1/2 of this mixture over cracker crumbs.
Top with cherry filling.
Add remaining cream cheese mixture; top with remaining crumbs.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: gingerbread
directions: Beat together shortening, egg yolks, sugar and sorghum.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
All alternately with the cup of hot water.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over pork-n-beans.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.

title: buttermilk gingerbread
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Start oven 10 minutes before baking.
Sift flour; measure and resift 3 times with salt, soda and spices with beater.
Cream butter until smooth; add sugar and egg and beat until smooth and fluffy.
Add molasses and beat hard 2 minutes longer.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk alternately.
Turn batter into pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or sauce.

title: ham and chicken supreme
directions: Cut ham and chicken into bite-size pieces.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach in the box. Beat egg yolks. Mash cream cheese and add both to the hot mushroom soup. Add spinach, beaten egg whites and Parmesan cheese. Put in buttered casserole. Bake 15 minutes. Last 2 minutes, top with onion rings and add a little cheese to top.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 10-inch skillet, cook zucchini and onion in margarine or butter until tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in seasoning.

title: baked cheese ball
directions: Open crescent roll dough and press seams together.
(Dough should be a rectangular shape.)
Place cream cheese in center of dough; coat with dill or chives.
Fold dough together to cover cream cheese block.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Take out and brush with beaten egg.
Return to oven for 10 minutes at 400°, until golden brown.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Add all other ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole.
Top with crumbled Ritz crackers and dots of butter.
Bake for 25 or 30 minutes in 325° to 350° oven.

title: poor man fruitcake
directions: Heat applesauce and margarine.
Add spices.
In large bowl, beat eggs and sugar. Add flour, one cup at a time.
Mix well.
Add other ingredients. Bake 3 hours at 300° in tube pan.

title: albondigas soup
directions: In medium bowl, combine ground beef, rice, egg, cilantro, seasoned salt and ice water. From into small meatballs. In a large saucepan, combine broth with vegetables and garlic powder with parsley. Bring to a boil. Add meatballs. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes, stirring occasionally. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: preserved cucumbers
directions: Wash small cucumbers and pack in fruit jars.
Make liquid of water, salt and vinegar.
Pour over pickles until jar is full, then seal.
These are good eating as salt pickles.

title: chicken chop suey
directions: Cook chicken and shred in long thin strips (1 to 1 1/2 cups). In a skillet, heat cooking oil and saute onions until lightly brown.
Add celery, cabbage and salt; cook for 5 minutes.
Add chicken, soy sauce and broth.
Cook over low heat.
Cover until vegetables are done.
To thicken broth, use cornstarch or flour (blend with 1 tablespoon cold water).
Serve hot.
May add additional vegetables.

title: cara jeanne's cranberry orange nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Stir in butter or margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in orange peel, orange juice and egg, just until all flour is moistened. Stir in cranberries and nuts.

title: pots de creme au chocolat(mousse)
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat half and half until tiny bubbles form around edge of saucepan (do not allow half and half to boil).
Stir occasionally with rubber spatula.
Remove double boiler top to work surface and with rubber spatula, beat egg yolks into the melted chocolate until smooth, then stir in sugar.
Gradually stir half and half into the chocolate mixture until thoroughly blended.
Replace double boiler top over simmering (not boiling) water.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture coats back of spoon, about 15 minutes.
Stir in 2 teaspoons vanilla extract.
Pour mixture into 6 (6 ounce) cups or stemmed glasses.
Refrigerate for about 4 hours or until mixture has set.

title: no bean chili dip
directions: In pie plate, spread cream cheese evenly on bottom.
Pour no bean chili over cream cheese.
Spread taco cheese over chili, place in microwave until cheese on top is melted.
Do not overcook.
Serve with taco chips.

title: chess bars
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl until crumbly.
Press mixture into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Cover with topping.

title: creamy strawberry jello dessert
directions: You will need a decorative jello mold pan or any deep glass pan like a casserole pan. Prepare 4 hours ahead of time.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix all 6 ingredients with electric mixer. Stir in crumbled cheese.
Makes about 1 1/2 quarts.

title: hamburger and corn pone pie
directions: Brown meat and onions in shortening.
Add seasonings and tomatoes.
Cover; simmer over low heat for 15 minutes.
Add beans. Pour meat mixture into greased casserole.
Top with corn bread batter, spreading with wet knife.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 425° oven.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add the milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until thick and bubbly.
Stir in the potatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook for 5 minutes or until all ingredients are thoroughly heated.

title: iron skillet cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put shortening in 9 inch iron skillet. Heat in oven because skillet must be very hot when batter is put into it.
Mix corn meal, salt, soda and sugar in bowl.
Add boiling water to coat the meal (improves texture).
Add buttermilk, eggs and baking powder.
Mix well.
Remove hot skillet from oven, pour excess melted fat into batter, mix again quickly and pour batter into hot pan.
Bake 20-25 minutes.
Brown top quickly under broiler.

title: italian scalloped potatoes
directions: In a greased quart dish arrange half the potatoes and half the onion.
Sprinkle with half the cheese (both); repeat layers.
Heat oven to 400°.
In small bowl combine soup, milk, Italian seasoning and garlic powder; spoon over potatoes.
Cover and bake one hour. Uncover; bake 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: short cut blind pigeons
directions: Mix meat, egg, rice, garlic powder and salt.
Steam coarsely chopped cabbage (drain).
Layer cabbage and meat mixture in casserole.
Mix tomato soup and tomatoes together.
Pour over mixture.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
One-third cup rice makes 1 cup cooked rice.

title: nutmeg log cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Beat in sugar and eggs.
Mix in flour, nutmeg, soda and salt.
Shape in long rolls on sugared board about the size of your finger.
Cut in 2-inch diagonal lengths.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: traditional english muffins in a loaf
directions: Grease and sprinkle with cornmeal two 8 x 4-inch loaf pans. Combine 3 cups flour with yeast, sugar, salt and soda.
Heat milk and water until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add to dry ingredients and beat well. Stir in remaining 3 cups flour to make a stiff batter.
Spoon into prepared pans.
Sprinkle tops with cornmeal. Cover and let rise in a warm place, free from drafts, for 45 minutes.

title: turkey salad bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all but cheese and chips and put in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle top with cheese and then chips.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: cherry divinity candy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over low heat, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Cook to hard ball stage (250°).
Beat egg whites stiff but not dry.
Add gelatin, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Beat until peaks form.
Pour syrup in fine stream over beaten egg whites until mixture will stand in peaks and loses its gloss.
Add nuts.
If too stiff, add a few drops of hot water.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant lengthwise.
Scoop out insides, leaving 1/3-inch in shell.
Cook in saucepan with little water until tender. Drain.
Add butter and rest of ingredients (egg last).
Mix well, put in eggplant shells and bake at 325° for about 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve as main dish or side dish.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Congratulations to all of the parishioners, staff and priests of St.
Mary's Church of the Immaculate Conception.
The past 150 years have been filled with great events as your community of faith has continued to steadfastly grow in the gospel.
May the next 150 years be so filled with God's abundant blessings.
Good luck in all of your endeavors and may peace and happiness fill your hearts.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Mix together and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Set aside.
Put 1 stick oleo, cocoa, oil and water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; pour over flour, etc. mixture.
Then add eggs, buttermilk and soda.
Mix well and bake in an ungreased cookie sheet pan at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chow mein noodle cookies
directions: Melt chips in a double boiler and pour over noodles and peanuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Cool 1 hour.

title: turkey-noodle parmesan
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, prepare noodles according to package directions; drain.
In same saucepan, combine soup, milk, 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese and black pepper.
Add noodles and turkey.
Over low heat, heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with parsley and Parmesan cheese.
Garnish with onion strips, if desired.
Prep time:
20 minutes.
Cook time:
10 minutes.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of chicken soup

title: rose's pimiento cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix well. Serve on bread or with crackers.

title: chicken cutlets
directions: Marinate cutlets in eggs, water, paprika and garlic for 2 hours.
Bread marinated chicken in seasoned bread crumbs and saute in margarine.
Place browned chicken in oblong casserole dish, lined with foil.
Add chicken broth, wine, cheese, mushrooms, etc. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove foil cover and bake 15 minutes more.
Serve over rice.

title: tomato potato soup
directions: Saute onion in oil until soft.
Add tomato paste, garlic powder and water and bring to a boil.
Add potatoes and simmer until soft.
Add oregano and salt.
Just before serving, stir in cheese.
Serve in mugs for a special treat.
Serves 7.

title: la donna's pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed for 5 minutes.
Add sugar, then stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and spices.
Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Pour into a 15 x 10-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Have a hand or dish towel, sprinkled with powdered sugar, ready.
Remove cake from pan at once and place on towel.
Roll up in towel and cool.

title: golden crumb broccoli
directions: Cut up broccoli to make about 6 cups.
In saucepan, cook broccoli, covered, in small amount of boiling salted water for 15 minutes; drain well.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, cheese, pimiento and lemon juice.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with crushed crackers.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: graduation sandwiches
directions: Chop chicken and celery fine.
Add salad dressing and seasonings.
Blend well.
Trim crusts from bread.
Spread with spicy chicken mix.
Roll to form diplomas, then tie with narrow ribbon or use pimento slices.

title: apple chip cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Add salt, baking soda, cinnamon, flour and vanilla.
Add apples and walnuts.
Bake in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not cover tightly to store.

title: hot sauce
directions: Mix ingredients and cook 1 hour; stir often.
Put in jars. Put in hot water bath for 15 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter over low heat and add cocoa.
Mix flour and sugar together and add eggs and vanilla.
Combine both mixtures and pour into greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: corn-potato chowder
directions: Heat margarine in saucepan until melted.
Stir in onion and cook until tender.
Stir in package potatoes with sauce mix, water and milk.
Heat to boiling, stir frequently.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer, stirring frequently, until potatoes are tender (20 to 25 minutes).
Stir in corn with liquid, salt, pepper and red pepper sauce.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes more.
Recipe can be doubled, just as good the next day reheated.

title: striped delight
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 c. sugar and melted butter. Press firmly into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese with sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Fold in half of Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Prepare pudding as directed on package, using 3 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over cream cheese layer. Chill several hours or overnight.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding.
Garnish with grated chocolate or chopped nuts, if desired.
Makes 15 servings.

title: baked beans and ground beef
directions: Rub chicken with butter and salt.
Pour drippings over chicken as it bakes.
Bake at 375°.
Bake a 2 to 2 1/2 pound chicken for 1 1/4 hours, a 2 1/2 to 3 pound chicken for 1 1/2 hours and for a 3 to 4 pound chicken 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: wilted cabbage
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and set aside.
To fat in pan, add onion, sugar, vinegar, salt, and pepper.
Stir.
Add shredded cabbage.
Cook on medium heat, uncovered for 15 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Drain and place in dish.
Sprinkle with bacon and serve.

title: ranch vegetables
directions: In casserole dish mix dressing mix and oil.
Add frozen vegetables and toss.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes.

title: 5 day pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers. Put in gallon jar with garlic and dill. Mix vinegars and salt and pour over cucumbers. Put in refrigerator for 3 to 5 days or longer. Serve cold.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix together, eggs, sugar, cocoa and shortening.
Add plums and raisins.
Gradually stir in flour and salt.
Mix well.

title: spicy franks
directions: Cut franks in 1-inch pieces. Brown in butter. Stir in remaining ingredients. Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Stir now and then.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Prepare salad in a large bowl.
Add ingredients, one at a time, as given, each in a separate layer.
Do not toss.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.

title: emerald cabbage
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add cabbage, celery, green pepper, onion, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook vegetables over low heat 10 to 12 minutes, stirring mixture often.
Serve at once.

title: crabmeat bites
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread on split muffins and freeze. Broil 5 to 8 minutes until brown.
Cut in quarters.

title: jiffy caramel corn
directions: Melt honey and butter together in a saucepan; pour over popped corn in a large mixing bowl.
Toss until corn is well coated.
Add nuts and mix.
Spread corn mixture on greased cookie sheets and bake in a 375° oven until browned.
Stir corn mixture in oven if it begins to brown unevenly or burn.

title: cold pack mustard pickles
directions: Mix cold and pour over packed cucumbers.
Makes 12 quarts.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix together.
Press into 9 x 13 lightly greased pan.

title: pizza duds
directions: Mix ingredients and spread on slices of cocktail bread.
Broil until it bubbles.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; add water.
Beat egg in measuring cup and add mayonnaise to fill to 1 cup.
Add all together and mix. Lightly grease 8 x 8-inch pan and bake in 350° oven for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Blend cake mix and jello; add oil, then water.
Stir until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add 1 package frozen strawberries.
Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: striped delight
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with 1/4 cup sugar and butter.
Press firmly in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese with sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Fold in half the whipped topping.
Spread over crust.
Prepare pudding as directed on package, using 3 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over cream cheese layer. Chill several hours or overnight.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding layer.
Garnish with grated chocolate and/or chopped nuts.

title: okra and tomato gumbo(microwave)
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Cover tightly and microwave for 10 to 15 minutes on High.
Taste to see if seasonings need adjusting.
Good served over rice.
A Southern dish that is very tasty!

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix together and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with cherries, if desired.
Cool and serve.

title: creamy cauliflower soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except cream in Dutch oven.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 13 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Pour hot mixture into blender a little at a time and puree until smooth.
Return soup to Dutch oven.
Stir in light cream and heat 2 more minutes.

title: crock-pot creamy swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into small pieces; add salt and pepper.
Place in crock with sliced onion and bell pepper.
Pour mushroom soup over all.
Cover and set at low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Lay chicken in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soups and sour cream together; pour over chicken.
Crumble Ritz crackers over top.
Sprinkle with poppy seed and almonds.
Pour melted butter over the top; cook for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan dream cookies
directions: Sift flour, cornstarch and powdered sugar.
Cut in butter with pastry blender until soft dough forms.
Add nuts, using hands, if necessary, to work until it is smooth and holds together.
Chill until dough is firm enough to handle.

title: chocolate chip cookies(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine and brown sugar substitute.
Add egg and vanilla; cream until light.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to margarine mixture alternately with milk; stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until brown. Makes 36 cookies.
Exchange:
One cookie equals 1 bread and 1/2 fat and contains 100 calories.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Stir in cream cheese, soup and water; let cream cheese melt.
Simmer, but do not boil.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Pour meat mixture over noodles.

title: lemon-buttered broccoli(microwave)
directions: Place broccoli in 2-quart casserole.
Cook, covered, on full power for 7 1/2 to 10 1/2 minutes or until tender.
Stir to break apart halfway through cooking time.
Drain and set aside.

title: tostada grande
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef; drain well.
Stir in seasoning, tomato sauce, chilies and Tabasco sauce; heat until hot and bubbly.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes or until mixture thickens.
Lightly grease a 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Separate rolls or biscuits; arrange in pan.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Spread beans over dough.
Top with meat mixture. Bake at 375° for 18 to 22 minutes or until crust is golden brown. Sprinkle immediately with cheese.
Garnish with lettuce, tomato and onion.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: crawfish dip
directions: Combine sour cream with cream cheese.
Add celery, onion, salt, pepper and lemon juice to taste.
Mince crawfish tails and add to the cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve.

title: cucumber and tomato salad
directions: Slice and peel cucumbers into thin circles.
Slice tomatoes (peel if you wish).
Mix all ingredients together.
Serve chilled.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix the first three ingredients above and spread 1/2 of mixture in a buttered and floured 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Bake 350° for seven minutes.

title: first birthday cupcakes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line muffin cups with paper baking cups. In large mixer bowl, stir together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Add eggs, shortening, buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat on low speed of electric mixer 1 minute, scraping bowl occasionally.
Then, beat on high speed for 3 minutes.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 full with batter.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan to wire rack.
Cool.
Frost with One-Bowl Buttercream Frosting. Garnish as desired.
Yields about 2 1/2 dozen cupcakes.

title: peanut butter spread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Serve with raw vegetables, chips or crackers.

title: salsa verde
directions: Prepare onions and peppers; remove stem end and seeds from peppers.
Dice onions and saute in heavy small pot.
When golden, add garlic.
After a minute, add diced hot peppers.
Simmer for 10 minutes, adding water to keep to stew consistency.
Add tomatoes and simmer another 5 minutes.
Add a little flour for thickening and adjust with water to maintain stew to soup viscosity.
Add salt and a little vinegar for bite.
Good on most things.

title: italian burgers
directions: Mix beef, onions, sweet peppers, basil, oregano, garlic and black pepper. Shape into 4 burgers. Coat a nonstick skillet with nonstick spray and warm over medium-high heat. Add the burgers and brown on both sides. Add tomatoes and cook for 10 to 12 minutes. Serve burgers on toasted bread and top with 1 tablespoon cheese and 1 tablespoon of tomatoes and another toast slice.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Boil chickens with salt and pepper.
Take off bone.
Save 2 quarts stock.

title: amish zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs together; stir well.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in with the first ingredients.
Add vanilla, grated zucchini and nuts.
Put in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: hot vegetable dish
directions: Mix the first five ingredients and pour into casserole dish. Crush Ritz crackers and mix with butter.
Place on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° until hot or bubbly.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Pour over the hash brown potatoes in casserole dish.
Mix the margarine and crushed corn flakes. Spread over mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Mix soy sauce, sugar, Accent, ginger and oil in bowl.
Pour over chicken wings.
Marinate overnight or put in Ziplock bag with chicken and freeze.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream by hand the sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Add oil.
Mix together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts, then fold in 4 cups of diced raw apples (6 medium sized Winesaps are best).
Put in a well-greased and floured sheet cake pan. Sprinkle a 6 ounce package of butterscotch chips over top of batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 50 minutes.
Do not use mixer.

title: herbed biscuits
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large bowl.
Cut in margarine with a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Add buttermilk, stirring with a fork, just enough until ingredients are moistened.

title: mom's peach marmalade
directions: Wash, peel and pit peaches.
Put through food chopper, using a fine blade.
Place in saucepan with lemon juice, sugar and butter. Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Stir in pectin and marmalade.
Let cool, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes.
Pour into hot jars and seal.
Makes 5 pints.

title: chicken florentine with fresh mushrooms
directions: In medium size saucepan, combine chicken breast and onion with water to cover.
Cover and poach over medium-low heat until just white throughout, about 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, melt margarine in a large frying pan.
Add mushrooms and cook until tender, about 5 minutes.
Preheat broiler.
Place spinach in an 8-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with nutmeg, salt and pepper to taste.
Arrange chicken in single layer over spinach.
Top with mushrooms.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Broil 1 to 2 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: peanut butter frickles
directions: Mix all ingredients and with a teaspoon drop mixture on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° or until cookies are puffed but still soft.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: pineapple muffins
directions: Stir together the flour, baking powder and salt. Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in egg until blended.
Add flour mixture and pineapple.
Stir
only until moistened.
Turn into paper lined muffin tins. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 12 large or 24 to 36 tiny muffins.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all with a spoon.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan 45 minutes at 350°.
Ice while hot with:

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Cook raisins in cup of water 5 minutes and cool.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and mix well.
Add raisins and vanilla, then add dry ingredients which have been mixed together. Add nuts last.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased tin pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400° (until light brown).
Batter may be stored in refrigerator and baked as desired.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease bread pan.
Sift together first three ingredients, set aside.
In a large bowl, gradually cream margarine and sugar together until fluffy.
Add eggs and milk.
Alternately add bananas and dry ingredients to margarine and sugar mixture.
Mix thoroughly after each addition.
Add nuts, if desired.
Bake for one hour or until a toothpick, when inserted into middle of loaf, comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.

title: fake pineapple
directions: Remove peeling and seeds from squash.
Grate squash.
Mix all ingredients well and simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Process 30 minutes in hot water bath.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in other ingredients.
Spread on top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit and nut fudge
directions: Put the sugar, milk and molasses in a saucepan.
Stir until dissolved.
Boil to 238° or until a little of the mixture forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Stir in the butter and chocolate.
Allow to cool.
Beat until creamy.
Add nuts, fruits and vanilla.
Pour into greased tins.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: bing cherry-coke salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple.
Set aside.
Heat juice enough to dissolve jello.
When cooled, add cokes.
When slightly thickened, stir in fruit.
Pour into mold or bowl and refrigerate until congealed.
If desired, add chopped nuts at this time.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add a small amount of dressing to beef; set aside to cool.
Combine remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Add beef and mix together.
Crunch up Doritos; add right before serving.

title: pepper relish
directions: Mix thoroughly; place in jars and seal.

title: "quick" lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and Eagle Brand milk together thoroughly. Fold in Cool Whip; stir with spoon until smooth.
Pour into the crust; chill for 2 hours.
It's light and fresh!

title: marinated salad
directions: Mix first five ingredients and set aside.
Place carrots in 9 X 13 pan.
Sprinkle with 1/3 of onions.
Place broccoli over carrots sprinkle 1/3 of onions.
Place cauliflower on top and sprinkle with remaining onions.
Pour oil mixture over all and refrigerate overnight.
Before you serve, drain off oil mixture and toss.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Mix all ingredients together. Marinate overnight, stirring several times.
You can garnish with cherry tomatoes cut in half before serving.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cut up bacon; fry with onion until bacon is crisp and onion is transparent.
Add vinegar and water to pan; when heated, add sugar to taste (sweet and sour).
Slice boiled potatoes into large ovenproof dish.
Pour hot dressing over potatoes; toss and place in warm oven until served.
Cover to avoid dryness.

title: gingered pork chops
directions: Sprinkle pork chops evenly with salt, pepper and sage.
Saute chops in margarine in a large skillet about 10 minutes on each side, until browned.
Remove meat; set aside.
Add mushrooms and spices to skillet; saute until mushrooms are tender.
Stir in orange juice; cook 2 minutes longer.
Return meat to skillet; heat until piping hot.

title: pork chops
directions: Season pork chops with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Then mix honey and mustard.
Pour over pork chops and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: brenda's spicy chili
directions: In skillet, cook onions and ground beef together until beef is brown and onions are translucent.
Salt and pepper to taste. Drain and empty into a large pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add 4 to 5 cups of water and bring to a rapid boil.
Simmer for 1 to 2 hours.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to melted butter and egg and beat well, then add orange juice and beat again.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chocolate macaroons
directions: You also need parchment paper.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook on top of stove until thoroughly mixed.
Ready instantly to use in case you forget to buy ready-to-use at store.

title: parmesan onion canapes
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients. Spread on bread. Place on a baking sheet and broil about 2-3 minutes. The canapes should be golden and bubbly. Makes 36.

title: cereal cookies
directions: Cream fat until soft.
Add sugar gradually; cream until fluffy.
Add the well beaten eggs.
Sift the soda with the flour. Add the remaining ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheets; bake in 350° to 375° oven.

title: copper pennies salad
directions: Slice carrots and boil in salted water until fork-tender. When cool, alternate layer of carrots, pepper rings and thinly sliced onion rings.

title: pinto bean nachos
directions: Put chips on a baking sheet. In a saucepan heat beans and salsa until hot. Spoon over chips then sprinkle with cheese bake at 350 degrees until cheese melts. Add jal. and enjoy.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Wash spinach well to remove sand.
Separate leaves and cut off roots.
Bring water to boil in pot and add spinach.
Boil, uncovered, for about 2 minutes.
Drain and chop fine.
Melt butter and blend in the flour.
Add milk slowly and then the cream; stir constantly until smooth.
Bring to boil for about 1 minute.
Add chopped spinach.
Mix and heat through.
Add salt and grated onion; mix well.
Heat for another minute.
Serves 6.

title: world famous roast beef
directions: Line roaster with aluminum foil with enough excess to wrap roast.
Mix soy sauce, wine, sugar and water.
Stir in onion soup mix.
Pour over roast and wrap in foil.
Cook 4 to 5 hours at 300°.
(Makes delicious gravy.)

title: chicken-in-soups
directions: Combine soups and wine.
Add chicken.
Bake 1 hour, covered, at 350°.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, shortening, sugars, egg and vanilla thoroughly.
Stir in remaining sifted dry ingredients. Spread in ungreased oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until done.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix butter, eggs and sugar.
Add pineapple with juice; mix well.
Add bread; mix in well.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan for 50 minutes at 375°.

title: french cherry pie
directions: Beat cream cheese with sugar and vanilla.
Whip pint of cream well; fold in cheese mixture.
Pour in crust.
Chill 6 to 8 hours. Spread can of pie filling on top.
Decorate with cream, if desired.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add oil, then vanilla. Mix flour and apples with this.
Bake 1 hour at 325° in loaf pan or large flat pan.
While still hot, pour Buttermilk Icing on it, punching holes to allow icing to seep in.

title: chicken & beer
directions: Place cut-up chicken in a 4 quart cooking pot.
Add all the ingredients to pot.
Add all the ingredients to pot and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until tender, approximately 1 hour. Add liquid if ingredients are getting thick.
Should be a medium gravy consistency.

title: whip cream icing
directions: Beat Crisco and butter together.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat 5 to 10 minutes.
Add hot milk slowly; beat well.
Add vanilla and beat until creamy.

title: stir-fry beef or chicken
directions: Heat oil in nonstick pan.
Stir-fry meat until done.
Cut vegetables up and combine with meat.
Pour soy sauce over mixture and stir until coated.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Bring first five ingredients to a boil and let boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and quick oats.
Stir well and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let harden for a few hours, then serve.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend oil and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift all the dry ingredients together and mix well.
Add carrots, pecans and vanilla.
Bake in three 10-inch greased and floured cake pans for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost with the following.

title: honey dressing
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients, then add the rest of ingredients. Use mixer and blend well.
Keep in refrigerator.
This can be used with any fruit salad.
Serves 12.

title: marinated salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and cover with salad dressing.
Let marinate overnight.

title: scalloped potatoes and pork chops
directions: Layer sliced potatoes with pork chops in crock-pot.
Pour over top the mushroom soup, celery soup and milk.
Grate Cheddar cheese on top and cook on low for several hours, until potatoes are tender, about 5 to 6 hours.
Velveeta cheese slices on top could also be used.

title: fancy holiday cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar, extract and milk.
Stir in flour and fruits.
Refrigerate for a few hours.
Drop from spoon on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: chopstick tuna
directions: Combine soup and water.
Add noodles, celery, tuna, cashews and salt and pepper.
Toss lightly.
Place in ungreased dish (10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch).
Sprinkle few noodles over top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until heated.
Garnish with drained oranges.

title: kidney bean relish
directions: Chop onion, celery and eggs together.
Add beans, mayonnaise, relish and other seasonings.
Refrigerate.
Serves 6.

title: barbecue beef burgers
directions: Mix together well and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve on hot hamburger buns.

title: venison roast
directions: Trim fat from roast.
Season meat.
Place in roasting pan, cover with apple slices.
Cut onion over all.
Sprinkle with Worcestershire and add water.
Cover and cook at 250° for 6 to 7 hours.
Add additional water if needed.
When done, discard liquid. Carrots and potatoes may be added halfway through cooking, also celery.
Serves 14 to 18 people.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix altogether.
Put in middle of big round loaf of Hawaiian bread.
Make a nest in bread by scooping out the middle of the loaf.

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, melt morsels and margarine.
Stir in crumbs and nuts.
Mix well.
Press half of mixture in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Beat in milk, vanilla and egg.
Mix well and pour over crumb mixture and top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Cut in squares.
Store in refrigerator.

title: sour cream coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare a 7 x 3 inch loaf pan. Sift flour with salt and soda, set aside.
Beat butter with sugar with electric mixer till light and airy, add vanilla and egg, beat till fluffy.
Stir in 1/2 flour mixture, beat until smooth.
Add sour cream, beat until smooth, follow with other 1/2 flour, beat 30 seconds until smooth.
Spread 1/2 batter in pan, sprinkle with 1/2 topping, repeat.
Bake 30-35 minutes till pulls away from pan and springs back lightly when touched.

title: pear pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until it looks done.
Let cool.

title: church windows
directions: Melt stick of margarine and chocolate chips together.
Let cool.
Mix with marshmallows.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate. When cold, cut into squares.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Put fudge topping in hot water (sealed) so it will be easier to spread.
When cake is cool, spread fudge topping over cake. Chill for a few minutes.
Add creme de menthe to large whipped topping and whip.
Spread on top of fudge.

title: hot punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except red hots.
Take some of the mix and put in a small pan along with the red hots and melt over low heat. After red hots have melted, pour this in other mixture and mix well.
Heat to serve.

title: mushroom mousse
directions: In a skillet, saute mushrooms in butter until liquid has evaporated.
Soften gelatin in chicken broth; add marjoram and heat to dissolve.
Remove from fire and add sherry.
Place mushrooms and broth mixture in blender or processor.
Add egg yolks and remaining ingredients except for the cream and egg white.
Blend until smooth.
Add cream and blend again.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: In microwave bowl melt butter and cream cheese, stirring at 30 second intervals until melted.
Gradually add milk and Parmesan cheese until hot.
Best if stirred with wire whip.
Serve over cooked noodles.
May also be cooked on stove top over medium high heat in heavy saucepan.
Stir constantly.
Serves 4.

title: cherry pie
directions: Pour juice off cherries and save.
Add sugar, flour and cornstarch to juice.
Heat, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add cherries, almond flavoring, food coloring and butter.
Pour in 9-inch pie crust.
Add top crust.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in 425° oven 10 minutes, then in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done.

title: fruit juice punch
directions: Make syrup with water and sugar. Boil 5 minutes. Cool.
Dilute frozen juices according to directions on can. Add orange juice, lemonade and grape juice to syrup. When ready to serve, add ginger ale. Serves 24.

title: marinated salad
directions: Bring to boil the sugar, oil, vinegar and water.
Cool to lukewarm and pour over sauerkraut, pepper, onion and carrot. Chill; keep in covered bowl.
Will keep 2 or more weeks.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Clean the chicken. Cut into pieces. Add the salt, minced garlic and pepper to the chicken. Put in a kettle and add bay leaf, vinegar and water. Cover and let simmer until the chicken is tender and the liquid has practically evaporated. Add fat and fry meat until brown. Serve hot or cold.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Melt and bring to a boil oleo and water.
Add cocoa.
Cool a little, then add flour, sugar, salt, eggs, vanilla, vinegar, sour cream or buttermilk.
Butter and flour cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Drain off the oil.
Cut up onion and peppers very small.
Mix together cornbread mix.
Use a Pyrex pan, if possible.
Pour 1/2 of cornbread mix into pan.
Spread evenly. Pour 1/2 of sweet creamed corn on top of mix.
Sprinkle cheese on evenly.
Spread all of the meat over the cheese.
Sprinkle onion and peppers on meat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread evenly. Bake until done.
Serves 4.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Blend together butter, dash of pepper, flour, sugar and salt. To this mixture, add chopped onion and sour cream.
Put 2 well drained cans French-style green beans in a buttered baking dish. Cover with sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle generously with grated cheese.
Cover with crushed cornflakes and bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and chop apples.
Mix with peanut butter and stir in Cheerios.

title: fruit pizza(beautiful dessert)
directions: Make cookie dough as directed.
Press into disposable pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together.
Spread over baked cookie dough.
Decorate with sliced fruit.
Some ideas:
red and green grapes, strawberries, raspberries, blueberries, kiwi, etc.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: scalloped parsley potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut into wedges or slices.
Cook potatoes in a little water for about 10 minutes.
They should not get mushy.
In a saucepan, combine butter, milk and flour.
Whisk together.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Cook for about 5 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, parsley and potatoes.
Heat slowly.
Season to taste.
Sprinkle with extra parsley when serving.
For a more pungent flavor, add a little grated nutmeg.
For a low-fat alternative, substitute 1/2 cup vegetable broth for 1/2 cup milk.
Preparation time 40 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a well-greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rich butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and add sugar, then eggs, flour and vanilla.
Take a very small amount of dough, spread thin and top with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: raspberry cake
directions: Beat margarine with electric mixer until creamy.
Gradually add sugar and beat until well blended.
Beat egg whites until stiff, set aside.
Beat egg yolks until thick.
Add to first mixture alternately with milk, beating after each addition until smooth. Add vanilla, then fold in egg whites.
Divide evenly among 3 greased and floured 9-inch layer cake pans.
Bake in preheated 450° oven about 10 minutes.
Turn out on racks to cool.
Spread filling and frosting between layers and on top.

title: spiced cocoa
directions: Mix all together. Store in container.

title: kay's strawberry jello
directions: Combine Jell-O with boiling water.
Add all other ingredients. Pour half the mixture into a 9 x 9-inch or 7 x 11-inch dish. Chill until firm.
Spread sour cream on top, then add rest of mixture. Chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place soup, water, onion and rice in baking dish.
Stir together.
Lay chicken in, skin side up.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, beating well.
Add eggs and molasses; mix well.
Combine flour and next 4 ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk; begin and end with flour mixture.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 1 1/2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar after you remove from oven.

title: dessert gingerbread
directions: Cream butter, add sugar and beat until light.
Add molasses, milk and egg.
Mix and sift dry ingredients and add them to the first mixture.
Bake in moderate oven (350°).
Top with whipped cream.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pie filling in the bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine dry cake mix, nuts and melted butter.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until golden brown.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: broccoli squares
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain.

title: cheese dip
directions: Cut Velveeta cheese into small pieces.
Put in a large skillet over low heat, brown ground beef while cheese melts.
Drain.
Add ground beef, cheese soup and picante sauce.
Leave over low heat until all cheese has melted and all ingredients are blended well, stirring often.
Pour over chips or place in a small bowl and dip chips one at a time.
Great for small parties and holidays. Delicious.

title: easy pork chop casserole
directions: Butter bottom and sides of 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole.
In skillet, brown pork chops on both sides.
Remove and set aside. To saucepan add butter and lightly saute onions.
Do not overcook. In strata fashion, layer chops in bottom of casserole, layer of sliced potatoes, then onions.
Pour 1/3 of soup mix over top. Repeat with second layer of chops, etc. ending with top layer of potato slices.
Pour remaining soup mix over top and cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chops are tender.
Serves 4.

title: prune cake
directions: Combine oil, eggs and sugar.
Combine flour, salt, soda and spices.
Add to oil mixture.
Add buttermilk, coconut, nuts and prunes.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12 1/2 x 2-inch pan. Bake for 40 minutes at 300° or until done.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Brown onion and celery slightly in oleo.
Beat eggs, milk, pepper and baking powder.
Add about 1/2 cup broth to moisten. Stir all together.
Pour into baking dish and bake about 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: bacardi rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Grease and flour 10-inch tube or 12-inch Bundt pan. Sprinkle nuts over bottom of pan.
Mix all other ingredients and pour batter over nuts. Bake 1 hour. Cool. Invert. Prick top. Add glaze.

title: ooey gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, 2 beaten eggs and melted butter; place in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Place softened cream cheese into 1/2 stick melted butter.
Mix well.
In separate bowl, mix together drained Mexicorn and drained green chilies.
Pour butter mixture over corn; stir together. Bake for 25 minutes at 350° or until hot and bubbly.
Yummy!

title: 7-layer lettuce salad
directions: In an 8-inch square dish, layer the first 6 ingredients in order listed.
Blend salad dressing with sugar and cream.
Add to top of salad, then sprinkle cheese and bacon on top.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight before serving.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: hot spinach balls
directions: Put uncooked spinach into sieve and press out liquid.
Add other ingredients.
Form into balls and place on cookie sheet and freeze.
Put into plastic bag until needed.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen balls.

title: spring salad
directions: Dissolve lemon jello with water. Add orange concentrate.
Mix well. When slightly thickened, add pineapple and bananas.
Place in mold.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Blend in egg and vanilla. Mix in flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Roll in walnut size balls and press with a sugared glass.
Bake at 425° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: lemon butter
directions: Put first four ingredients in double boiler.
Stir, add egg, put on medium heat, stir constantly and cook until smooth.
Take off heat and add butter.
Stir.
Chill.
Pour in small jelly glass.

title: irish potato soup
directions: Boil the water in a saucepan.
Add potatoes, carrot, onions, thyme, bay leaf and clove.
Cover over low heat for 45 minutes. Force the mixture through a sieve.
Add milk, cream, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Correct seasoning. Serve hot.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice by box directions and set aside.
Place broccoli in boiling salt water and boil for about 4 minutes.
Drain broccoli well and place in large container and add remaining ingredients. Mix all ingredients well, including rice and salt to taste.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: clemson barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken in Pyrex dish.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over chicken pieces.
Cover dish with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: skoby's creamed corn
directions: Cook corn as directed on package.
Mix all other ingredients except bread crumbs. Pour over corn and stir well.
Pour into casserole dish and bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix together
1st
six	ingredients.
Stir in Jiffy mix and bake in
8-inch square greased pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: top of the stove meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into a loaf.
Brown loaf on all sides in a large frypan in oil.
Add onion and saute until lightly browned.
Add water, cover and let simmer 1 hour or until tender. Remove loaf and make gravy from drippings.

title: baked mashed sweet potatoes with marshmallows
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In small saucepan, heat half and half, sugar, butter and salt over low heat; stir until butter has melted.
Beat egg yolks in a medium size bowl.
Gradually beat in half and half mixture.
Beat yolk mixture into potatoes.
Beat egg whites and fold in.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole and top with marshmallows.

title: pizza cups
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Press biscuits in muffin tin. Fill with meat mixture; top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all together, adding cornbread mix last.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or longer in 9 x 9-inch square pan.

title: tomato and mozzarella summer salad
directions: Place tomato (stem side down) on plate.
Cut thick slashes into tomato, keeping base intact.
Cut Mozzarella in thick slices and insert into cut tomato.
If desired, drop slices of garlic between cuts.
Sprinkle fresh chopped basil, salt and pepper. Drizzle with good olive oil.

title: apple sausages with cornmeal mush
directions: In large saucepan, heat 1 cup water, the candies and food color until candies melt.
Place apple rings in syrup; simmer until tender, about 20 minutes.
Place links in skillet.
Add 3 tablespoons water.
Cover; simmer for 8 minutes.
Remove cover; cook until well done, turning sausage to brown evenly.
Serve hot sausage links and apple rings with Cornmeal Mush.
Makes 5 servings.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 350°.
In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Add cocoa and
stir until dissolved.
Add hot water and stir again.
With wire whisk, stir in sugar, flour, salt, vanilla and milk.
Stir until batter is smooth.
Mix in pecans and pour into pie crust.
Bake on preheated cookie sheet for 50 minutes or until custard sets.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, sugars and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: zippy tuna dip
directions: Drain tuna, break up into flakes.
Gently stir in mayonnaise, yogurt, olives, peppers, green onions and cilantro.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done.
Pull cooked chicken apart and off the bone.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Crush bag of Doritos and put on top of chicken.
In large saucepan, blend the two soups, broth, Velveeta and Ro-Tel.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Pour over Doritos.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well each time.
Sift together the flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Add the flavorings.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350° until cake tests done.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and sprinkle with powdered sugar. Serves 10 to 12.

title: sweet potato custard (pie)
directions: Measure cooked, mashed potatoes and put in large mixer bowl to process on low speed to mash well.
Add margarine while potatoes are hot.
Add sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 1 hour until well set and lightly browned.
Yield:
1 nine-inch pie.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix first 4
ingredients together.
Sprinkle flour over fruit and mix.
Set aside.
Cream
butter and sugar.
Add 1 at a time the eggs.
Add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Combine batter with fruit and pecans.
Mix well.

title: up-to-date macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook pasta.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in large pot; add flour and stir.
Stir in broth and milk.
Cover and cook over medium heat until it thickens and boils.
Reduce to low. Stir in cheeses and seasonings.
Stir until melted.
In large skillet, melt 1 tablespoon butter.
Stir-fry vegies until desired doneness.
Mix pasta, vegies and cheese sauce.
Top with Parmesan.

title: pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cover roast with flour mixture.
In large skillet, add 3 tablespoons butter.
Brown roast on all sides.
Remove roast and place in large roasting pan.
Arrange onions, potatoes and carrots around roast.
Sprinkle on soup mix over roast and vegetables.
Add water.
Cook for 2 hours, covered.
Add water if needed.
Cook for 25 minutes or longer, uncovered, until veggies and roast are brown and tender.

title: football-shaped cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9-inch square pan at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes. Cool.
Cut 4 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch edge off opposite 2 ends of cake (football shaped).
Frost football with frosting, rounding out edges.
Cover generously with coconut.
Decorate with candy corn and chocolate chips in center for lace.
Place curved licorice lace on each side of center decorations.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Let roll mixture rise 1 time.
Roll out on floured surface in a rectangular shape.
Combine sugar, butter and cinnamon.
Spread generously over all dough surface.
Roll dough as for jelly roll. Cut in 1-inch slices and place in cake pan.
Do not use cookie sheet.
Let rise again.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Mix enough coffee with powdered sugar to make a thin icing.
Brush over rolls with pastry brush.

title: praline pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine 2 1/2 cups flour, baking powder and soda.
Add to cream mixture, alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Dredge pecans in remaining 1/2 cup flour.
Stir pecans and vanilla into batter
Pour into 2 greased and floured 10-inch tube pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan 15 minutes.

title: wild rice shrimp bake
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Meanwhile, in a large skillet, saute the shrimp, green pepper, onion and mushrooms in butter until shrimp turn pink.
Add the soup to the rice; stir into the shrimp mixture.
Transfer to a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with croutons.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: chocolate haystacks
directions: In saucepan bring sugar, cocoa, milk and butter to full boil. Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop quickly from teaspoon on waxed paper; cool.
Yields 48.

title: cheesy baked egg
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Spread on bread making slight hollow in center.
Fill with unbroken yolk.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and fresh ground pepper.
Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven. Lunch only.

title: egg salad mold
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over water in saucepan.
Place over low heat; stir constantly until gelatin dissolves, about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in salt, lemon juice and Tabasco.
Gradually blend into mayonnaise.
Chill, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Turn into a 3-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold and garnish with salad greens.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tortellini pesto soup
directions: Bring broth and onions to boil.
Stir in tortellini.
Reduce to medium heat.
Cook 3 minutes uncovered.
Stir in pea pods.
Cook additional 3 minutes.
Stir in pesto sauce.
Heat and serve.

title: cheddar snack crackers
directions: Beat margarine and Cheddar cheese. Add flour gradually. Stir in Rice Krispies and Tabasco to taste; may be omitted but adds zip.
Place by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten with palm of hand. Bake 10 to 15 minutes in 350° oven
or until lightly browned. Makes 5 dozen.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add to mixture.
Add apples and pecans last.
Pour into greased tube pan. Sprinkle lightly with cinnamon sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: burritos
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain grease.
Add chili beans, burrito seasoning and 1/2 cup of water.
Simmer about 15 to 20 minutes. Fill tortillas with bean mixture.
Layer with lettuce, cheese, tomato and onion.
Fold and place more cheese on top.
Place in the microwave for 15 to 20 seconds.
Add hot sauce and sour cream, if desired.

title: caesar salad
directions: Tear cleaned romaine into bite size pieces.
Combine remaining ingredients in container and shake well.
Toss with lettuce.
Add croutons, fresh sliced mushrooms and freshly grated Parmesan or Mozzarella cheese, if desired.

title: baked turkey stew
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in hot margarine or butter until tender.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Add undrained tomato and juice cocktail.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Add turkey. Transfer to 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover; bake in 375° oven 20 minutes or until heated through.
Season with salt and pepper. Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Boil giblets in lightly salted water.
Remove meat from necks. Chop all fine or put through meat grinder.
Reserve liquid for broth.
Use bouillon to make up remainder of broth needed for 9 or 10 cups.

title: copper pennies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let set overnight.
Serve as a vegetable or salad.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: summer fruit dip
directions: Whip ingredients together; store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Makes an excellent dip for fresh fruit.
(Strawberries, cantaloupe, honeydew, apples.)

title: jay's chili(yields 8 servings)
directions: In Dutch oven, saute first four ingredients in hot oil until tender.
Add meat, 1 pound at a time, stirring until meat loses redness.
Drain; add water.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring after each addition.
Simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours, stirring frequently.
Season to taste with garlic salt and pepper, if desired.
Serve with Pillsbury Cornbread Twists.

title: hot cheesy seafood dip
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in top of a double boiler; bring water to a boil. Reduce heat to low; cook, stirring frequently, until cheese melts. Stir in next 3 ingredients. Transfer mixture to a chafing dish; sprinkle with onions, if desired. Serve warm with tortilla chips or Fritos. Makes 4 cups. Can freeze. Can do ahead.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add combined flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
