Mix well.
Stir in oats.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Throw in a cup of crushed pecans. Bake 8 to 9 minutes for a chewy cookie or 10 to 11 minutes for a crisp cookie.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Remove to wire rack. Makes about 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix strawberry cola and Jell-O in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Let cool. Slice strawberries in pie crust. Refrigerate until jelled and then top with Cool Whip and strawberries.

title: pasta dish
directions: Boil pasta.
Set aside.
Spray nonstick pan with oil.
Saute peppers and onion until tender.
Add pasta and stir; add soy sauce and water.
Let simmer about 10 minutes.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Prebake the pie shell until almost done.
While this is baking, cook the filling.

title: miss smith's homemade pretzels
directions: Mix dry yeast and water.
Add sugar and salt.
Add flour. Knead dough until smooth.
Cut off pieces.
Roll pieces of dough with your hands and shape.
Place on cookie sheet and brush shapes with egg.
Sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 425°.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Break eggs over apples and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients. Bake in 350°
oven in 8 x 8-inch pan, 45 minutes.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Cut chicken into strips, brown lightly with onions and garlic in oil.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, seasoning and green peppers. Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice and remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes.
Stir before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Peel the potatoes and peel and slice the onion.
Boil both together until the potatoes are tender.
Add butter, salt, pepper and milk; mash until fluffy.
Cook the spinach, covered, without water, until tender (frozen spinach need only be thawed).
Drain thoroughly and chop fine.
Heat the undiluted soup over a low flame; stir in nutmeg, then the spinach.
Save out about 3/4 cup of the potato mixture for a border.
Spread the remainder in the bottom of a buttered casserole.
Top with the spinach mixture. Cut up the cheese into 1-inch wide strips and arrange on top of the spinach like spokes.
Border the edge of the casserole with the rest of the potatoes, fluffing them up with a fork.
Place under broiler to melt and brown the cheese.
Serves 6.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil cut-up chicken.
Add celery.
Bring to boil.
Cook until done.
When chicken is done, debone chicken.
Bring broth to boil. Add tomato sauce and noodles.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 30 minutes. Add deboned chicken.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 30 more minutes.

title: yummy sandwich
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and use as a spread for the bread slices.
Put any kind of sliced sandwich meat and sliced cheese over the filling, adding a little mayonnaise between the meat and cheese and other slice of bread.
(A variety of meats, breads and cheeses in the same batch makes for a real surprise package!)
Fresh and moist and yummy!!

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together. Chill. Serve with crackers or chips.

title: tiptop angels(yield: 8 servings)
directions: Dip pieces of cake quickly into melted butter.
Coat with brown sugar.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes. Serve with coffee and ice cream.

title: finger paint
directions: In cold water dissolve gelatin (let set).
In 1 cup water dissolve laundry starch.
Put starch into 2 cups hot water and cook until boiling (over medium heat).
Remove from heat and add gelatin mixture.
Add soap flakes or detergent.
Stir until dissolved. Cool.
Put into separate jars and add food coloring.
Use on glazed shelf paper.
Let dry. it can be ironed on with medium-heated iron and used to decorate items such as wastebaskets, etc.

title: buckeye balls delight
directions: Line cookie sheet with waxed paper.
Mix peanut butter, vanilla, and sugar with your hands until smooth.
Shape into small balls, place on waxed paper, and refrigerate.

title: savory baked chicken
directions: Combine salad dressing, lemon juice and seasonings; mix well. Pour over chicken; chill several hours or overnight.
Reserve salad dressing mixture.
Place chicken skin side up on a rack in a baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes, brushing occasionally with salad dressing mixture.

title: cool whip frosting
directions: Mix milk, sugar and pudding mix together with wire whisk. Let mixture thicken for several minutes. Fold in Cool Whip.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: In a large bowl, mix together corn meal, flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Then add eggs, milk and oil to the corn meal mixture.
Stir in chopped jalapeno peppers, onion and cheese. Pour into a well-oiled pan and bake at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: christmas rainbow cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Bake in 2 well-greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans for 15 minutes.
Poke with fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Do not remove from pans.
Dissolve each package of jello separately in 1 cup of boiling water.
Pour raspberry jello over one layer of cake and pour the lime jello over the other.
Chill for 4 hours.
Unmold one layer onto serving plate and top with 1 cup Cool Whip.
Unmold second layer onto first.
Frost top and sides with remaining Cool Whip.
Chill. Garnish with gumdrops flattened and cut to resemble holly.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Remove bones and skin from salmon.
Flake well.
Add green pepper, onion and egg; mix well.
Add bread crumbs.
Form into loaf.
Bake in greased loaf pan in preheated oven at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: scripture cake(look up the references in the old testament.)
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar; beat until light.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Beat in honey.
Mix dry ingredients and add alternately with milk to the egg mixture. Beat until smooth.
Stir in nuts and fruits.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch) lined with wax paper.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour, or until done.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes.
Turn cake out on rack and peel off paper. Turn right side up to cool.
Enjoy!

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Heat oil in a skillet and add zucchini, onion, parsley and the spices.
Saute mixture over medium heat, stirring often until zucchini is done but still crisp and tender.
Toss in chopped tomatoes and cook for 5 minutes.
Turn mixture into a serving dish and sprinkle with the parmesan cheese.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions. Drain, rinse and set aside. Put broccoli in a microwave-safe dish; cover with plastic and cook for 3 minutes. Add the minced onion and continue cooking for 1 to 2 minutes. Drain well and squeeze the extra moisture out with the back of a spoon.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Shape into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, flour, syrup, melted butter and crushed pineapple.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes or until filling is set.

title: caramel sauce(microwave)
directions: Place sugar and water in 4-cup microwave-safe glass measure. Cover tightly and microwave on High for 7 to 8 minutes, until syrup turns light gold.
Mixture will be extremely hot.
Let stand for 2 minutes, then remove from microwave and gradually stir in cream and vanilla.
Microwave, uncovered, for 1 to 2 minutes more, until golden brown.
Cool slightly, then pour into clean jar or container.
Cover tightly and refrigerate.
Makes 1 1/2 cups. Good over ice cream or fresh pears.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain the can of salmon well.
Add eggs (beaten lightly), onion, milk and enough flour to give the right consistency to shape into balls.
Roll in corn flakes and fry in Mazola oil. Drain on paper towels and serve while hot.

title: lions club ranch beans
directions: Soak beans 4 hours or overnight.
Add tomato sauce, canned tomatoes, onion powder, chili powder and bacon ends.
Add water to cover.
Bring to a boil and simmer covered until done.
Add water as necessary to keep beans covered.
About an hour before serving, season to taste with salt, pepper and liquid smoke.
Serves 50 to 70.
Cooking Time:
8 hours.

title: burger bean bake
directions: Cook bacon, crumble into small pieces.
Cook ground beef and onion, drain.
Add bacon to meat and the remaining ingredients.
Mix well, put into baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: beef with peppers
directions: Heat skillet; add oil and crushed garlic (optional).
When garlic turns brown, remove.
Add beef; cut in small, thin pieces and fry a few minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add soup stock and continue to cook a few minutes.
Add mixture of cornstarch, soy sauce and water.
Cook until sauce thickens, stirring slowly.
Add green pepper and onion.
Add ginger, chopped fine.
Heat thoroughly and serve hot.
Serves 4 to 6.
May be served over rice or chow mein noodles.

title: reese's cups
directions: Mix; roll into small balls.
Dip in dipping chocolate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil noodles and strain.
Heat milk and add cheese; cut into small pieces.
Simmer until dissolved.
Add mushroom soup.
Slice eggs; pour all ingredients over noodles and mix.
Season to taste. Bake about 1 hour in 350° oven, covered.

title: summer casserole
directions: Cut wieners into thin slices.
Saute green pepper and onion in butter.
Stir in bread crumbs, beans, wieners and cheese.
Place in a 4-quart casserole dish.
Cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg.
Mix well.
Add milk and mix. Add salt, soda and baking powder to flour; mix with sugar mixture.
Add nuts, cherries and dates.
Chill mixture.
Use a teaspoon and drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lime and chocolate dessert
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and let set until slightly congealed. Chill large bowl and beaters.
Pour in evaporated milk and beat until it stands in peaks.
Combine with chilled and whipped Jell-O mixture.
In another bowl, combine chocolate wafer crumbs with melted butter and spread 1/2 of the mixture on the bottom of a 13 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Pour in the Jell-O mixture and spread remaining crumbs on top.
Chill overnight if possible.

title: farfalle carbonara
directions: In a nonstick skillet coated with cooking spray, saut garlic, onions, ham and peas 2 minutes or until soft.
Add white wine and simmer 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Whisk together next 5 ingredients and add to pea mixture.
Cook mixture over medium heat 1 to 2 minutes or until thickened.
Add 1/4 cup water and cooked pasta to skillet; cook 2 minutes or more to heat through.
Season with freshly ground black pepper and Parmesan cheese to taste. Makes 6 servings.

title: dreamsicle fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter and condensed milk.
Boil to soft-ball stage (approximately 5 minutes).
Add Marshmallow Creme and vanilla chips.
Mix well.
Remove 1 cup of mix.
Add orange flavor and color to what's left in the pan.
Stir well.
Pour in 9 x 13 dish. Pour 1 cup of removed mix on top and swirl with knife.
Put in fridge until set.

title: muffin pizzas
directions: Split English muffins in half.
Toast, if desired.
Top each half with 1 1/2 tablespoons of chili sauce, 1 tablespoon of shredded cheese, a sprinkle of Italian seasoning and 2 of the pizza garnishes.
Arrange pizzas on a paper towel in the oven. Microwave for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
The more pizzas you cook, the longer the cooking time.

title: eggplant and okra
directions: Put in saucepan.
Cover.
Cook slowly 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon finely chopped parsley.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lime cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; set aside.
Cream the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; set aside.
Whip condensed milk, then add cheese mix and beat.
Then add jello and mix.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.
Reserve a few cracker crumbs to garnish top.

title: strawberry salad(dressing)
directions: Leaf lettuce, red lettuce, romaine or iceberg mixed greens. Red onion cut into rings and separated.
Add a pint of strawberries, sliced with 6 - 8 almonds.
Mix dressing ingredients and set aside.
Mix greens, strawberries, onion, and almonds.
Pour dressing over and serve immediately.

title: fresh coconut icing
directions: Bring all ingredients except 1/2 cup of half and half with cornstarch dissolved in it to a bubbly boil.
Stir in cornstarch mixture and continue cooking and stirring for 8 to 10 minutes. Put frosting on your favorite yellow or white cake layers while frosting is hot.
This will frost three 9 x 13-inch layers or four 8-inch square layers.
It's very juicy.

title: grandma latty's apple rolls
directions: Roll dough thin in circle.
Put 1/2 cup apples in center.
Top with 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Wrap dough up around apples and sugar. Place rolls in 6 x 10-inch pan.
Put a pat of butter or margarine on each roll.
Bake in a 425° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Take from oven and allow to cool slightly.

title: french fry casserole
directions: Cover bottom of casserole dish with ground beef.
Cut onion over this layer.
Place crinkle cut French fries over onion.
Pour cream of mushroom soup (diluted with 1/2 can of water) over fries. Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes at 350°.

title: esoteric salad
directions: Drain and save liquids from oranges, pineapple and peaches. Combine liquids.
Add concentrated orange juice and enough water to equal 3 cups of liquid.
Pour in saucepan and add the pudding mixes.
Heat to top of stove, stirring constantly, until the mixture comes to a rapid boil.
The mixture should now be thick with fish-like eyes.
Let this mixture cool.
Add fruit and enjoy.

title: chicken-vegetable gumbo
directions: Remove tip and stem from okra.
Slice 1/4-inch slices and set aside.
Coat a large Dutch oven with cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add onions and next 4 ingredients.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add okra, tomatoes and next 6 ingredients.
Stir well.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Add chicken; stir well.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Yield: 2 quarts.
Good served over rice!

title: toffee
directions: Oil an 11 x 15-inch baking sheet with edges.
In heavy 3-quart saucepan, combine butter, sugar and salt.
Stir well with wooden spoon and place over moderate heat.
Bring to boil, stirring occasionally to dissolve sugar.
When mixture boils, wash down sides of pot with pastry brush dipped in water or use wet paper towel.
Continue cooking over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, but not touching sides of pan, until syrup reaches 290° on candy thermometer.
Pour mixture into oiled pan and allow to cool partially, then score toffee into squares with a knife.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Pour pineapple with juice in boiler along with jello.
Mix well.
Bring mixture to a bubbling boil, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; pour into serving container and refrigerate until it starts to thicken.
Then stir in buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Return to refrigerator until set.

title: texas millionaires
directions: Combine brown sugar, white sugar, syrup, butter, milk and vanilla.
Allow this mixture to come to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Add, very slowly, making sure not to stop the boiling, 1 cup evaporated milk.
Cook over a moderate flame until the mixture reaches a soft ball stage.
Add pecans and pour into a large buttered pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into squares.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add extract.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Continue to cream until light.
Add lemon juice.
Place 1/2 of crumbs in the bottom of an 9-inch square pan.
Spread mixture on top.
Add cherry pie filling.
Cover with whipped topping. Sprinkle rest of crumbs on top.
Refrigerate; cut into squares.

title: caramel pie *
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, flour and salt.
Add milk and vanilla.
Bake in unbaked pie shell for 1 hour with temperature at 350°.

title: grandpa louie mollnar's gravy
directions: Take juice from roast, with half the onions and bell peppers. Bring to a boil. In another container take 1 cup of water and 1 cup of flour and mix until thick. Add to boiling water and you're good to go.

title: smoky crescents
directions: Cut sausage links in half so you have 24 short
links.

Unroll crescent roll dough and spread it out flat. Cut the 8 triangles lengthwise into 3 triangles each. This will give you 24 long, thin triangles of dough. Starting at the wide end of each dough triangle, place a short sausage link on dough; roll up. Repeat. Place rolls on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with barbecue sauce or mustard for dipping, if desired.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix well and pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover top with buttered crumbs before baking.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add pepperoni and onion and cook on low for 5 minutes with lid on.
Add beef mixture to the remainder of ingredients. Mix well in a large bowl.
Spread evenly into an 8 x 11-inch baking dish and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: caramel crunch popcorn
directions: Cover 2 baking sheets with aluminum foil and spray with nonstick cooking spray.
Spread the popped popcorn on the baking sheet in a single layer.
In a medium nonstick skillet, combine the sugar, margarine and syrup; bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly (about 3 minutes).
Continue cooking and stirring until the mixture turns a light caramel color, about 5 minutes.
Don't overcook or the caramel will brown and burn. Remove from the heat and slowly stir in the vanilla.
Pour the caramel mixture over the popcorn.
When the caramel has cooled, break it into bite-sized pieces.
Makes 24 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese. Add Marshmallow Creme. When well blended, add Cool Whip. Serve with chunks of melon, cantaloupe, honeydew, pineapple, apple, banana, etc.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: In a colander, toss cucumbers and salt.
Place colander in sink or bowl and let drain for 2 hours.
Mix sugar, vinegar and celery seed in large bowl until sugar dissolves.
Add cucumbers, bell pepper and onion; toss to mix.
Spoon into clean jars.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.
Can be refrigerated for 4 months.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: party punch
directions: Combine grape juice and ginger ale.
Pour into punch bowl or glasses.
Garnish with berries.

title: thrifty tennis casserole(simple, hearty, but good)
directions: In 2-quart greased casserole, layer potatoes, onions and wieners.
Salt and pepper each layer and pour on enough sauce to lightly cover.
Repeat until all ingredients are used up, topping with remaining sauce.
Cover and bake at 350°
for a couple of hours, or bake at 250°
for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Freeze for 12 hours.
Will keep for 3 months.

title: brandied pear
directions: Slice
pear
in thin slices;
sprinkle with lemon juice and add sweetener, then the rest of ingredients.
Toss lightly and let stand 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Stir the sugar, flour and cocoa together.
Combine the eggs and vanilla; beat while adding can of milk.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured Pyrex pie dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: salmon log or sandwich spread
directions: Scrape skin, bones, etc. from salmon and mash finely.
Beat in rest of ingredients.
Roll in chopped pecans and chill 6 to 8 hours.
Makes 2 logs.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Cream margarine. Add cheese, flour and salt. Mix well. Add rice krispies. Shape into small balls. Place on cookie sheet and flatten. Bake at 350 degrees until done.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and brown sugar.
Mix egg and vanilla extract.
Mix flour, salt and baking soda.
Combine all 3 mixtures and add chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: zucchini stuffing casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in a little boiling salt water until tender. Drain.
In saucepan, cook carrot and onion in 4 tablespoons butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Brown ground beef; add to carrot and onion mixture.
Add 1 1/2 cups stuffing cubes, soup and sour cream.
Gently stir in zucchini.
Put into casserole dish.
Melt remaining butter; add rest of stuffing cubes.
Toss and put on top of casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: busy day dinner
directions: Place all ingredients in large roasting pan.
Preheat oven at 300° and bake, covered, 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serve over noodles.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Core and seed green pepper.
Put through coarse blade of food processor.
Put green pepper, cucumbers, onion and garlic in large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt.
Add cold water and ice cubes.
Let stand 2 hours.
Remove garlic and drain vegetables.
Mix sugar, vinegar, mustard seed, celery seed and turmeric in large boiler. Add vegetables.
Bring to boil on high heat.
Remove from heat and pack in sterilized jars.

title: frozen strawberry pie
directions: Combine in large mixing bowl the strawberries, sugar, egg white and lemon juice.
Beat with electric mixer at highest speed until soft mounds form, about 5 to 8 minutes.
In another bowl, beat the whipping cream until thick.
Fold into strawberry mixture by hand.
Spoon into baked shell.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Freeze until firm, 4 to 6 hours.
Cover.

title: favorite pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients by hand and pour into pie shell.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Combine undrained pineapple and eggs.
Mix sugar, flour and salt; stir into pineapple mixture.
Pour into greased shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Toss bread cubes into melted butter. Spoon over pineapple.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Add cheese to dry jello and mix.
Add water and juice.
Cool to soft consistency.
Add pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.
Add Dream Whip; fold in gently.
Pour into container or mold and refrigerate.

title: jefferson davis pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add butter and beat until well blended. Add cream, eggs and vanilla and blend until smooth.
Pour into 2 unbaked 9-inch pie crusts.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, then lower temperature to 325° and bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pepsi-cola chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except rice in Dutch oven.
Bake about 1 hour or until chicken is tender and thoroughly cooked.
Serve with rice or noodles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pickled cabbage syrup
directions: Bring sugar and vinegar to slow boil for 5 minutes.
Cool and pour over grated cabbage, carrots, celery and green peppers.

title: microwave baked trout
directions: Rinse trout under cool water and pat dry.
Season with salt and pepper.
Combine garlic powder, bread crumbs and cheese in a bowl and mix well.
Dip trout in egg white, then in crumb mixture, coating well.
Loosely wrap each trout in plastic wrap or wax paper
and place in large microwave dish.
Cook on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until trout flakes easily.
Garnish with parsley sprigs.

title: oriental flank steak
directions: Place steak in large shallow dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over steak.
Let stand several hours, stirring occasionally.
Broil or grill steak to desired doneness. Cut into thin slices on the diagonal.

title: red punch for 50
directions: Mix and freeze for 3 hours or more.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and boil 5 minutes.
This is very good on any meat.

title: corned beef and cheese pie
directions: Arrange corned beef slices in pie shell.
Beat together remaining ingredients and pour over beef.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until firm.

title: cherry tarte
directions: Drain cherries.
Combine 2/3 cup cherry juice with pineapple, tapioca and sugar.
Bring to a boil and cook until tapioca is clear.
Add cherries.
Remove from heat.

title: fruit swirl
directions: Put all ingredients in blender; blend until thoroughly mixed. Serve immediately.
Makes four 1-cup servings.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Cut ice cream into blocks.
Line pan with blocks of ice cream. Pour syrup over ice cream.
Crush Oreo cookies and sprinkle over entire pan.
Top with Cool Whip and small amount of crushed Oreos. Keep in freezer until ready to serve.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Drain two cans of broiled mushroom crowns.
Hollow out and chop enough of the pieces to make 3 tablespoons.
Cook pieces with the chopped onion in 1 teaspoon salad oil.

title: tingler
directions: In a blender, mix juices and bananas on medium speed for about 1 minute.
Add tofu, cottage cheese, berries and yogurt; mix for 1 minute (longer if a lighter drink is desired).
Add sparkling mineral water; stir.
Serve over chipped ice.
Makes 5 cups.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Season ground beef with salt and pepper and form into meatballs about 1 inch in diameter.
Brown in skillet.
Drain pineapple slices, reserving juice.
Mix the pineapple syrup, pickles with juice and cornstarch.
Add to skillet.
Cook and stir until gravy thickens and is clear.
Add the pineapple slices, cover and cook 5 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Melt butter in water.
Mix everything else and chill 1 hour. Roll into balls and wrap about 1/3 piece of bacon around each. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream the butter and sugar. Add egg, milk, vanilla and almond extract.
Beat well!
Add flour and baking powder gradually to mixture.
Put into cookie press.
Press onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: butchertown brown bread
directions: You also need 6 gold lined No. 3 tin cans.

title: easy spaghetti bake(6 servings)
directions: Fry bacon.
Add onions and garlic; cook until soft.
Add meat; brown lightly.
Stir in seasonings, tomato sauce and water. Cover; simmer for 25 minutes.
Break 1/2 spaghetti into greased 1-quart casserole.
Cover with 1/2 sauce and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake in medium oven (350°) for 30 minutes. Uncover; bake 15 minutes longer, until browned and bubbly.

title: toasted coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix per box instructions and bake in a sheet cake pan. Prepare topping (while cake bakes) by mixing remaining ingredients together. Spread over warm cake and return to the oven and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sesame chicken cutlets
directions: Beat egg in bowl.
Add salt, pepper, lemon juice and lemon peel.
Set aside.
Mix sesame seed and bread crumbs together. Place each breast half between 2 pieces of waxed paper and flatten to thickness of 1/4-inch with mallet.
Dip breasts in flour, then egg mixture, then crumbs.
Place in single layer on waxed paper. Refrigerate at least 1/2 hour before cooking.
Melt butter in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add breasts and cook until golden brown on both sides, 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve on warm platter.
Garnish with lemon slices and parsley.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: orzo with lemon and herb
directions: Bring vegetable stock to a boil in a large saucepan.
Add orzo and cook for about 8 minutes until just tender.
Drain and toss with herbs and lemon juice.
Season with pepper and salt.
Serve hot, room temperature or chilled.
Can be made up to 6 hours in advance.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken breasts and hearts of palm
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wrap each chicken breast around a heart of palm.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and pepper.
Fasten with toothpicks.
Place seam side down in buttered Pyrex dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Serve with Hollandaise Sauce in packets.

title: strawberry cream roll
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon-colored.
Beat at high speed. Add vanilla and sugar; beat until fluffy and thick.
Add dry ingredients all at once.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: low country boil
directions: Mix 1/4 cup
Tabasco
sauce,
tablespoon
salt and 2 teaspoons seafood seasoning
in a large bowl or pan.
Marinate fresh shrimp in the
mixture for 30 to 45 minutes.	Cut onions in rings and let
boil
in
water
or	beer for 5 minutes, cut sausage in chunks and bring to a boil, let simmer until juices permeates from
sausage
and
remaining
seasoning, celery and green pepper, simmer for 5 minutes, add corn, then shrimp, let simmer for 10
to
15 minutes occasionally stirring to be sure all shrimp and pieces
of
corn have been immersed in boil for at least 5
minutes.
Place
on
platter
and	serve with your favorite seafood sauce.
Serves 6 to 10 people.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Dissolve jello in water. Add all other ingredients. Pour into greased and floured cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until center comes out clean on toothpick.

title: lemon cream puffs
directions: In a saucepan, bring water and butter to a boil.
Add flour all at once, stirring until a smooth ball forms.
Remove from heat.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Continue beating until mixture is smooth.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 3 inches apart onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 400° for 30-35 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove to wire racks.
Immediately split puffs and remove tops, discard soft dough from inside.
Set puffs and tops aside to cool.

title: texas brownies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour and sugar.
In a 9 x 11-inch microwave-safe dish, combine butter, shortening, coffee or water and cocoa.
Microwave at High power for 2 minutes or until just boiling.
Pour boiling mixture over flour mixture.
Stir to blend.
Add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour mixture into a micro-safe 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Microwave at Medium-high power for 18 minutes, turning dish every 4 to 5 minutes until brownies test done.
They may still appear soft of the surface.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and eggs. Stir in dry ingredients. Roll into small balls.
Roll balls in a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pink delight dessert
directions: Combine pie filling, pineapple and milk together; mix well. Then add Cool Whip; mix again and chill.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Place pasta in a pot of boiling saltwater and cook for about 15 minutes or until pasta is done. Drain and wash pasta, then place in large mixing bowl. Add onions, celery and bell peppers and mix thoroughly. Next, add shrimp, crabmeat, mayonnaise, Creole mustard and Tony Chachere. Mix very well. If more mayonnaise is desired, add more. When salad is well mixed, add ketchup. Stir in ketchup and mix well. When pasta is well mixed, pour into dish and cover. Place in the refrigerator for about 2 hours. Serve chilled.

title: pork chops - southern baked
directions: Trim fat from chops.
Mix salt, pepper and garlic into a paste.
Rub into pork chops.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Arrange chops in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes longer.

title: calico beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: harvest potatoes
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except topping.
Mix well.
Place in 9 x 13-inch well-greased baking dish.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 300° for 40 minutes to 1 hour.

title: better than potato salad
directions: Cook rice and let cool.
Add all ingredients and keep refrigerated.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Add a mixture of the sugar, cornstarch, seasoned salt, dry mustard and onion.
Stir in the milk and melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour. Stir once.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in small serving pieces. Do not flour meat. Brown steak in oil. Add onions, salt and pepper. Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water. Add to meat and simmer 1/2 hour or until meat is almost tender. Add tomatoes and green pepper; simmer 10 minutes longer. Combine cornstarch, cold water and soy sauce. Stir into meat mixture. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly; cook for 5 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray a 10-inch pizza pan with Pam; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except reserved cheese and sesame seed.
Spread cereal mixture in prepared pan to form a crust; sprinkle top with reserved cheese and seed.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, until the cheese melts.
Cool on rack at least 10 minutes before cutting into 8 wedges.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread mix.
In an oblong dish, layer bite size pieces of bread, tomatoes, pepper, onions, bacon and pickles.
Pour 1/2 of mayonnaise and pickle mixture over 1st layer and remaining over top.
Store in refrigerator overnight or at least 2 to 3 hours.

title: petite cheesecakes
directions: You will need 2 dozen paper baking cups.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli per package directions.
Drain and reserve 1 cup liquid.

title: artichoke dip and fried tomatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients in a small casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until golden brown and bubbly, approximately 35 to 40 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer the ingredients in a clear salad bowl.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt butter in skillet and add onion, celery and green peppers.
Cook slowly until tender; add flour and seasoning and stir.
Stir in tomatoes; cook 10 minutes over low heat.
Add shrimp.
Remove bay leaf and lemon slice.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning; spread on platter.
Sprinkle hamburger (optional), cheese, lettuce and tomato over top evenly in layers.
Pour picante sauce over top of everything or serve in bowl on side.
Serve dip with tortilla chips.

title: sauce for hot dogs(ice cream social recipe)
directions: Cut onions fine; barely cover with water and simmer a few minutes.
Add meat; cook.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: champagne salad
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar, set aside. Drain strawberries (don't use juice). Mix bananas, pineapple, strawberries and pecans. Add cheese mixture. Blend in Cool Whip. Pour into a 9 x 13 inch pan (ungreased) and freeze. Can be made a day or two ahead of time. Take out 15 minutes before serving.

title: snicker bars
directions: In large bowl, put ice milk.
Start mixer and add next 3 ingredients in order given; blend after each.
Add Grape Nuts.
Put in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Freeze (it helps to spray pan with nonstick spray).
Cut into 8 bars.
Each one is 1/2 fruit, 1/4 milk, 1/2 protein, 1/2 fat, 1/2 bread, 40 optional calories.

title: tamale corn
directions: Remove	shucks	from the tamales and reserve the liquid (3/4 cup).
Mix	cream-style
corn and mashed tamales.
Grate the cheese
and
add
to
corn and tamales.
Add milk and egg. Add tomato liquid and chili powder.
Sprinkle crushed crackers on top and
dot
with
butter.
May
serve as a meat.
Can be prepared a day
ahead.
Let
stand a little when removed from oven before serving.

title: onion cheese balls
directions: Mix together all ingredients and roll into a ball.
Serve.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well and store in fridge.

title: baked sliced potatoes
directions: Cut unpared into 1/4 -inch-thick slices.
Place overlapping slices in a buttered oven-to-table, 13 x 9 inch baking dish.
Mix Margarine and Oil.
Brush slices with mixture.
Pour remaining over Potatoes.
Sprinkle with Garlic, Salt and Thyme.
Bake at 400 for 25 to 30 minutes or until Potatoes are done and browned at the edges.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: turkey casserole(low-fat)
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Cook peas, onion and celery in microwave, about 6 minutes to steam tender.
Add all ingredients (except cheese) to macaroni and stir.
If mixture appears too dry, add 1/2 cup water.
Place ingredients in baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Cover with cheese, broken into pieces and spread evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
(Tuna and chicken can be used also.)
Can be made ahead of time and baked later.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spread chicken on bottom of sprayed pan.
Mix soups, sour cream, salt and pepper together.
Pour over chicken.
Crumble crackers; add butter and poppy seed.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350° until browned.
Will thicken as it sets.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Take the skin off chicken breasts, debone or use boneless chicken, cut into stirps or chunks and place in large casserole dish.
Stir in cream of chicken soup and 1/2 can of water.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Make up stuffing per instructions (I use only 1/2 of the envelope of spices).
Take chicken out of oven when done.
Spoon in cooked Stove Top stuffing, mix thoroughly, put back in oven for about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: banana punch
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil in a large sauce pan.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Blend in a blender (I do one-half at a time):
pineapple juice, orange juice and bananas.
Mix with sugar water that has been cooled.
Fill 1-quart containers and freeze until ready to use.

title: jalapeno dip
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; saute onion with bacon.
Drain grease. Add Velveeta cheese and let melt.
Add tomatoes and peppers and simmer on low heat.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak onions and cucumbers in salt water overnight.
In the morning, pour off salt water.
Heat vinegar, sugar and spices to boiling.
Add pickles and heat to boiling point.
Fill jars and seal tight.
Makes 6 pints.

title: trisha's cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add pudding, fruit and juice.
Form into ball.
Place almonds on top or try to roll on.

title: baked beans
directions: Boil dried beans for 2 minutes. Cover and let stand for 1 hour. Cook until tender (about 1 1/2 hours).

Pour liquid and beans into baking dish. Add catsup to taste. Add brown sugar to taste. Add vinegar. Sprinkle powdered mustard on top. Add chopped onion and put several slices of bacon on top. Cover and bake at 350° for 3 hours.

title: taco cheese dip
directions: Layer each item on serving dish.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: freckle face taters
directions: Quarter hot potatoes lengthwise and place in a bake and serve dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese over potatoes.
Melt butter in a skillet and add remaining ingredients; stir until mixture is moist.
Crumble mixture over potatoes and broil until cheese melts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: 7 layer bean dip
directions: Layer in a casserole (shallow dish) in order given.
Serve with chips and salsa.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths.
In a shallow bowl combine sugar and cinnamon.
Dip each biscuit piece in butter and then roll in sugar and cinnamon and place in a grease bundt pan.
repeat this process until all biscuits are dipped and placed in the pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
When done, immediately go around the edges with a knife to make sure it comes out with ease.
Invert pan onto dish and gently raise the pan off.
If some sticks to the top you can melt a little butter, with cinnamon and sugar to paste on top.

title: easy chicken noodle soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot; cook on low for about 6 hours.
Chicken noodle soup recipe serves 4.

title: ratitos
directions: Slit each pepper on the side and remove seeds, leaving stem in place.

title: macaroni and cheese with dogs
directions: Bring water to a boil in a large pot.
Add noodles and oil. Let simmer for 10 minutes.

In another pan, boil hot dog pieces. In a large microwavable dish, combine butter, milk and Velveeta. Microwave on high for 10 to 12 minutes or until cheese is melted. Drain noodles and rinse thoroughly with hot water.
Combine noodles, cheese mixture and hot dog pieces.
Mix well and serve warm.
Grated Parmesan, salt and pepper can be added for flavor when serving.
This dish can be reheated and served as a leftover. Serves 6.

title: cheddar cheese chowder
directions: Add boiling water to vegetables, salt and pepper.
Cover. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes until just tender.
Do not drain.
In large pan or Dutch oven, make a white sauce with margarine, flour and milk.
Add cheese.
Stir to melt cheese.
Add vegetables and liquid they were cooked in.
Heat well; do not boil.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes; peel and dice.
Add sour cream and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Spoon into a 2-quart casserole.
Pour 1/2 cup melted butter on the top.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 25 minutes or until lightly browned on top.

title: pie's fruitcake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and eggs.
Add flour, spices and salt; mix well.
Add fruit and nuts.
Stir.
Put mix in pan.

title: 8 layer salad
directions: Layer in order:
Lettuce, celery, carrots, onion and peas. Spread mayonnaise on top.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Top with bacon bits, then cheese.
Cover and chill 4 to 6 hours.
Do not stir before serving.
Keeps several days.
Serves 8 to 9.

title: deviled egg casserole
directions: Halve eggs lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash.
Mix with mustard, 3 tablespoons sour cream and salt.
Fill whites.
Melt margarine in skillet; saute onion, pepper and mushrooms until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pimento, soup and remainder of sour cream.
Place 1/2 of soup mixture in a 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Arrange eggs in single layer in dish.
Pour remaining soup mix over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: quick mix cake
directions: Combine
all
ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Place in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: chocolate peanut goodies
directions: Combine Duncan Hines milk chocolate frosting and Jif creamy peanut butter in large bowl.
Stir with wooden spoon until blended.
Add oats and chopped peanuts.
Stir until thoroughly blended.
Press candy mixture into ungreased 8-inch square pan. Cut in 36 pieces.
Decorate tops with peanut halves.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
Makes 1 3/4 pounds of candy.

title: english toffee
directions: Cook butter and sugar over medium-high heat until color of brown paper bag, 7 minutes or more.
Never remove when yellow and never leave unattended.
Stir in almonds.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Pour melted Hershey bars over top and sprinkle nuts over Hershey bars.
Cool and break into chunks.
Put into refrigerator to cool.

title: jim's cheese sauce(microwave)
directions: Microwave for one minute, stir and pour over hot baked potato. Yields 2 servings.

title: french toast with orange butter
directions: Place bread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine eggs, milk, salt, nutmeg and vanilla; beat well.
Pour mixture over bread. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in electric skillet at 300°.
Remove six slices of bread from dish and cook in butter 10 to 12 minutes on each side or until cooked through. Repeat procedure with remaining butter and bread.
Serve hot with Orange Butter.
Makes 6 servings.

title: carrot fruit salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Stir well. Cover and chill 2 hours.
Gently stir sour cream into carrot mixture.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: creamy swiss and broccoli soup
directions: Boil ham in water 10 minutes; add broccoli. Cook until tender. Gradually add milk to flour, stirring until well blended. Gradually add milk mixture to ham mixture, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add cheese and seasonings.
Cook until cheese begins to melt.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix, then roll in nuts if desired.

title: sugar cream squares
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well.
Pat down in oblong cake pan that is buttered.

title: zucchini muffins or pie
directions: One slice of pineapple topped with a scoop of jellied cranberry sauce.

title: strawberry flip
directions: Clean and cut up strawberries.
Crush ice with an ice crusher (or wrap ice in a dish towel, place on a cutting board and hit it with a hammer).
Mix all ingredients for 1 minute in a blender or shake well in a covered plastic container.
Makes 2 servings.

title: tuna crab salad mold
directions: Mix gelatin in cold water.
Heat over hot water and mix with mayonnaise.
Mix with other ingredients and put in mold.
Chill.

title: vegetable salad
directions: In a large bowl mix together broccoli, cauliflower, peas, celery and green onions.
In a small bowl blend sour cream, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing together.
Pour over vegetable mixture.
Mix.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: potato goulash
directions: Fry bacon until crisp, crumble, add onion, cook until tender and golden.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Place sugar on a baking board and put butter on top.
Kneading gently with the fingers and heel of hand, mix together.
When all sugar is absorbed into the butter, add flour to the board (maybe a 1/4 of the total amount at a time) and knead until all the flour is absorbed and dough is smooth, not breaking apart.
Cut the dough in half and roll each piece to approximately 7-inch in diameter (it will be about 1/2-inch thick).
Crimp the edges and prick all over with a fork.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Mix peaches and cornstarch together to thicken peaches.
Pour on top of cake mix.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until done (cake tester comes out of cake dry).
Serve with whipped cream.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger.
Put all ingredients except cheese and sour cream into a 2-quart saucepan.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
When serving, sprinkle cheese on top and add 1 tablespoon sour cream. The amount of hot peppers you use would depend on how hot you want the soup to be.
Use tortilla chips instead of crackers to complement this soup.

title: pecan sweet potatoes
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Blend cornstarch, brown sugar and salt; mix with butter.
Gradually add orange juice, stirring until thickened and clear.
Put sweet potatoes into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour sauce over sweet potatoes.
Sprinkle with pecans. Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until heated through.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Pour
Sprite over sherbet.
Add cherries.
Mix together lightly, leaving
a
good
portion of sherbet in center.
Pour into glasses.
More Sprite can be added until sherbet is gone.

title: pepper snaps
directions: In a small bowl, combine dry ingredients and set aside.
In a medium bowl, cream the butter and \sugar.
Add eggs; mix well. Gradually add dry mixture; stir just until blended.
Wrap in wax paper or clear plastic.
Put in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Form 1/2 teaspoon of dough into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart.
Bake for about 10 minutes, until lightly browned.
Cool on wire rack. Makes about 8 dozen.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Oil the crock-pot well.
Add all ingredients and mix well. Cook 4 hours on low.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Put first 8 ingredients in pot and boil until broccoli is tender.
Add half and half, soups and cheese.
Heat until all is melted (do not boil).
Stir as it heats.
Serves 8.

title: shrimp scampi and pasta
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Saute onions, parsley and garlic in butter until tender.
Reduce heat to low. Add shrimp.
Cook, stirring frequently, 3 to 5 minutes. Add water, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Pour over cooked pasta.

title: buffalo chili
directions: Brown meat in large pot.
Rinse and drain.
Saute onion in nonstick pan.
Put meat and onion in large pot and add all other ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon tablespoon size dollop into hot oil and gently flatten to about 1/4-inch thick.
Cook about 3 minutes or until golden brown on both sides.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Squeeze lemon juice on shrimp before adding noodles.
Add all ingredients together, mixing lightly.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix first three ingredients with pastry blender.
Spread in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cover with filling.

title: tuna dip
directions: Drain tuna; chop onion and mix with the rest of ingredients in a large bowl.
Dip is fluffier if you use mixer.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: chocolate oatmeal candy
directions: Boil milk, sugar, margarine and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into greased pan.
No further cooking necessary.
Makes 2 dozen squares.

title: hamburger cabbage casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions, drain.
Add all remaining ingredients, except coleslaw.
Stir and blend together.
Place coleslaw in bottom of a 2 qt casserole dish.
Spoon mixture over slaw.
Cover and bake at 400 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes; mix with other ingredients and beat well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven and add topping.

title: brandy alexander pie
directions: Put water in a medium saucepan.
Stir in gelatin until softened.
Add 1/3 cup sugar, salt and egg yolks.
Blend.
Heat slowly until gelatin is dissolved and mixture thickens.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat and stir in liqueurs.
Chill until mixture mounds.

title: beef and bean enchiladas
directions: Brown the ground chuck with onions.
Drain and stir in refried beans.
Remove from heat.
In saucepan, heat soup, milk, water and tomato sauce.
Wrap 6 tortillas in paper towel and heat 1 minute on High in microwave.
Wrap tortillas with meat filling.
Place wrapped tortillas in baking dish.
Add sauce over top of tortillas.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Five minutes before ready to remove, add cheese on top.
Serve with sour cream and black olives.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Saute squash and onion in margarine for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; add seasonings, let cool.
In large bowl, beat eggs; add cheese and stir in squash mixture.
Place roll dough in bottom and sides of baking dish to make shell.
Spread mustard over dough.
Pour in squash mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: cabbage tomato rice casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in a small amount of water until crisp-tender. In a saucepan, combine 1 tablespoon butter, tomatoes, salt, sugar and minced onion. Cook for 5 minutes. Arrange cabbage, tomato mixture and rice in layers in a casserole dish. Combine bread crumbs, cheese and remaining butter and sprinkle over the top. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: best brownies
directions: Mix and pour into 11 x 7-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Put in refrigerator immediately from oven to cool.

title: green rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Pour into large casserole dish and cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour with oven at 350°.

title: chicken a la king with pepper biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 375°f. 190°c. gas mark 5. Prepare biscuits as label directs but brush biscuit tops with egg white and sprinkle with the black pepper.
Bake as directed and keep warm.
Cut the chicken into 2 cubes, and in a non stick 12-inch skillet over a medium heat, in 1 tablespoon of hot oil, cook the chicken until browned and the juices run clear.
Remove chicken to a bowl.

In the same skillet add 1 more tablespoon of hot oil and 2 tablespoons of water, cook the red pepper and onion until browned and tender. Return the chicken to the skillet with any accumulated juices from the bowl.
Stir in the gravy, milk and frozen peas; heat through. Serve with the warm biscuits.
Serves 5.

title: sponge candy
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and vinegar in large heavy 6 quart saucepan.
Stir and cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in a 16 x 11 x 2-inch pan. Add sugar to pineapple and bring to a boil.
Pour over cake while hot, then cool. Add 3 cups cold milk to pudding mix and beat until thick. Pour over pineapple mixture.
Mix Cool Whip and sour cream; spread over pudding.
Sprinkle nuts over pudding, then coconut.
You may add cherries on top, if desired.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: salmon supper
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Saute onion and green pepper in hot fat until onion is golden.
Blend in salt and flour.
Gradually stir in milk and soup.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Add flaked salmon, peas and lemon juice.
Pour into baking dish, 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch.
Top with biscuits.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dill dip
directions: Blend ingredients together until smooth; refrigerate.
This dip is best made the day before serving, to give the herbs time to flavor the cheese.
Excellent as a dip for fresh vegetables or on hunks of sourdough bread!

title: beef-filled macaroni shells
directions: Cook macaroni shells as directed on package, using maximum cooking time.
Drain, rinse with cool water.
Arrange on paper towels to dry.
While shells are cooking, cook ground beef and onion in a large skillet until done.
Drain off fat.
Stir in catsup, mustard, chili powder and garlic salt.
Heat.
Heat shortening to 365° and fry several shells at a time for about 2 minutes or until golden brown; turn once during frying.
Drain on paper towels.
As shells are fried, spoon about 1 tablespoon warm filling into each fried shell.
Garnish with a sweet pickle slice. Serve warm.
Makes 3 to 5 dozen appetizers.

title: cool rise sweet dough rolls
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, undissolved yeast, sugar and salt in large bowl.
Using electric mixer, mix well.
Add butter; blend thoroughly.
Add hot tap water.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Scrape bowl occasionally.
Add eggs and 1 cup more flour.
Beat with electric mixer at high speed for 1 minute or until thick and elastic.
Gradually stir in just enough of remaining flour with wooden spoon to make a soft dough which leaves sides of bowl.
Turn out onto floured board.
Knead 5 to 10 minutes or until dough is smooth and elastic.
Cover with plastic wrap, then a towel.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Prepare Basic Biscuits, except after cutting in shortening, stir in cheese, dry mustard and red pepper. Bake as normal. Makes 12 to 14 biscuits.

title: breakfast in a cup
directions: Combine rice, 1/2 cup cheese, chiles, pimentos, milk, eggs, salt, pepper and spices.
Spray muffin pan and fill 12 cups with mixture.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until set.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and put in bottom of 9 x 9-inch microwave dish.
Spread on cheese sauce.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add to ground beef the salsa and place on top of cheese.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bring to a boil, stirring all the time; then boil for 2 minutes.
Then add 1 teaspoon vanilla and beat with mixer, for about 5 minutes.

title: spam balls
directions: Mix and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Then roll in chopped pecans.

title: okra creole
directions: Microwave okra in 1/4 cup water 9 to 11 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Drain.
Mix cornstarch with small amount of tomato juice until smooth.
Add to okra and stir in other ingredients. Cover and microwave 10 minutes longer.
Stir occasionally.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown chops in hot fat; remove.
Add onion, soup and milk to fat in pan; blend and set aside.
Starting with potatoes, put alternate layers of potatoes and cabbage into 2-quart casserole or 8 x 8 x 2-inch cake pan; sprinkle each layer with flour, pour soup sauce over each layer.
Place chops on top; cover casserole or use foil to cover pan.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: squash and apple bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut squash in half.
Remove seeds and fibers; pare squash.
Cut into 1/2 inch slices.
Stir remaining ingredients except apple slices.
Arrange squash in ungreased baking dish 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inches; top with apple slices. Sprinkle sugar mixture over top.
Cover with foil.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until squash is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vinegar beets
directions: Mix vinegar and cornstarch.
Pour into pan with sugar.
Cook until thickens.
Add beet juice.
Cook slowly until thick.
Add beets.
Add butter.
Cook slowly 15 minutes.

title: stuffing*
directions: Mix together and top breasts (use 1/4 cup on each).
Fold sides in and roll up.
Place, seam side down, in 12 x 7 x 2-inch pan. Pour sauce over.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Uncover.
Sprinkle with 1 cup shredded Swiss cheese and paprika.
Bake 2 minutes until the cheese melts.

title: graham cracker roll
directions: Mix all together. Press this mixture into a mold. Chill overnight. Unmold. Slice and serve. Top with whipped cream.

title: spicy chicken(low-fat)
directions: Prepare in Teflon skillet or on Teflon grill over low heat. Roll each piece of meat in seasoning and cook until done, turning frequently.
When done, top with shredded cheese and cover until melted. Serve immediately.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Put all ingredients, except cream cheese, in double boiler. Cook and stir constantly until thick.
Let cool to room temperature.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy and fold into other ingredients.
Serve with various fresh and canned fruits.
Cut into chunks.

title: american lasagne
directions: Brown meat, garlic and Parmesan cheese.
Add tomato sauce, seasonings and onion.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Cook noodles. In large casserole, alternate layers of meat sauce, noodles, cheese and cottage cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: middle street crumb cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add oil, milk and eggs.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Put batter into ungreased 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar, then cinnamon. Dot top with butter. Bake until tester comes out clean in center, about 50 minutes.
Cool slightly. Cut into squares.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and keep in covered jar.
Use about 2 teaspoons
(more
or less according to taste) per cup of hot water.

title: swedish sweet bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in milk, sugar, salt, eggs, shortening and 2 1/2 cups flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic about 5 minutes.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and milk. Add remaining ingredients. Can be mixed with a mixer until about the last 2 cups of flour. Let rise to double, then punch down and put in refrigerator. Pinch off and let rise as needed. Will keep a week or more in the refrigerator. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: noodles and franks
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
In small saucepan heat tomato soup, undiluted, and frankfurters until hot; add noodles and serve.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: supper pie
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes and gravy mix according to package directions. Spread potatoes in well-greased 9-inch pie plate, covering bottom and sides to make a shell.
Mix ground beef, egg, bread crumbs, vegetables and 1/4 cup gravy.
Mix well.
Spoon carefully into potato shell, patting with back of spoon to level off evenly. Brush edges of potato crust lightly with oil or melted butter. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve with remaining gravy.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat together eggs,
milk, sugar, cinnamon, vanilla and salt. Place bread crumbs	in
1/2-inch
round baking dish. Sprinkle raisins over bread.
Pour
egg mixture over all. Bake in 325° oven for 40 to
45 minutes, until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: mother's gingersnaps
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll dough in small balls with hands, dip each in granulated sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet, 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: baked squash casserole
directions: Cut off tips of squash.
Then cut each into 3 to 4 pieces. Drop into a large saucepan with enough boiling water to cover. Return to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook until tender.
Drain and mash.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Boil and slice potatoes.
Heat in pan the last four ingredients until melted.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oven baked barbecue chicken
directions: Cook onion until soft in hot oil.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 15 minutes (2 chickens or equivalent pieces).
Place chicken skin side up in large pan; do not overlap.
Cover with sauce.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 60 to 90 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: hanky-panky
directions: Brown beef and sausage with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Melt cheese in meat.
Spread 1 full teaspoon of mixture on rye bread and bake on a cookie sheet at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apple salad
directions: Gently mix fruit, celery and pecans.
Mix apple juice, yogurt and margarine until smooth.
Pour over apple mixture.
Serve on lettuce-lined plates.

title: orange rice cream
directions: Make early in day, or one hour before serving.
Cook rice as label directs; refrigerate.
Peel orange, cut into sections; reserve 10 sections for decoration; cut rest in half and sprinkle with sugar; refrigerate.
Just before serving, whip cream stiff and add vanilla.
Fold in rice and halved orange sections (if very juicy, drain off some juice).
Arrange in serving dish; decorate with 10 orange sections and chocolate pieces.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: beef stroganoff - mom's
directions: Cut sliced round steak into thin strips; dust with flour and dash of pepper.
In a large skillet, brown the meat in butter; add mushrooms, onions and garlic and brown lightly.
Stir in beef broth and cover; cook until meat is tender, stirring now and then. Gradually stir in sour cream, cook over low heat for 5 minutes. Serve over cooked noodles.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift flour, cinnamon and salt together.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, oil, vanilla and sifted dry ingredients a little at a time.
The mixture will be thick.
Add the zucchini; mixture will be gummy.
Pour into two well-greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Check at 50 minutes with toothpick.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into a buttered 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until top is golden.

title: paradise jam
directions: Boil prepared fruit 1 minute; add Certo and remove from heat. Stir for 5 minutes to prevent floating fruit. Skim foam if necessary. Ladle into jars. Cover at once with wax. If using jelly jars with 2-piece lids, fill jar to 1/8-inch of top. Screw tops on tight. Invert jars for 5 minutes, then turn upright. After jars have cooled, check seal.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Beat all ingredients in blender on high speed 1 minute or until smooth. Pour into pie plate.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 8 servings.

title: green punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and chill. Add ginger ale at serving time. Serves about 24 (4 ounce) servings.
Ten times amount will serve 250 people.

title: festive pork roast
directions: In large plastic bag, combine first five ingredients; mix well. Add roast, turning to coat on all sides. Cover and refrigerate 3 to 4 days (turning several times a day). Remove meat, discard marinade. Place with fat side down on a rack in shallow roasting pan. Bake uncovered at 325° 2 to 2 1/2 hours. Cover and let stand 15 minutes before carving. Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: orange julius
directions: Put in blender and whip until frothy

title: brownstone front cake
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar and sour cream. Mix. Combine flour, soda, salt and cocoa. Add to creamed mixture. You can add a tablespoon of oil. It helps when cream is thick. Bake at 350° (approximately 1 hour, but check it with toothpick). This is a large cake. It will make 3 layers.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Add onions to 1/4 cup of cooking oil and cook until dark golden brown. Add shrimp to onions and saut. Add well washed rice with water; salt rice to taste. Bring to a boil until almost all the water has evaporated. Stir mixture well. Cover on real low fire until cooked, about 20 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Coat beef with seasoned flour.
Heat oil in Dutch oven, then add beef and brown on all sides.
Drain off fat.
Add onion, seasonings, lemon juice, sugar, Worcestershire, water, tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours, adding more water if necessary.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Melt cheese and soup together.
Add other ingredients plus sausage and stir.
Serve warm.
Very tasty with tortilla chips.

title: italian meat balls and sauce
directions: Simmer together for some time.

title: fish and vegetables
directions: Layer 1/2 of vegetables in an 8 x 8-inch dish.
Season fish; place on vegetables.
Cover with remaining vegetables.
Add water; dot with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Place all ingredients in dish.
Stir.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours before serving.
Yields 12 servings.

title: macaroni delight
directions: Boil macaroni for 10 to 12 minutes.
Place broccoli in pot. When it comes to a boil, put in seasoning.
Drain.
Let cool 5 minutes.

title: amish cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, oil and butter. Add the remaining ingredients, mix well. Roll in small ball and flatten with glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 375° for 8 - 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Defrost and drain broccoli well.
Mix broccoli, cream of mushroom soup, beaten eggs, grated Cheddar cheese, grated onion, mayo and half of melted butter.
Pour in casserole dish.
Top with small amount of bread crumbs and remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rum cake
directions: Boil sugar, water and butter for one minute.
Add rum.
After removing cake from pan, pour the liquid mixture slowly over cake.

title: lemonade or limeade
directions: Dissolve sugar in 1 cup water.
Add lemon or lime juice.
Add remaining cold water.
Serve over ice.
Makes 6 1/2 cups.

title: mimi's texas slaw
directions: Grind vegetables with coarse blade; mix well. Add salt and let stand 2 hours. Drain well. Add sugar, seeds and vinegar. Do not cook. Put in jars in the refrigerator. Keeps for weeks.

title: picadillo(cuban ground beef)
directions: Brown ground beef, drain and set aside.
Saute garlic, onion and olives in olive oil.
Add the browned ground beef, tomato sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer on low heat for 15 minutes.
Serve with white rice.

title: rhubarb punch
directions: Cut into pieces fresh rhubarb and cook in 2-quarts of water until soft.
Strain through cloth bag.
Dissolve sugar in 2 cups of water. Boil 10 minutes.
Cool and add lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Mix rhubarb mixture.
Chill.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.
Makes 1 gallon.
Will serve 24 people.

title: overnight fresh pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers lengthwise in spears or crosswise in slices. Slice onion into rings.
Alternate layers of cucumbers and onions into a large glass or ceramic bowl.

title: sweet 'n sour beans
directions: Heat to bubbling at 325°.
Serves 6.

title: chow mein hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix with all remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with chow mein noodles.

title: easy cherry cheese danish
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine and cream together the cream cheese, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Butter 1 jelly roll pan.
Pat 1 package of crescent rolls into the bottom and a little up the sides of pan.
Bake 4 minutes to set.
Spread cheese mixture evenly on top.
Spread on pie filling.
Stretch remaining roll and lay on top.
It will not completely cover.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.
When cool, sift on powdered sugar.

title: grandma's stuffing
directions: Mix together 1/2 the broth with all the other ingredients. Make stuffing real moist before refrigerating (cover with wet towel)...stuff bird when stuffing is cool. Use other 1/2 of broth in gravy.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry hamburger; drain.
Mix with taco seasoning and simmer for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add rest of ingredients and pour French dressing over all; mix.
(Add Doritos and dressing just before serving to insure freshness.)

title: orange balls
directions: Process vanilla wafers into crumbs in the blender. Add pecan pieces to crumbs and process. Combine crumbs, ground pecan pieces, powdered sugar, orange juice concentrate and butter in a large bowl. Stir until blended. Divide mixture in half. Cover one portion with plastic wrap and set aside. Shape remaining portion into 1-inch balls and roll in coconut. Repeat with other portion. Store balls in airtight container in refrigerator for up to one week.

title: pearl street's chicken and broccoli
directions: Cut broccoli in 1-inch pieces.
Heat butter, garlic and parsley.
Cook for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add wine and chicken. Continue cooking over medium heat.
When chicken is almost done, add broccoli.
Cook a few minutes more, stirring often, then add peppers.
Serve over hot, cooked rotini.
Serves 2.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk.
Bring to full, rolling boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla. Crush crackers fine and add to candy mixture.
Beat until mixture begins to hold shape.
Spread into greased 8-inch square pan. Cool and cut.
Yummy, you will not know this is made from soda crackers!

title: baked cabbage
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Cook cabbage in boiling salted water for 10 minutes.
Drain and let cool; chop finely.
In mixing bowl, blend eggs, 3 tablespoons oleo, cream, salt and pepper; stir in cabbage.
Turn into casserole dish.
Blend remaining oleo and crumbs and sprinkle over cabbage.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: peanut soup
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a heavy 2 to 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Remove from heat and puree until smooth.
Return soup to saucepan and add rice, chili and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer, covered, 15 to 20 minutes until rice is tender.
In a small bowl, mix 1/2 cup of the soup and peanut butter until blended.
Stir in Tabasco sauce. Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove dried chili.
Thin with water if too thick.
Add additional salt if needed.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients. Shape into one-inch meatballs. Brown on all sides over medium heat.
Put meatballs in Pyrex and cover with sauce.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: date nut bread
directions: Pour hot water over dates and soda, cover, let sit for 15 minutes.
Cream sugar and shortening, add well beaten egg.
Add flour, salt and date mixture alternately to sugar.
Cream well and add pecans and vanilla.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 1 hour at 375 degrees.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler; stir in milk.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly until thickened.
Cook, uncovered, 15 minutes more, stirring occasionally.
Beat egg yolks; gradually stir in hot mixture. Return to double boiler.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Line bottom of casserole with vanilla wafers; top with layer of sliced bananas.
Continue to layer wafers, bananas and custard, ending with custard on top. Beat egg whites stiff, but not dry.
Gradually add remaining 1/4 cup sugar and beat until mixture forms stiff peaks.
Pile on top of pudding and bake at 425° for 5 minutes or until delicately browned. Serve warm or chilled.

title: pecan pralines
directions: In a large saucepan mix soda, buttermilk and sugar and boil slowly to soft ball stage.
Mixture turns brown as it cooks, but need stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add flavoring, margarine and pecans. Stir until it begins to look like it is ready to sugar.

title: orange fluff
directions: Follow directions on Jell-O box for orange Jell-O.
Add drained mandarin oranges.
Refrigerate until set.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Wash potatoes real good.
Cut into bite-size pieces (about 1-inch square).
Place clean and cut potatoes into pan with enough water to cover potatoes.
Boil until potatoes are tender, but not falling apart.
When potatoes are done, drain water off and let cool.
Then, in a 9 x 13-inch dish, put cooled potatoes, seasoned with salt and pepper.
Then add a layer of shredded cheese, then a layer of sour cream, then a layer of green onions, then a layer of bacon bits.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mixture will be slightly runny.
Blend in some self-rising flour for texture.
Roll out and cut about 3/4 inch thick so biscuits will rise.
Put either oil or melted butter in bottom of cookie sheet or loaf pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown at 400°.
Pour melted butter over them after baked.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Mix together and store in refrigerator.

title: aunt hattie's pork roast
directions: Saute pork roast with salt, pepper and flour in butter in pan. Put sauerkraut with 1/2 of the juice in a crock-pot.
Cut up the apples (leave skin on) into wedges.
Cut the new potatoes in half. Add the soup mix.
Put sauerkraut in bottom of crock-pot.
Put pork roast in next, then add apples and potatoes.
Cook on low all day (7 A.M. to 4 P.M., approximately).

title: banana pudding dessert
directions: Mix pudding and milk until thickened.
Add Cool Whip and stir until mixed.
Line bottom of oblong pan with graham crackers.
Top with sliced bananas.
Pour 1/2 of pudding mixture on top.
Line with more graham crackers and spread other 1/2 of pudding mixture on.
Line with more graham crackers and finally, top with favorite pie filling (I like strawberry best).
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: herbed meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; work with hands to make certain it is well mixed.
Pack into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: candied popcorn
directions: Keep popped popcorn in oven at 200 - 250 degrees to keep warm. Boil brown sugar, butter, corn syrup, vanilla and salt for 5 minutes.
Take off stove and add baking soda.
Stir well and add to popcorn in a large oven proof bowl.
Stir well and return to oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Stir well and return to oven for another 10 minutes.
Take out of pan and place on waxed paper until cool.
Store in an air tight container.

title: parmesan dill fish fillets
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen.
In mixing bowl, stir together egg white and water.
In another bowl, stir together crushed crackers, dill weed, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Dip fish into egg white mixture, then into cracker mixture to coat.
Cook fish in hot skillet until fish flakes easily with a fork, turning once.
Or bake in the oven at 400° for 45 minutes, turning once.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour 45 minutes.

title: traditional christmas fudge
directions: Combine butter, evaporated milk, sugar and salt in medium heavy saucepan.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, morsels, nuts and vanilla.
Stir vigorously for 1 minutes or until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into foil-lined 8-inch square baking pan.
Sprinkle with additional pecans if desired.
Chill until firm.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: granny's applesauce cake
directions: Mix applesauce and soda; add shortening and sugar.
Blend in eggs.
Mix in flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Bake in oven (350°) for 45 minutes or until well done.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, water and salt in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils, then cook, without stirring, to hard boil stage.

title: cherry raisin walnut shortbread bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease an 8-inch square pan. Combine flour and sugar, cut in margarine until mixture resembles fine meal.
Press into greased pan and bake 20 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Meanwhile, mix eggs, brown sugar and vanilla beating well.
Stir in soda, walnuts, raisins and coconut. Spoon over hot crust, spread evenly.
Return to oven; bake an additional 20 to 25 minutes or until top is set.
Cool, cut into bars and serve.

title: sweet potato snowballs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly butter a cookie sheet.
In a bowl, blend sweet potatoes, brown sugar, butter and allspice. Roll marshmallows separately in mixture, forming balls.
Roll each into coconut.
Place on a baking sheet and cook 5 to 8 minutes or until marshmallows heat but don't melt.

title: jalapeno bread
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
When cooled, mix with remaining ingredients (except biscuits).
Cut biscuits into fourths and place in large bowl.
Pour mixture over biscuit pieces and toss with hands until well distributed.
Put into a lightly greased bundt pan.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat. Drain.
Add soups, pepper and milk until hot. Line baking dish with tortillas, overlapping them and letting them come up the sides.
Pour in meat mixture and top with cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and tortillas begin to brown.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, margarine and other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shells and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done. Makes 2 pies.

title: coffee ring
directions: Place milk, sugar and shortening in saucepan.
Scald milk. Remove from heat. Add salt and cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in two tablespoons warm water and add to mixture.
Beat in flour and knead.
Let rise to double bulk and knead again.

title: lemon pie
directions: Reserve 1/4 to 1/2 cup vanilla wafer crumbs and margarine in a bowl.
Press into bottom and side of 9-inch pie plate.
Mix lemonade and condensed milk in bowl.
Fold in whipped topping. Spoon into pie shell.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs in circle around edge of pie.
Chill in refrigerator for 8 hours.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Mix ingredients except pie crust in pot.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Put in pie crust.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and dot with butter.
Bake for 30 minutes in 425° oven.

title: marble cheese steak
directions: Bake or fry steaks to medium done.
When done, layer sliced tomatoes and sweet onion on top of steaks.
