Cover and bake or fry until tomatoes and onion are soft.
Layer steaks, tomatoes and onions with cheese.
Cook until cheese has melted.
Serve with favorite veggies.

title: veggie burger
directions: Ground bell pepper, onion, garlic, carrot and mushrooms.
(May chop fine in food processor for best results).
Cook 1 cup of couscous as directed on box of pasta.
Add to ground ingredients, then add 1 scrambled egg.
Mix well.
Roll out to patties.
Bake or fry as desired.
Serve on hamburger buns (cheese optional).
May use rice instead of couscous.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Mix all together and roll out into desired size tortillas.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Put aluminum foil around crust after 25 minutes cooking time.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs, salt, soda and lemon juice.
Beat well.
Mix vanilla, flour, apples and nuts.
Bake in 11 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pistachio chocolate chip cake
directions: Blend cake mix, oil and eggs together.
Then add sour cream and pudding mix for 5 minutes.
Grease pan with Crisco (Bundt pan).
Sprinkle bottom of pan with chocolate chips.
Pour little over half of mixture into pan.
Swirl syrup in with knife.
Pour rest of mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Remove from pan while still warm.

title: cheese hash browns
directions: Saute onion and butter together.
Combine sour cream and soup with butter and onion.
Crumble hash browns, if patties; combine with soup mixture and add 8 ounces cheese.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add rest of ingredients in casserole. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spicy nuts
directions: Heat pecans in moderate oven for 5 minutes, stirring once.

title: shrimp-rice parmesan
directions: About 1 hour and 15 minutes before serving, in hot oil in skillet over medium heat, cook rice, stirring constantly, until golden.
Add water, tomatoes, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, onion and carrots.
Cook, covered, until carrots are tender.
Add shrimp.
Cook 5 minutes or until shrimp are tender.
Serve, passing cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: candy bar cake
directions: Combine candy bars and 1/2 cup butter in a heavy saucepan; place over medium heat and stir constantly until candy bars melt. Set aside.

Beat remaining 1/2 cup butter at medium speed with an electric mixer, about 2 minutes or until soft and creamy. Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed for 5 to 7 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears. Stir in vanilla.
Combine flour and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix at low speed, just until blended, after each addition.
Stir in pecans and candy bar mixture.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes on wire rack.
Remove from pan, let cool completely on wire rack.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown ground beef, green pepper and onion in skillet.
Drain grease. Add Philadelphia cream cheese and salsa.
Heat until cheese is melted and place in crock-pot. Serve with "dip size" Fritos corn chips.

title: porridge pie(handy for picnic lunches, or for entertaining friends.)
directions: Lightly beat milk and eggs together in a large bowl. Add first measure of cheese, rolled oats, salt, pepper, herbs and cottage cheese. Drain and flake tuna. Add to bowl. Wash and chop the spinach. Wash and slice the mushrooms.
Peel and grate the carrot. Peel and chop the onion.
Blanch the tomatoes and chop.
Add spinach, mushrooms, carrot, onion and tomatoes.
Mix thoroughly. Put in ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle with second measure of cheese. Bake at 180° C (350°) for 40 to 60 minutes. Serve hot or cold.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Turn crock-pot on high setting while chopping and cutting ingredients.
Combine all ingredients except peas in crock-pot. Cover and reduce heat to low setting.
Cook 7 to 8 hours or until meat and vegetables are tender.
Stir in peas during last 30 minutes of cooking time.
(If using high setting, cook for 5 hours or until tender.)
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: brunch eggs(serves 24)
directions: Scramble very, very, very lightly in butter the eggs and milk until just barely set.
Put layer of eggs in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle half of soup on eggs, sprinkle can of mushrooms and sprinkle cheese on top.
Add second layer.
Sprinkle top with paprika and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: quick cheddar cheese squares
directions: Combine mayonnaise and milk in small saucepan.
Cook on low heat about 5 minutes or until mixture thickens slightly, stirring constantly.
Add Cheddar cheese; stir and heat until cheese is melted.
Serve over cooked chicken, vegetables or pasta.
Makes 1 cup sauce.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onion and drain.
Mix with soup and water.
Put in bottom of pan.
Pour soup over.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Arrange Tater Tots on top evenly.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes or until onions really start to smell.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish.
Spread 1 1/4 cups rice in bottom of pan or baking dish.
Spread 1 package dry onion soup over 1 cup of cut-up chicken.
Mix celery soup with 1 can of water and add to casserole.
Mix cream of chicken or cream of mushroom with 1 can of water and add to casserole.
Bake at 350°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Press rolls in a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Spread sausage over rolls.
Next put cheese, then pour beaten eggs and milk over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Using mixing bowl, stir together butter and sugar.
Stir in egg and milk.
Stir in baking powder and enough flour to make thick dough.
Stir until dough clings together.
On floured surface, using floured rolling pin, roll dough very thin.
Using floured cookie cutter, press out cookies.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.
Sprinkle sugar lightly over tops of cookies while still hot.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream butter and sugar and then add well beaten egg yolks and mix well.
Sift flour and then measure and sift again with baking powder.
Mix vanilla and lemon and almond extracts in the milk and add alternately with dry ingredients.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake 50 to 55 minutes in 350° oven.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Pop popcorn in air popper.
Yields 5 to 6 quarts popped corn. Place
in large bowl.
Combine butter, sugar, syrup and salt in heavy saucepan.
Heat and stir over medium heat until boiling. Then
boil
without
stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir
in
vanilla and soda.
Pour over popcorn and toss well until
all
pieces
are
coated.
Spread on 2 large ungreased shallow
pans.
Bake
in 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every
15 minutes.
Cool
completely.
Break
apart
and store in airtight containers.

title: sun glazed chicken
directions: Place chicken in a baking dish.
Combine all ingredients. Brush both sides of chicken with glaze.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Brush with more glaze.
Bake 10 minutes and brush with glaze.
Bake until chicken is done, maybe another 30 minutes. Serve on a bed of rice.

title: poppy chicken
directions: Place chicken in a casserole dish.
Combine sour cream and cream of chicken soup and pour over chicken.
Melt butter and combine with crackers and poppy seed, then pour over the top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cabbage souffle casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in small amount of water with salt until tender; drain.
Spread bread slices with margarine.
Combine eggs and milk; soak bread in egg mixture until soft.
Add cabbage, cheese, salt and pepper; mix well.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole. Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: summer tuna salad
directions: Mix cooked shells with olive oil, 2 teaspoons lemon juice, salt, pepper, green onion and mayonnaise.
Mix 2 teaspoons lemon juice and dried dill with tuna.
Add to shells mix.
Add peas. Gently mix.
Chill and serve.

title: eagle brand double delicious cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine.
Pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with chips and press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool and cut into bars.
Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: hot vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook spinach as directed.
Drain; set aside.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
Combine mayo, sour cream, cheese and blend.
Stir mixture into spinach, add mushrooms and artichoke hearts.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Slice tomatoes 1/2-inch thick and put on top of spinach.
Saute crumbs in butter until golden. Sprinkle over top of tomatoes.
Bake uncovered 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: pink raspberry punch
directions: Combine sherbet and Hawaiian Punch.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: brown cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then roll by hand into small balls. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Frost with confectioners sugar frosting when cool.

title: ham pot pie
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder. Beat egg and add 1/2 cup milk. Add to dry ingredients. Add shortening.
Add enough milk to make a soft dough. Roll out and
cut into 1/2-inch squares. Drop into boiling broth and add chunks of ham and potatoes. Cook 20 minutes.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown hamburger.
Make rice to box directions, but do not evaporate water.
Add hamburger to rice. Add bean sprouts and chow mein in large pan. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Preparation time:
30 minutes.

title: baked almond chicken
directions: In shallow baking dish, place chicken, then salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with paprika, about 1/2 teaspoon.
Cut up margarine and add, then water.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered. Remove from oven and spread soup over chicken and sprinkle with sliced almonds.
Cover and bake 15 minutes more.
Bake 5 more minutes, uncovered.
Serve with Green Rice.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: *Or you may use a graham cracker crust.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour 2 (9 x 1 1/2-inch) round baking pans. Stir together flour, cocoa powder, baking soda and salt.
In a large mixer bowl, beat the 1/2 cup shortening on medium speed of electric mixer about 30 seconds.
Add the 1 cup sugar and vanilla and beat until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating on medium speed for 1 minute after each.
Add dry ingredients and water alternately to beaten mixture, beating on low speed after each addition until just combined.

Thoroughly wash the beaters. In a small mixer bowl, beat egg whites until soft peaks form; gradually add the 3/4 cup sugar, beating until stiff peak forms. Fold egg whites mixture into batter; combine well.
Turn batter into prepared pans.
Spread batter evenly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake test done.
Cool 10 minutes on wire racks.
Remove from pans.
Cool thoroughly on wire racks.

title: 1000 calorie pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie crusts.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Set aside.
Sift together next 5 ingredients.
To this, add buttermilk, shortening and the yeast mixture.
Roll on floured dough board until thin.
Fold in half, making edges even and roll thin.
Fold in half again and roll until thickness of biscuit desired.
Cut out biscuits and place in an airtight plastic container.
Keep stored in refrigerator until needed.
They will keep for at least two weeks.
Do not let them rise before placing in oven.
Bake at 350° until brown.
This will make about thirty 2 1/2-inch biscuits.

title: southern chocolate pie
directions: In saucepan, beat egg yolks slightly; add 1 cup sugar slowly until mixed and creamy.
Sift dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture.
Mix until all blends; add milk and vanilla gradually and cook on low heat until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Top pie with meringue and brown at 400°.

title: glazed meatballs and apples
directions: Combine egg with milk; stir in bread crumbs and salt.
Add ground beef and mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls; place in shallow pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Mix water, ketchup and brown sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add apples.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Stir together soy sauce, cornstarch and mustard.
Stir into apple mixture and cook 2 minutes.
Using a slotted spoon, transfer meatballs to saucepan. Heat through and serve warm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except walnuts.
Roll into a ball or a log.
Roll cheese balls in walnuts until completely covered.
Wrap in aluminum foil and refrigerate for 1 hour or overnight.
Serve with Town House crackers.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mocha coffee
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in a container with a tight fitting lid.
Add 2 to 3 teaspoons to cup of hot water.

title: squash mix
directions: Saute squash, zucchini and onion until tender.
Add corn and cheese.
Melt.
Serve.

title: garlic roasted chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with lemon juice, garlic powder, seasoning salt and pepper.
Wrap chicken loosely in foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Place chicken in ovenproof dish and bake.
Top with garlic cloves.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: perky cauliflower slaw
directions: Chop or shred cauliflower.
Toss together in large bowl cauliflower, onion and radishes.
Blend together the lemon juice, horseradish, salt, pepper and mayonnaise.
Toss with vegetables until well blended.
Chill, covered, in refrigerator.
Serve in lettuce cups.
Sprinkle each with snipped parsley.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese; add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and baking powder, then vanilla. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice; add all other ingredients to rice and cook 5 minutes on top of stove.
Pour into a covered dish; sprinkle with cheese.
Cook at 400° until cheese is melted or a little brown.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Melt soup in double boiler over hot water.
Add gelatin mixture and stir until mixed well.
Add cream cheese to soup mixture, followed by all other ingredients.
Blend together with mixing spoon and pour in 2-quart casserole mold.
Refrigerate about 8 hours or overnight.

title: fish fillet with spinach
directions: Put fillets in dish.
Cover with thawed spinach.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Cover with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: cheese rotel dip
directions: Put Ro-Tel in pan or double boiler first, then cubed cheese and melt slowly. Stir often.
Add chili and green onions. Stir until heated through.
Serve with favorite chips.
Keeps well in refrigerator for 2 to 3 weeks.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix jellos and cool.
Add crushed pineapple and cheese (cut fine); also add nuts.
Let set up some.
Lay pineapple rings on top with a cherry in middle of each slice.
Chill until set.

title: bacon tomato dip
directions: In medium bowl, stir together all ingredients, except crackers or vegetables until well mixed.
Cover; refrigerate at least 2 hours to blend flavors.

title: spicy mandarin orange muffins
directions: Drain mandarin orange segments well and spread on paper towels while making batter. Sift flour, measure and sift with baking powder, salt, nutmeg, allspice, cinnamon and sugar into a bowl. Cut in shortening until very fine.
Combine egg and milk. Add all at once.
Mix just until moistened. Add orange segments.
Mix lightly until evenly distributed.
Spoon into greased muffin tins, filling about 3/4 full. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden.
Remove. Dip top in melted butter, then in cinnamon-sugar mixture. Serve hot.
Makes 12.

title: camper's cocoa
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
To make cocoa, put 1/3 cup of mix in cup.
Add hot water.
Will keep forever.

title: woodcock
directions: Cut up cheese and add to tomato sauce. Cook slowly. Beat the egg and stir all remaining ingredients into sauce until well heated and cheese is melted.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break bread into small chunks and put in a large bowl.
Add milk and let soak for about 10 minutes.
Crush with hands until blended.
Add eggs, sugar, raisins and vanilla.
Pour margarine into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spoon pudding mixture into pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 or more minutes, until pudding is firm.
Let cool, then cut into squares.
Spoon Whiskey Sauce over individual servings.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, salt, milk, bread and vanilla; bake at 350° in buttered dish until golden brown, approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place milk, sugar and butter in saucepan; stir together over medium heat to mix together well.
Continue stirring until it boils.
Once it boils, do not stir and let continue to boil exactly 5 minutes.
Take off heat and add vanilla, marshmallows and peanut butter.
Stir until marshmallows are melted and mixture takes on a dull appearance rather than shiny.
Pour into buttered dish.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Cut up egg and add to asparagus, then add
mushroom soup with 1/2 can water; mix well. Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: bean-onion salad
directions: Drain beans; add celery and onion.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix with beans.
Let set in refrigerator several hours before serving.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Shell eggs.
Place in hot sterilized jars and cover with boiling liquid.
Seal immediately.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix well and put in graham cracker crust.
Simple and easy.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Melt oleo in 13 x 10-inch cake pan; cool slightly, then add crumbs and the rest of the ingredients on top of each other as listed in recipe.
Do not stir!!!
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. When cool, cut into bars.

title: **christmas fruit salad
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Gradually add sugar, light cream and lemon juice. Mix; cook in double boiler until smooth and thick, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour this over fruit mixture, marshmallows and nuts and mix lightly.
Chill at least 24 hours before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: perfect pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in heavy Dutch oven.
Add meat and brown on all sides.
Remove meat and add onion, celery and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Add rest of ingredients.
Drain off fat.
Add meat.
Cover and cook 2 1/2 or 3 hours.
Transfer meat to warm platter.
Strain and return sauce to stove; work in cornstarch.
Bring to a simmer, stirring often until thickens. Season with salt and pepper.
Slice meat and pour some of the gravy over the meat.
Pass the rest.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until crisp in a small amount of water.
Drain well.
Put back in pan and add cheese and 1/2 of butter.
Melt and mix well.
Add water chestnuts.
Put into casserole dish.
Top with crumbled crackers and remaining half stick of butter, melted. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix all together; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beans 'n rice burritos
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Bring broth, salsa, cumin and salt to boil in saucepan.
Cook rice.
Add rice, beans and tomato to saucepan; return to boil.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes, or until water is absorbed.
Stir in cheese, onions and hamburger.
Spoon mixture down center of warmed tortilla.
Fold one end over filling; roll up.
Serve immediately.

title: kiss cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix peanut butter, sugar and eggs well. Dough will be sticky.
You can dip your fingers in flour, then roll dough into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet about 2-inches apart.
Bake 10 to 14 minutes.
Remove and place Kiss in center.

title: cheesecake
directions: 1. Pour cherry liquid into heavy suacepan. Add margarine, powdered sugar, and raisins. Stir to dissolve sugar.
Bring mixture to a boil for 5 minutes.
2. Remove from heat and pour into large mixing bowl. Let
mix cool completely.
3. Sift flour and spices. Mix 1/2 c. flour and gumdrops.
Add dry ingredients to raisin mix. Fold in gumdrops,
drained cherries, and nuts. Blend well.
4. Spray (2) 9 x 5 x 3 loave pans. Pour into pans. Bake at
at 350° for 40-50 minutes. Let cool in pans for 5
minutes before removing to wire rack to cool. Let sit overnight before slicing.

title: tequila (sunset) beef steaks
directions: Place meat in large plastic bag.
Add all of the ingredients; seal bag.
Chill from 1 to 24 hours; turn bag occasionally.
Drain steaks.
Cook on low to medium flame on grill to desired perfection.

title: jalapeno bread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour half of bread into pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup grated cheese on top.
Add the rest of the bread mix.
Cook at 450° until done.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients; cook in muffin pans.
Fill each only 1/2 full.
Bake at 425° until brown.
Makes approximately 12 rolls.

title: apple squares
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon onto wax paper. Melt butter or margarine in a medium size saucepan over moderate heat.
Remove from heat.

title: chicken pie
directions: Skin chicken and take off bone.
Put into greased casserole dish.
Mix soup and stock.
Pour mixture over chicken.

title: making a happy home
directions: These ingredients, thoroughly kneaded with the salt of good common sense, flavored with the graces of nature and art, music and flowers, will make a paradise of a desert, a palace of a hovel.

title: lemon cheese jello salad
directions: Prepare lemon jello as directed on box.
Add vinegar and sugar; partially set and whip.
Add pineapple and cheese.
Fold in cool whip.
Refrigerate.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs.
cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove egg yolks and mash together in small mixing bowl.
Mix in paprika, mayonnaise and mustard powder.
Spoon into egg shells and sprinkle with paprika.
Cool and serve.

title: kola baked beans
directions: Scrape rind of salt pork.
Score deeply with sharp knife. Place onion in deep casserole; add beans.
Bury pork in beans so only rind shows.
Combine molasses, mustard, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and chile sauce.
Add enough cola beverage to make 1 1/2 cups.
Pour over beans.
Bake in slow oven at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Yields 8 servings.

title: fruit cake bars
directions: Grease and flour 8
x
14 x 2-inch pan.
Pour nuts into pan and press
down.
Melt
margarine and sugar over low heat; remove from heat.	Add
flour,
well
beaten eggs and vanilla; pour over nuts.
Sprinkle fruit over batter.	Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: kraut salad
directions: Chop all vegetables; mix with kraut that has been drained. Mix sugar and vinegar.
Pour over salad.
Let set in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Drain.
May keep for week.

title: cucumber cheese ball
directions: *I prefer pickling (small) cucumbers because they taste better and don't have as many seeds; you can get them at Easyway.
If you do use pickling cucumbers, it will take more than two because they are smaller.

title: carrot-orange-yogurt bars
directions: In
a
bowl
beat
butter or margarine with an electric mixer on	medium	to
high
speed,
about 30 seconds or until softened. Add
about	half
of
the flour, the sugar, yogurt, egg,
baking powder, orange peel and baking soda to the margarine.
Beat
until thoroughly combined, scraping sides of bowl occasionally.
Then beat or stir in remaining flour.
Stir in carrot.
Spread
batter into
a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.	Bake
in
a
350° oven
for 25 to 30 minutes or until a toothpick
inserted
near center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on
a wire rack.
Frost with Orange Yogurt Frosting.
Cut into bars.
Store, covered, in the refrigerator.
Makes 24.

title: barbecued spareribs for fifty
directions: Separate ribs into 8 ounces portions.
Place in roasting pans. Brown uncovered in oven at 350° until browned lightly, about 30 minutes.
Pour off fat.
Pour sauce over ribs.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° until meat is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake an additional 20 to 30 minutes.

title: seven minute icing
directions: Cook slowly the flour and milk until thick.
Let cool.
Cream together the sugar, butter and vanilla.
Be sure to use an electric mixer.
Add the cooled flour and milk mixture; beat well.

title: tuna cracker dip
directions: Mix all together and chill overnight.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook beans with all seasonings and peppers.
Add smoked sausage and simmer until done.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: chicken delight
directions: Boil and bone chicken.
Cut into bite sized pieces.
Combine chicken with the soups.
Add celery, water chestnuts, green onions and almonds (reserve a few to put on top).
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, then spread Chinese noodles over top, then sprinkle on reserved almonds and return to oven for another 10 minutes.

title: fat-free pioneer biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spray baking sheet with spray (no fat). Add Pioneer biscuit mix and milk.
Mix well and turn on floured paper.
Add flour to dust dough and roll to thickness desired. Cut into biscuits and place on sprayed baking sheet or pan.
Bake 6 to 7 biscuits for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: bourbon slushies
directions: Blend frozen bananas and frozen strawberries and serve.

title: beef tips with rice
directions: Melt
margarine
in heavy skillet.
Set aside.
Combine flour, salt and pepper; dredge steak strips in mixture.
Brown in margarine.
Add
bouillon; cover and simmer 1 hour or until beef is
very tender.
Add milk;
cover and simmer 30 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: lipton pepper steak
directions: Cut meat into thin strips 2 inches long.
In large skillet, heat oil and brown meat, turning frequently.
Stir in Lipton onion soup mix and 2 cups water.
Cover; simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in peppers.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes or until meat is tender. Blend cornstarch with 1/2 cup water.
Stir into skillet.
Cook while stirring until thickened.

title: crab dip
directions: Warm the cream cheese to ease the mixing process.
Mix all ingredients.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Brown green pepper, onions, garlic and celery in butter. Combine flour, sugar, salt and cayenne pepper.
Add canned tomatoes, bay leaf and Tabasco.
Simmer all 45 minutes.
The last ten minutes, add small frozen shrimp.
Serve over rice.

title: buffalo style wings
directions: Cut wings
at joints and discard tips.
Mix flour and 2 tablespoons
of
cayenne
pepper together.
Rinse chicken with water and then coat pieces with flour-pepper mixture.
Bake at 400° for
minutes
until crispy.
Melt margarine and add 2 tablespoons
Tabasco
sauce.
For
spicier wings, add optional cayenne pepper.
Dip
each
piece
of chicken into butter mixture. Shake
off excess.
Serve with blue cheese dressing and celery sticks.

title: banana coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in bananas.

title: chocolate-cherry pie filling cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for cake and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove cake from oven.
Make icing and pour over cake.

title: impossible ham and swiss pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Sprinkle ham, cheese and onions on plate.
Beat other ingredients until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake until golden brown, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: bran waffles
directions: Pour boiling water over 100% Bran and let stand.
Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add buttermilk and blend.
Add bran and water mixture, then flour, baking soda, salt and Bran Buds.
Mix thoroughly.
Spoon batter into greased muffin tins and bake at 400° for 16 to 19 minutes or until tops are firm to touch.

title: creamy cheesecake
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients.
Place in spring-form pan; refrigerate.
Beat cream cheese until smooth, beat in egg yolks and 3/4 cup sugar.
In small bowl, beat egg whites and cream of tartar. Fold into cheese mixture.
Bake in 350° oven 1/2 hour.
Remove, raise oven temperature to 425°.
Beat last 3 ingredients.
Spread slowly on top of cake.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix flour, grated cheese and salt. Cream butter, then add mixture.
Blend well. Shape into rolls.
Wrap in wax paper and freeze.
Leave several hours. Remove from freezer and let thaw a little.
Cut in slices and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: chicken chili verde tacos
directions: Combine cabbage, cilantro and salsa in a serving dish and set aside.
Cut chicken crosswise into 1/2 inch wide strips.
In a 10 to 12 inch nonstick pan over medium-high heat, stir oil, onion and garlic for 2 minutes.
Increase heat to high, add chicken, and stir often until meat is no longer pink in center, 4 to 6 minutes. Add cumin and oregano.
Stir for 15 seconds.
Spoon into serving dish.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Blend sugar, shortening, salt and vanilla; stir in beaten egg and flour sifted with baking powder.
Mix smooth.
Stir in nuts. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Soften cream cheese, then add chilies, olives, hot sauce and garlic.
Mix well.
Spread mixture on flour tortillas.
Cover tortillas with approximately 3 slices chicken.
Roll up tightly and wrap in plastic wrap.
Chill in refrigerator at least 2 hours, preferably overnight.

title: child's love cake for mother
directions: Mix well.
Bake in a hearty warm oven, and serve to Mother every day!
She ought to have it in big slices!

title: taco salad
directions: Just add in one large bowl the tomatoes (diced up) and the sliced onions.
Add the diced green peppers.
Break up or slice the lettuce and add it in.
Add in the 2 different packages of cheese. Add the kidney beans (cold).
Brown hamburger, drain and cool.
Add hamburger; then add the bag of Doritos (but hold the top in one hand and smash them into small pieces).

title: nut loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly. Pack into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Keep refrigerated until cold. Cut into blocks.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with mixture.
Cream the cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar, eggs and vanilla and pour over the crust.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Allow to cool.
Spread the blueberry pie filling over cool cream cheese.
Cover with whipped cream.

title: kristen's strawberry jam
directions: Mix strawberries, sugar and lemon juice in Dutch oven.
Heat to boiling, stirring frequently, until translucent and jam is thick, about 25 minutes.
Quickly skim off foam.
Pour jam into sterilized jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Makes 5 half pint jars.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Beat the first 5 ingredients and pour into
a well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together the brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over the cake. Swirl into the cake with a small teaspoon handle.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix in bowl, the brown sugar, flour, salt and pie spice. Add the pumpkin, milk and slightly beaten eggs. Stir until smooth. Pour into a 9 inch unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. This was one of Janice Odom's recipes.

title: meringues
directions: Line 3 cookie sheets with a few sheets of baking parchment. In a large, clean bowl, whisk egg whites and salt until they are stiff, using an electric mixer.
You should be able to turn the bowl upside down without any movement of the egg whites. Carefully beat the sugar into the egg white mixture a little at a time.

The meringue should start to look glossy at this stage. Sprinkle superfine sugar, a little at a time, and continue beating until all the sugar has been incorporated and the meringue is thick, white and stands in tall peaks.
Transfer it to a pastry bag fitted with a 3/4-inch star tip.
Pipe about 26 small whirls onto prepared cookie sheets.
Bake in a preheated oven at 250° F. for about 1 1/2 hours or until pale golden in color and can be easily lifted off the paper.
Let the meringues cool in the turned-off oven overnight.
Just before serving, sandwich 2 together with the whipped heavy cream and arrange on plate.
Makes 13.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Place turkey and chopped onion in a large pot and brown. You may drain if you like but there will be very little grease from the turkey. Mix in remaining ingredients and cook slowly until cabbage is tender. The amounts of cabbage, onion and celery are not critical. Also, you may increase the amount of chili powder if you like. The amount of water may be varied to your taste. A few chopped jalapenos will add a nice touch if you like hot peppers.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
In cake pan pour melted margarine and sprinkle brown sugar on top of margarine.
Arrange pineapple slices on top of brown sugar.
Spoon cake batter over mixture and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix dressing, cheese and Italian dressing.
Place chicken on greased grill over medium coals or rack of broiler pan 5 to 7-inches from heat.
Brush with 1/2 of dressing mixture and grill or broil for another 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: creole shrimp
directions: Cook onions in butter until yellow.
Blend in other ingredients.
Cook slowly, stirring occasionally until thickened (30 minutes).
Stir in shrimp.
May use cooked or uncooked, if uncooked just cook longer until they are done.

title: wilma's tuna supreme
directions: Heat soup, add cheese and tuna.
Add other ingredients.
Serve over chow mein noodles.

title: hamburger garden casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well.
Add chopped celery, green pepper, onions, carrots, tomato sauce and water.
Simmer over low heat for 10 minutes.
Stir in cooked spaghetti, mushroom soup, oregano, salt and pepper; mix well.
Pour into casserole and top with cheese.
Bake in 300° oven for 30 minutes.

title: fabulous fudge
directions: Just 5 minutes cooking - no beating!
Mix in heavy 2-quart saucepan sugar, milk, marshmallow cream, butter and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly over medium heat until boils.
Boil and stir five minutes more.	Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate morsels until completely melted.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread in buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool.	Cut into 30 pieces.

title: peanut butter cookies(school recipe)
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars. Add peanut butter and mix well. Add beaten eggs, then dry ingredients; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Press ball both ways with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until done.
Cookies should not be hard when pulled from the oven.

title: apple crunch
directions: Place apples in an 8-inch square, greased casserole pan. Combine sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over apples. Combine flour, brown sugar and butter. Spread mixture over sugared apples. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until fruit is tender and top is browned. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop raw broccoli and add bacon, nuts and raisins.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour on salad and mix well. Chill.
You may add pimento for color.

title: ginger dip
directions: Drain and chop chestnuts.
Finely chop parsley and chop crystallized ginger.
Combine all ingredients; cover and chill for at least 8 hours.
To reduce fat and cholesterol, fat-free mayonnaise and nonfat sour cream alternatives may be substituted. Serve as a dip with fresh vegetables.
Yields 3 cups.

title: pepperoni dip
directions: Mix sour cream with cream cheese to soften. Add remaining ingredients and mix. Slice top of bread off to make a "lid". Hollow out bread and discard. Fill with mixture. Put lid on and wrap with foil. Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour.
Serve on toasted garlic bread slices. (They are usually in big, clear bags in store bakeries.)

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apples, nuts, flour, soda, cinnamon, sugar and salt in mixer.
Beat in egg, butter and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: shrimp potato boat
directions: Scrub potatoes thoroughly.
Bake or microwave potato until done.
When cool to touch, slice top of potato open lengthwise. Scoop out pulp, leaving a firm shell about 1/4 inch thick.
Mix pulp with other ingredients.
Whip until smooth.
Stir in shrimp. Stuff shells with shrimp mixture and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: baked crab
directions: Saute minced seasoning in butter until it becomes glazy but not brown.
Mix crab meat and crumbs and add cooked seasoning.
Add mustard, mayonnaise, eggs, garlic, salt and pepper; mix well.
Pack into well-greased shells.
Top lightly with crumbs.
Bake in 400° oven until lightly browned.
Serves 10.

title: holiday snack mix
directions: Melt butter; add to melted butter the salts, sauces and onion powder.
Mix dry ingredients in large containers and place in cake pans or roasters.
Pour some of the liquid mixture over it, just enough to slightly dampen.
Bake at 250° for 15 minutes.
Stir every 5 minutes, adding more liquid if desired.

title: cocoa brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla until well blended.
Blend dry ingredients, then mix in.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in well-greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake about 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into 2-inch squares.

title: seafood spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, onion, oregano, basil, red pepper, garlic powder and thyme.
Bring to boiling. Reduce heat.
Cook, uncovered, over medium-low heat, 10 minutes or until mixture thickens slightly, stirring occasionally.
Add shrimp and green pepper.
Cook, uncovered, 10 minutes or until shrimp are no longer pink, stirring occasionally.
Serve over spaghetti.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Thaw frozen bread dough.
Put oil on cookie sheet.
Press dough flat to fit pan.
Turn dough over.
Line dough with sliced pepperoni and Mozzarella cheese.
Roll up like jelly roll; let rise 15 to 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: goodie ice cakes
directions: You will need plastic cups.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup of water.
Combine sugar, egg, milk and 1 cup water.
Add salt and flour.
Knead several times.
Put in bowl; brush with Crisco.
Cover tightly and put in refrigerator until it doubles in bulk.
Punch down and let rise 10 minutes. Make in rolls and let rise 2 1/2 hours or until double in bulk. Preheat oven.
Bake at 425° until done.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix well with hand.
Shape into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
May be made in advance and frozen.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine peanut butter with cream cheese.
Blend with mixer until light and fluffy.
Add confectioners sugar; blend well. Gradually add 1/2 cup milk; mix well on high until mixture thickens.
Fold in 1 (8 ounce) container of Cool Whip.
Spread mixture into graham cracker pie crust.
Cover and freeze.
EAT AND ENJOY!

title: spiced nuts
directions: Whip egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar, cinnamon, salt and nuts.
Melt the butter on large cookie sheet.
Spread nut mixture on melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir often.

title: mandarin chicken salad
directions: Poach chicken in simmered water 10 to 15 minutes or until no longer pink.
Drain, set to cool.
When cool enough to handle, remove skin and bones and shred (be sure to blanch the broccoli!).
Stir water into peanut butter until smooth.
Add soy sauce, vinegar, sesame oil, wine and sugar.
Stir in 1 tablespoon of onions and ginger mix.
Pour over chicken and broccoli-noodles in a large bowl and toss.
Garnish with peanuts.

title: sausage and peppers
directions: In covered skillet over medium heat, cook sausage chunks in 2 tablespoons of water for 5 minutes.
Uncover and cook until sausage is brown on all sides.
Add green peppers, cut into strips, sliced onion, separated into rings and minced garlic to sausage in skillet; cook until peppers are tender, but crisp. Stir frequently.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup, 1 can of water and vinegar.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Cook rice according to package directions.
Serve over rice.

title: butterscotch root beer pudding pop(kids section)
directions: Stir the root beer into the pudding and pour this mixture into the molds.
Place the molds in the freezer until frozen.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add beans.
Put layer of crushed chips in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Put meat on top of that, then a layer of lettuce.
On top of that, sprinkle your onions, celery and tomatoes.
Put sour cream on that as you wish, then your shredded cheese.
Put in oven for 10 minutes at 350°. Serves 6.

title: popsicles
directions: Put gelatin in bowl.
Add boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Add drink mix and sugar and stir.
Add cold water. Pour mixture into popsicle containers.
Freeze.
It is best to use the same flavor gelatin and punch mix.

title: cranberry orange bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Measure flour and blend dry ingredients.
Mix in all ingredients, except cranberries.
Fold in cranberries.
Pour in pan and bake 1 hour. Cool thoroughly before slicing.
Makes 1 large loaf or 3 small ones.

title: sausage nibblers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into bite size balls.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Great for parties and get-togethers.
Good for dipping, too.

title: granny's dressing
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees. Mix breads together first, then add sage, salt, pepper, and onion.

Mix broth, eggs, butter and cream of chicken soup together. Heat all together on stove until hot. Pour bread mixture, if mixture is to loose add extra cornbread. Cook in oblong pan or iron skillet for 45 minutes to 1 hour until golden brown. You may cut into squares or spoon out and serve.

title: yum cookie bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease square pan (9 x 9 x 2). Cream butter and brown sugar in large mixer bowl until light and fluffy. Add egg, milk and vanilla. Beat well.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in skillet and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in one big bowl, then pour into a greased skillet and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pasta fazoul soup
directions: Sear meat first, then drain the fat off.
Saute vegetables with spices, garlic and onion.
Add stock and beans.
Simmer until beans are tender.
Add cooked pasta last.

title: cocoa fudge cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Beat all ingredients on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, for 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally, for 3 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine ingredients in a greased 1-quart baking dish.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Rinse rice.
Cook rice in 1 1/2 quarts milk.
Allow to boil, and then simmer 20 minutes.
Add sugar and simmer until it thickens.
Blend in eggs, beaten in 1/2 cup milk and vanilla. Bring to a boil.
Add cream; boil again, and then cool and refrigerate.

title: chicken stir-fry over rice
directions: Saute vegetables and onion 6 to 8 minutes.
Combine sauce and meat.
Heat well.
Serve over hot rice.
